164 BOOLEAN
165 MmCreateProcessAddressSpace (
166  IN ULONG MinimumWorkingSetSize,
167  IN PEPROCESS NewProcess,
168  OUT PULONG_PTR DirectoryTableBase
169  )
170 
171 /*++
172 
173 Routine Description:
174 
175  This routine creates an address space which maps the system
176  portion and contains a hyper space entry.
177 
178 Arguments:
179 
180  MinimumWorkingSetSize - Supplies the minimum working set size for
181  this address space. This value is only used
182  to ensure that ample physical pages exist
183  to create this process.
184 
185  NewProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process object being created.
186 
187  DirectoryTableBase - Returns the value of the newly created
188  address space's Page Directory (PD) page and
189  hyper space page.
190 
191 Return Value:
192 
193  Returns TRUE if an address space was successfully created, FALSE
194  if ample physical pages do not exist.
195 
196 Environment:
197 
198  Kernel mode. APCs Disabled.
199 
200 --*/
201 
202 {
203  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectoryIndex;
204  PFN_NUMBER HyperSpaceIndex;
205  PFN_NUMBER PageContainingWorkingSet;
206  PFN_NUMBER VadBitMapPage;
207  MMPTE TempPte;
208 #if defined (_AMD64_)
209  MMPTE TempPte2;
210 #endif
211  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
212  KIRQL OldIrql;
213  PMMPFN Pfn1;
214  ULONG Color;
215  PMMPTE PointerPte;
216  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
217  PMMPTE PointerPde;
218  PFN_NUMBER HyperDirectoryIndex;
219 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
220  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
221  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectoryParentIndex;
222 #endif
223  PMMPTE MappingPte;
224  PMMPTE PointerFillPte;
225  PMMPTE CurrentAddressSpacePde;
226 
227  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
228 
229  //
230  // Charge commitment for the page directory pages, working set page table
231  // page, and working set list. If Vad bitmap lookups are enabled, then
232  // charge for a page or two for that as well.
233  //
234 
235  if (MiChargeCommitment (MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE, NULL) == FALSE) {
236  return FALSE;
237  }
238 
239  NewProcess->NextPageColor = (USHORT) (RtlRandom (&MmProcessColorSeed));
240  KeInitializeSpinLock (&NewProcess->HyperSpaceLock);
241 
242  //
243  // Get the PFN lock to get physical pages.
244  //
245 
246  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
247 
248  //
249  // Check to make sure the physical pages are available.
250  //
251 
252  if (MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE() <= (SPFN_NUMBER)MinimumWorkingSetSize){
253 
254  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
255  MiReturnCommitment (MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
256 
257  //
258  // Indicate no directory base was allocated.
259  //
260 
261  return FALSE;
262  }
263 
264  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_PROCESS_CREATE, MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
265 
266  MI_DECREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (MinimumWorkingSetSize,
267  MM_RESAVAIL_ALLOCATE_CREATE_PROCESS);
268 
269  ASSERT (NewProcess->AddressSpaceInitialized == 0);
270  PS_SET_BITS (&NewProcess->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_ADDRESS_SPACE1);
271  ASSERT (NewProcess->AddressSpaceInitialized == 1);
272 
273  NewProcess->Vm.MinimumWorkingSetSize = MinimumWorkingSetSize;
274 
275  //
276  // Allocate a page directory (parent for 64-bit systems) page.
277  //
278 
279  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
280  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
281  }
282 
283  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_PTE_PROCESS (PDE_BASE,
284  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
285 
286  PageDirectoryIndex = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
287 
288  INITIALIZE_DIRECTORY_TABLE_BASE(&DirectoryTableBase[0], PageDirectoryIndex);
289 
290  TempPte = ValidPdePde;
291 
292  PointerPpe = KSEG_ADDRESS (PageDirectoryIndex);
293 
294  //
295  // Map the top level page directory parent page recursively onto itself.
296  //
297 
298  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageDirectoryIndex;
299 
300  //
301  // Set the PTE address in the PFN for the top level page directory page.
302  //
303 
304  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageDirectoryIndex);
305 
306  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
307  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageDirectoryIndex,
308  MiCached);
309  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
310  }
311 
312 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
313 
314  PageDirectoryParentIndex = PageDirectoryIndex;
315 
316  PointerPxe = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
317  PageDirectoryIndex);
318 
319  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPteAddress(PXE_BASE);
320 
321  PointerPxe[MiGetPxeOffset(PXE_BASE)] = TempPte;
322 
323  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPxe);
324 
325  //
326  // Now that the top level extended page parent page is initialized,
327  // allocate a page parent page.
328  //
329 
330  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
331  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
332  }
333 
334  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_PTE_PROCESS (PDE_BASE,
335  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
336 
337  PageDirectoryIndex = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
338 
339  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageDirectoryIndex);
340 
341  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
342  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageDirectoryIndex,
343  MiCached);
344  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
345  }
346 
347  //
348  //
349  // Map this directory parent page into the top level
350  // extended page directory parent page.
351  //
352 
353  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageDirectoryIndex;
354 
355  PointerPxe = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
356  PageDirectoryParentIndex);
357 
358  PointerPxe[MiGetPxeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)] = TempPte;
359 
360  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPxe);
361 
362 #else
363  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPteAddress((PVOID)PDE_TBASE);
364  PointerPpe[MiGetPpeOffset(PDE_TBASE)] = TempPte;
365 #endif
366 
367  //
368  // Allocate the page directory for hyper space and map this directory
369  // page into the page directory parent page.
370  //
371 
372  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
373  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
374  }
375 
376  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_PTE_PROCESS (MiGetPpeAddress(HYPER_SPACE),
377  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
378 
379  HyperDirectoryIndex = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
380 
381  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (HyperDirectoryIndex);
382 
383  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
384  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (HyperDirectoryIndex,
385  MiCached);
386  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
387  }
388 
389  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = HyperDirectoryIndex;
390 
391 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
392  PointerPpe = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
393  PageDirectoryIndex);
394 #endif
395 
396  PointerPpe[MiGetPpeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)] = TempPte;
397 
398 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
399  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPpe);
400 #endif
401 
402  //
403  // Allocate the hyper space page table page.
404  //
405 
406  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
407  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
408  }
409 
410  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_PTE_PROCESS (MiGetPdeAddress(HYPER_SPACE),
411  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
412 
413  HyperSpaceIndex = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
414 
415  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (HyperSpaceIndex);
416 
417  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
418  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (HyperSpaceIndex,
419  MiCached);
420  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
421  }
422 
423 #if (_AMD64_)
424  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = HyperSpaceIndex;
425  PointerPde = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
426  HyperDirectoryIndex);
427 
428  PointerPde[MiGetPdeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)] = TempPte;
429  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPde);
430 #endif
431 
432  INITIALIZE_DIRECTORY_TABLE_BASE(&DirectoryTableBase[1], HyperSpaceIndex);
433 
434  //
435  // Remove page(s) for the VAD bitmap.
436  //
437 
438  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
439  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
440  }
441 
442  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_VA_PROCESS (MmWorkingSetList,
443  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
444 
445  VadBitMapPage = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
446 
447  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (VadBitMapPage);
448 
449  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
450  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (VadBitMapPage,
451  MiCached);
452  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
453  }
454 
455  //
456  // Remove page for the working set list.
457  //
458 
459  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
460  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
461  }
462 
463  Color = MI_PAGE_COLOR_VA_PROCESS (MmWorkingSetList,
464  &CurrentProcess->NextPageColor);
465 
466  PageContainingWorkingSet = MiRemoveZeroPageMayReleaseLocks (Color, OldIrql);
467 
468  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageContainingWorkingSet);
469 
470  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
471  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageContainingWorkingSet,
472  MiCached);
473  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
474  }
475 
476  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
477 
478  NewProcess->WorkingSetPage = PageContainingWorkingSet;
479 
480  //
481  // Initialize the page reserved for hyper space.
482  //
483 
484  TempPte = ValidPdePde;
485  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = VadBitMapPage;
486  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPte, 0);
487 
488  //
489  // Set the PTE address in the PFN for the hyper space page directory page.
490  //
491 
492  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (HyperDirectoryIndex);
493 
494  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPpeAddress (HYPER_SPACE);
495 
496 #if defined (_AMD64_)
497 
498  //
499  // Copy the system mappings including the shared user page & session space.
500  //
501 
502  CurrentAddressSpacePde = MiGetPxeAddress (KI_USER_SHARED_DATA);
503 
504  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
505 
506  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
507 
508  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
509  PageDirectoryParentIndex,
510  MM_READWRITE,
511  MappingPte);
512 
513  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
514 
515  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
516 
517  PointerPte = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
518  }
519  else {
520  PointerPte = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess,
521  PageDirectoryParentIndex,
522  &OldIrql);
523  }
524 
525  PointerFillPte = &PointerPte[MiGetPxeOffset(KI_USER_SHARED_DATA)];
526 
527  RtlCopyMemory (PointerFillPte,
528  CurrentAddressSpacePde,
529  ((1 + (MiGetPxeAddress(MM_SYSTEM_SPACE_END) -
530  CurrentAddressSpacePde)) * sizeof(MMPTE)));
531 
532  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
533  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
534  }
535  else {
536  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PointerPte, OldIrql);
537  }
538 
539  //
540  // Initialize the VAD bitmap and working set mappings.
541  //
542 
543  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
544 
545  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
546 
547  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
548  HyperSpaceIndex,
549  MM_READWRITE,
550  MappingPte);
551 
552  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
553 
554  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
555 
556  PointerPte = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
557  }
558  else {
559  PointerPte = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess,
560  HyperSpaceIndex,
561  &OldIrql);
562 
563  }
564 
565  PointerPte[MiGetPteOffset(VAD_BITMAP_SPACE)] = TempPte;
566 
567  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageContainingWorkingSet;
568  PointerPte[MiGetPteOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
569 
570  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
571  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
572  }
573  else {
574  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PointerPte, OldIrql);
575  }
576 #else
577 
578  TempPte = ValidPdePde;
579  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = VadBitMapPage;
580  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPte, 0);
581 
582  PointerPte = KSEG_ADDRESS (HyperSpaceIndex);
583  PointerPte[MiGetPteOffset(VAD_BITMAP_SPACE)] = TempPte;
584 
585  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageContainingWorkingSet;
586  PointerPte[MiGetPteOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
587 #endif
588 
589  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmProcessCommit, MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
590 
591  //
592  // Up the session space reference count.
593  //
594 
595  MiSessionAddProcess (NewProcess);
596 
597  return TRUE;
598 }
599 #endif
600 
601 
602 NTSTATUS
603 MmInitializeProcessAddressSpace (
604  IN PEPROCESS ProcessToInitialize,
605  IN PEPROCESS ProcessToClone OPTIONAL,
606  IN PVOID SectionToMap OPTIONAL,
607  IN OUT PULONG CreateFlags,
608  OUT POBJECT_NAME_INFORMATION *AuditName OPTIONAL
609  )
610 
611 /*++
612 
613 Routine Description:
614 
615  This routine initializes the working set and mutexes within a
616  newly created address space to support paging.
617 
618  No page faults may occur in a new process until this routine has
619  completed.
620 
621 Arguments:
622 
623  ProcessToInitialize - Supplies a pointer to the process to initialize.
624 
625  ProcessToClone - Optionally supplies a pointer to the process whose
626  address space should be copied into the
627  ProcessToInitialize address space.
628 
629  SectionToMap - Optionally supplies a section to map into the newly
630  initialized address space.
631 
632  Only one of ProcessToClone and SectionToMap may be specified.
633 
634  CreateFlags - Flags specifying varying parameters pertinent to process
635  creation. Currently, only the PROCESS_CREATE_FLAGS_ALL_LARGE_PAGE_FLAGS
636  are relevant to memory management. On output, these indicate to the
637  caller whether or not the process image was successfully mapped with
638  large pages.
639 
640  AuditName - Supplies an opaque object name information pointer.
641 
642 Return Value:
643 
644  NTSTATUS.
645 
646 Environment:
647 
648  Kernel mode. APCs disabled.
649 
650 --*/
651 
652 {
653  KIRQL OldIrql;
654  MMPTE TempPte;
655  PMMPTE PointerPte;
656  PVOID BaseAddress;
657  SIZE_T ViewSize;
658  NTSTATUS Status;
659  NTSTATUS SystemDllStatus;
660  PFILE_OBJECT FilePointer;
661  PFN_NUMBER PageContainingWorkingSet;
662  LARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset;
663  PSECTION_IMAGE_INFORMATION ImageInfo;
664  PMMVAD VadShare;
665  PMMVAD VadReserve;
666  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
667  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
668  PFN_NUMBER PdePhysicalPage;
669  PFN_NUMBER VadBitMapPage;
670  ULONG i;
671  ULONG NumberOfPages;
672  MMPTE DemandZeroPte;
673  ULONG AllocationType;
674  ULONG WowLACompatRes = 0;
675 
676 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
677  PFN_NUMBER PdePhysicalPage2;
678 #endif
679 
680 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
681  ULONG MaximumUserPageTablePages = MM_USER_PAGE_TABLE_PAGES;
682  ULONG MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages = MM_USER_PAGE_DIRECTORY_PAGES;
683  PFN_NUMBER PpePhysicalPage;
684 #if DBG
685  ULONG j;
686  PUCHAR p;
687 #endif
688 #endif
689 
690 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
691  PFN_NUMBER PxePhysicalPage;
692 #endif
693 
694 #if defined(_WIN64)
695  MMPTE TempPte2;
696  PMMPTE MappingPte;
697  PMMWSL WorkingSetList;
698  PVOID HighestUserAddress;
699  PWOW64_PROCESS Wow64Process;
700 #endif
701 
702  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
703  DemandZeroPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
704 
705 #if !defined(_WIN64)
706 
707  //
708  // Check whether our new process needs an update that occurred while we
709  // were filling its system PDEs. If so, we must recopy here as the updater
710  // isn't able to tell where we were in the middle of our first copy.
711  //
712 
713  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0] != 0);
714 
715  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
716 
717  if (ProcessToInitialize->PdeUpdateNeeded) {
718 
719  //
720  // Another thread updated the system PDE range while this process
721  // was being created. Update the PDEs now (prior to attaching so
722  // if an interrupt occurs that accesses the mapping it will be correct).
723  //
724 
725  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&ProcessToInitialize->Flags,
726  PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
727 
728  MiUpdateSystemPdes (ProcessToInitialize);
729  }
730 
731  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
732 
733 #endif
734 
735  VadReserve = NULL;
736 
737  //
738  // Initialize Working Set Mutex in process header.
739  //
740 
741  KeAttachProcess (&ProcessToInitialize->Pcb);
742 
743  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->AddressSpaceInitialized <= 1);
744  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&ProcessToInitialize->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_ADDRESS_SPACE1);
745  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->AddressSpaceInitialized == 0);
746 
747  PS_SET_BITS (&ProcessToInitialize->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_ADDRESS_SPACE2);
748  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->AddressSpaceInitialized == 2);
749 
750 
751  KeInitializeGuardedMutex (&ProcessToInitialize->AddressCreationLock);
752  ExInitializePushLock (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm.WorkingSetMutex);
753 
754  //
755  // NOTE: The process block has been zeroed when allocated, so
756  // there is no need to zero fields and set pointers to NULL.
757  //
758 
759  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.NumberGenericTableElements == 0);
760 
761  ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.BalancedRoot.u1.Parent = &ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.BalancedRoot;
762 
763  KeQuerySystemTime (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm.LastTrimTime);
764  ProcessToInitialize->Vm.VmWorkingSetList = MmWorkingSetList;
765 
766  //
767  // Obtain a page to map the working set and initialize the
768  // working set. Get the PFN lock to allocate physical pages.
769  //
770 
771  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
772 
773  //
774  // Initialize the PFN database for the Page Directory and the
775  // PDE which maps hyper space.
776  //
777 
778 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
779 
780 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
781  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (PXE_BASE);
782  PxePhysicalPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
783  MiInitializePfn (PxePhysicalPage, PointerPte, 1);
784 
785  PointerPte = MiGetPxeAddress (HYPER_SPACE);
786 #else
787  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)PDE_TBASE);
788 #endif
789 
790  PpePhysicalPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
791 
792  MiInitializePfn (PpePhysicalPage, PointerPte, 1);
793 
794  PointerPte = MiGetPpeAddress (HYPER_SPACE);
795 
796 #elif defined (_X86PAE_)
797  PointerPte = MiGetPdeAddress (PDE_BASE);
798 #else
799  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (PDE_BASE);
800 #endif
801 
802  PdePhysicalPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
803  MiInitializePfn (PdePhysicalPage, PointerPte, 1);
804 
805  PointerPte = MiGetPdeAddress (HYPER_SPACE);
806  MiInitializePfn (MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte), PointerPte, 1);
807 
808 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
809 
810  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
811  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (PDE_BASE + (i << PAGE_SHIFT));
812  PdePhysicalPage2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
813  MiInitializePfn (PdePhysicalPage2, PointerPte, 1);
814  }
815 
816 #endif
817 
818  //
819  // The VAD bitmap spans one page when booted 2GB and the working set
820  // page follows it. If booted 3GB, the VAD bitmap spans 1.5 pages and
821  // the working set list uses the last half of the second page.
822  //
823 
824  NumberOfPages = 2;
825 
826  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VAD_BITMAP_SPACE);
827 
828  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte,
829  0,
830  MM_READWRITE,
831  PointerPte);
832 
833  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
834 
835  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
836 
837  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Long != 0);
838  VadBitMapPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
839  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, DemandZeroPte);
840 
841  MiInitializePfn (VadBitMapPage, PointerPte, 1);
842 
843  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = VadBitMapPage;
844 
845  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
846 
847  PointerPte += 1;
848  }
849 
850  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
851 
852  PageContainingWorkingSet = ProcessToInitialize->WorkingSetPage;
853 
854  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->LockedPagesList == NULL);
855 
856  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
857  LockedPagesHeader = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
858  sizeof(LOCK_HEADER),
859  'xTmM');
860 
861  if (LockedPagesHeader != NULL) {
862 
863  LockedPagesHeader->Count = 0;
864  LockedPagesHeader->Valid = TRUE;
865  InitializeListHead (&LockedPagesHeader->ListHead);
866  KeInitializeSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock);
867 
868  //
869  // Note an explicit memory barrier is not needed here because
870  // we must detach from this process before the field can be
871  // accessed. And any other processor would need to context
872  // swap to this process before the field could be accessed, so
873  // the implicit memory barriers in context swap are sufficient.
874  //
875 
876  ProcessToInitialize->LockedPagesList = (PVOID) LockedPagesHeader;
877  }
878  }
879 
880  MiInitializeWorkingSetList (ProcessToInitialize);
881 
882  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL);
883 
884  BaseAddress = NULL;
885 
886  //
887  // Page faults may be taken now.
888  //
889  // If the system has been biased to an alternate base address to allow
890  // 3gb of user address space and the process is not being cloned, then
891  // create a VAD for the shared memory page.
892  //
893  // Always create a VAD for the shared memory page for 64-bit systems as
894  // clearly it always falls into the user address space there.
895  //
896  // Only x86 booted without /3GB doesn't need the VAD (because the shared
897  // memory page lies above the highest VAD the user can allocate so the user
898  // can never delete it).
899  //
900 
901  if ((MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS > (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA) &&
902  (ProcessToClone == NULL)) {
903 
904  //
905  // Allocate a VAD to map the shared memory page. If a VAD cannot be
906  // allocated, then detach from the target process and return a failure
907  // status. This VAD is marked as not deletable.
908  //
909 
910  VadShare = MiAllocateVad (MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA,
911  MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA+ (X64K)-1,
912  FALSE);
913 
914  if (VadShare == NULL) {
915  KeDetachProcess ();
916  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
917  }
918 
919  //
920  // If a section is being mapped and the executable is not large
921  // address space aware, then create a VAD that reserves the address
922  // space between 2gb and the highest user address.
923  //
924 
925  if (SectionToMap != NULL) {
926 
927  if (!((PSECTION)SectionToMap)->u.Flags.Image) {
928  KeDetachProcess ();
929  if (VadShare != NULL) {
930  ExFreePool (VadShare);
931  }
932  return STATUS_SECTION_NOT_IMAGE;
933  }
934 
935  ImageInfo = ((PSECTION)SectionToMap)->Segment->u2.ImageInformation;
936 
937 #if defined(_X86_)
938 
939  if ((ImageInfo->ImageCharacteristics & IMAGE_FILE_LARGE_ADDRESS_AWARE) == 0) {
940  BaseAddress = (PVOID) _2gb;
941  }
942 
943 #else
944 
945  if (ProcessToInitialize->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OVERRIDE_ADDRESS_SPACE) {
946  NOTHING;
947  }
948  else {
949  if ((ImageInfo->ImageCharacteristics & IMAGE_FILE_LARGE_ADDRESS_AWARE) == 0) {
950  BaseAddress = (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR) _2gb;
951  }
952  else if (ImageInfo->Machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_I386) {
953 
954  //
955  // Provide 4 gigabytes of address space for wow64 apps that
956  // have the large address aware bit set.
957  //
958 
959  BaseAddress = (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR) _4gb;
960  WowLACompatRes = X64K;
961 
962  PS_SET_BITS (&ProcessToInitialize->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_WOW64_4GB_VA_SPACE);
963  }
964 
965  //
966  // Create a guard 64K area for Wow64 compatibility
967  //
968 
969  if (ImageInfo->Machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_I386) {
970  BaseAddress = (PVOID) ((ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress - X64K);
971  }
972  }
973 
974 #endif
975 
976  if (BaseAddress != NULL) {
977 
978  //
979  // Allocate a VAD to map the address space between 2gb and
980  // the highest user address. If a VAD cannot be allocated,
981  // then deallocate the shared address space VAD, detach from
982  // the target process, and return a failure status.
983  // This VAD is marked as not deletable.
984  //
985 
986  VadReserve = MiAllocateVad ((ULONG_PTR) BaseAddress - WowLACompatRes,
987  (ULONG_PTR) MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS,
988  FALSE);
989 
990  if (VadReserve == NULL) {
991  KeDetachProcess ();
992  if (VadShare != NULL) {
993  ExFreePool (VadShare);
994  }
995  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
996  }
997 
998  //
999  // Insert the VAD.
1000  //
1001  // N.B. No failure can occur since there is no commit charge.
1002  //
1003 
1004  Status = MiInsertVadCharges (VadReserve, ProcessToInitialize);
1005 
1006  ASSERT (NT_SUCCESS (Status));
1007 
1008  LOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1009 
1010  MiInsertVad (VadReserve, ProcessToInitialize);
1011 
1012  UNLOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1013 
1014 #if !defined(_X86_)
1015 
1016  if (ImageInfo->Machine == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_I386) {
1017 
1018  //
1019  // Initialize the Wow64 process structure.
1020  //
1021 
1022  Wow64Process = (PWOW64_PROCESS) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (
1023  NonPagedPool,
1024  sizeof(WOW64_PROCESS),
1025  'WowM');
1026 
1027  if (Wow64Process == NULL) {
1028  KeDetachProcess ();
1029  ExFreePool (VadShare);
1030  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1031  }
1032 
1033  RtlZeroMemory (Wow64Process, sizeof(WOW64_PROCESS));
1034 
1035  ProcessToInitialize->Wow64Process = Wow64Process;
1036 
1037  MmWorkingSetList->HighestUserAddress = BaseAddress;
1038 
1039  //
1040  // Since the user can only access a limited amount of
1041  // virtual address space, reduce the number of commit
1042  // bits needed to span his page table pages.
1043  //
1044 
1045  MaximumUserPageTablePages = (ULONG) (MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE ((SIZE_T)BaseAddress, MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE) / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
1046  MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages = (ULONG) (MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE ((SIZE_T)BaseAddress, MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PPE) / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PPE);
1047  }
1048 #endif
1049 
1050  }
1051  }
1052 
1053  //
1054  // Insert the VAD.
1055  //
1056  // N.B. No failure can occur since there is no commit charge.
1057  //
1058 
1059  if (VadShare != NULL) {
1060 
1061  Status = MiInsertVadCharges (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1062 
1063  ASSERT (NT_SUCCESS (Status));
1064 
1065  LOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1066 
1067  MiInsertVad (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1068 
1069  UNLOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1070  }
1071  }
1072 
1073 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
1074 
1075  //
1076  // Allocate the commitment tracking bitmaps for page directory and page
1077  // table pages. This must be done before any non-MM_MAX_COMMIT VAD
1078  // creations occur.
1079  //
1080 
1081  ASSERT (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables == NULL);
1082  ASSERT (MmWorkingSetList->NumberOfCommittedPageDirectories == 0);
1083 
1084  ASSERT ((ULONG_PTR)MM_SYSTEM_RANGE_START % (PTE_PER_PAGE * PAGE_SIZE) == 0);
1085 
1086  MmWorkingSetList->MaximumUserPageTablePages = MaximumUserPageTablePages;
1087 
1088  MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables = (PULONG)
1089  ExAllocatePoolWithTag (MmPagedPoolEnd != NULL ? PagedPool : NonPagedPool,
1090  (MaximumUserPageTablePages + 7) / 8,
1091  'dPmM');
1092 
1093  if (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables == NULL) {
1094  KeDetachProcess ();
1095  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1096  }
1097 
1098 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
1099 
1100 #if DBG
1101  p = (PUCHAR) MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectoryParents;
1102 
1103  for (j = 0; j < ((MM_USER_PAGE_DIRECTORY_PARENT_PAGES + 7) / 8); j += 1) {
1104  ASSERT (*p == 0);
1105  p += 1;
1106  }
1107 #endif
1108 
1109  ASSERT (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories == NULL);
1110  ASSERT (MmWorkingSetList->NumberOfCommittedPageDirectoryParents == 0);
1111 
1112  MmWorkingSetList->MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages = MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages;
1113 
1114  MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories = (PULONG)
1115  ExAllocatePoolWithTag (MmPagedPoolEnd != NULL ? PagedPool : NonPagedPool,
1116  (MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages + 7) / 8,
1117  'dPmM');
1118 
1119  if (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories == NULL) {
1120  ExFreePool (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables);
1121  MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables = NULL;
1122  KeDetachProcess ();
1123  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1124  }
1125 
1126  RtlZeroMemory (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories,
1127  (MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages + 7) / 8);
1128 #endif
1129 
1130  RtlZeroMemory (MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables,
1131  (MaximumUserPageTablePages + 7) / 8);
1132 
1133 #if DBG
1134  p = (PUCHAR) MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories;
1135 
1136  for (j = 0; j < ((MaximumUserPageDirectoryPages + 7) / 8); j += 1) {
1137  ASSERT (*p == 0);
1138  p += 1;
1139  }
1140 #endif
1141 
1142 #endif
1143 
1144  //
1145  // If the registry indicates all applications should get virtual address
1146  // ranges from the highest address downwards then enforce it now. This
1147  // makes it easy to test 3GB-aware apps on 32-bit machines as well as
1148  // 64-bit apps on NT64.
1149  //
1150  //
1151  // Note this is only done if the image has the large-address-aware bit set
1152  // because otherwise the compatibility VAD occupies the range from 2gb->3gb
1153  // and setting top-down by default can cause allocations like the stack
1154  // trace database to displace kernel32 causing the process launch to fail.
1155  //
1156 
1157  if ((MmAllocationPreference != 0) &&
1158  ((VadReserve == NULL) || (BaseAddress > (PVOID)(ULONG_PTR)_2gb))) {
1159 
1160  PS_SET_BITS (&ProcessToInitialize->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_TOP_DOWN);
1161  }
1162 
1163 #if defined(_WIN64)
1164 
1165  if (ProcessToClone == NULL) {
1166 
1167  //
1168  // Reserve the address space just below KUSER_SHARED_DATA as the
1169  // compatibility area. This range (and pieces of it) can be
1170  // unreserved by user mode code such as WOW64 or csrss. Hence
1171  // commit must be charged for the page directory and table pages.
1172  //
1173 
1174  ASSERT(MiCheckForConflictingVad(ProcessToInitialize, WOW64_COMPATIBILITY_AREA_ADDRESS, MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA - 1) == NULL);
1175 
1176  VadShare = MiAllocateVad (WOW64_COMPATIBILITY_AREA_ADDRESS,
1177  MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA - 1,
1178  TRUE);
1179 
1180  if (VadShare == NULL) {
1181  KeDetachProcess ();
1182  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1183  }
1184 
1185  //
1186  // Zero the commit charge so inserting the VAD will result in the
1187  // proper charges being applied. This way when it is split later,
1188  // the correct commitment will be returned.
1189  //
1190  // N.B. The system process is not allocated with commit because
1191  // paged pool and quotas don't exist at the point in Phase0
1192  // where this is called.
1193  //
1194 
1195  if (MmPagedPoolEnd != NULL) {
1196  VadShare->u.VadFlags.CommitCharge = 0;
1197  }
1198 
1199  //
1200  // Insert the VAD. Since this VAD has a commit charge, the working set
1201  // mutex must be held (as calls inside MiInsertVad to support routines
1202  // to charge commit require it), failures can occur and must be handled.
1203  //
1204 
1205  Status = MiInsertVadCharges (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1206 
1207  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1208 
1209  //
1210  // Note that any inserted VAD (ie: the VadReserve and Wow64
1211  // allocations) are automatically released on process destruction
1212  // so there is no need to tear them down here.
1213  //
1214 
1215  ExFreePool (VadShare);
1216  KeDetachProcess ();
1217  return Status;
1218  }
1219 
1220  LOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1221 
1222  MiInsertVad (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1223 
1224  UNLOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1225  }
1226 
1227 #endif
1228 
1229  if (SectionToMap != NULL) {
1230 
1231  //
1232  // Map the specified section into the address space of the
1233  // process but only if it is an image section.
1234  //
1235 
1236  if (!((PSECTION)SectionToMap)->u.Flags.Image) {
1237  Status = STATUS_SECTION_NOT_IMAGE;
1238  }
1239  else {
1240  UNICODE_STRING UnicodeString;
1241  ULONG n;
1242  PWSTR Src;
1243  PCHAR Dst;
1244  PSECTION_IMAGE_INFORMATION ImageInformation;
1245 
1246  FilePointer = ((PSECTION)SectionToMap)->Segment->ControlArea->FilePointer;
1247  ImageInformation = ((PSECTION)SectionToMap)->Segment->u2.ImageInformation;
1248  UnicodeString = FilePointer->FileName;
1249  Src = (PWSTR)((PCHAR)UnicodeString.Buffer + UnicodeString.Length);
1250  n = 0;
1251  if (UnicodeString.Buffer != NULL) {
1252  while (Src > UnicodeString.Buffer) {
1253  if (*--Src == OBJ_NAME_PATH_SEPARATOR) {
1254  Src += 1;
1255  break;
1256  }
1257  else {
1258  n += 1;
1259  }
1260  }
1261  }
1262  Dst = (PCHAR)ProcessToInitialize->ImageFileName;
1263  if (n >= sizeof (ProcessToInitialize->ImageFileName)) {
1264  n = sizeof (ProcessToInitialize->ImageFileName) - 1;
1265  }
1266 
1267  while (n--) {
1268  *Dst++ = (UCHAR)*Src++;
1269  }
1270  *Dst = '\0';
1271 
1272  if (AuditName != NULL) {
1273  Status = SeInitializeProcessAuditName (FilePointer, FALSE, AuditName);
1274 
1275  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
1276  KeDetachProcess ();
1277  return Status;
1278  }
1279  }
1280 
1281  ProcessToInitialize->SubSystemMajorVersion =
1282  (UCHAR)ImageInformation->SubSystemMajorVersion;
1283  ProcessToInitialize->SubSystemMinorVersion =
1284  (UCHAR)ImageInformation->SubSystemMinorVersion;
1285 
1286  BaseAddress = NULL;
1287  ViewSize = 0;
1288  ZERO_LARGE (SectionOffset);
1289 
1290  AllocationType = 0;
1291 
1292  if ((*CreateFlags & PROCESS_CREATE_FLAGS_LARGE_PAGES) != 0) {
1293  AllocationType = MEM_LARGE_PAGES;
1294  }
1295 
1296  Status = MmMapViewOfSection ((PSECTION)SectionToMap,
1297  ProcessToInitialize,
1298  &BaseAddress,
1299  0,
1300  0,
1301  &SectionOffset,
1302  &ViewSize,
1303  ViewShare,
1304  AllocationType,
1305  PAGE_READWRITE);
1306 
1307  //
1308  // The status of mapping the section is what must be returned
1309  // unless the system DLL load fails. This is because if the
1310  // exe section is relocated (ie: STATUS_IMAGE_NOT_AT_BASE), this
1311  // must be returned (not STATUS_SUCCESS from the system DLL
1312  // mapping).
1313  //
1314 
1315  ProcessToInitialize->SectionBaseAddress = BaseAddress;
1316 
1317  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1318 
1319  if ((*CreateFlags & PROCESS_CREATE_FLAGS_LARGE_PAGES) != 0) {
1320  PMMPTE PointerPde;
1321 
1322  //
1323  // Determine whether or not the image was succesfully mapped with
1324  // large pages. Note that no locks are required as no other thread
1325  // can access this process, and no page in the process can be trimmed
1326  // (the process is not yet on Mm's list of working sets).
1327  //
1328 
1329  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (BaseAddress);
1330 
1331  if (
1332 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
1333  (MiGetPxeAddress (BaseAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
1334 #endif
1335 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
1336  (MiGetPpeAddress (BaseAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
1337 #endif
1338  (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
1339  (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde) == 0)) {
1340  *CreateFlags &= ~PROCESS_CREATE_FLAGS_LARGE_PAGES;
1341  }
1342  }
1343 
1344  //
1345  // Map the system DLL now since it is required by all processes.
1346  //
1347 
1348  SystemDllStatus = PsMapSystemDll (ProcessToInitialize,
1349  NULL,
1350  FALSE);
1351 
1352  if (!NT_SUCCESS (SystemDllStatus)) {
1353  Status = SystemDllStatus;
1354  }
1355  }
1356  }
1357 
1358  MiAllowWorkingSetExpansion (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm);
1359 
1360  KeDetachProcess ();
1361  return Status;
1362  }
1363 
1364  if (ProcessToClone != NULL) {
1365 
1366  strcpy ((PCHAR)ProcessToInitialize->ImageFileName,
1367  (PCHAR)ProcessToClone->ImageFileName);
1368 
1369  //
1370  // Clone the address space of the specified process.
1371  //
1372  // As the page directory and page tables are private to each
1373  // process, the physical pages which map the directory page
1374  // and the page table usage must be mapped into system space
1375  // so they can be updated while in the context of the process
1376  // we are cloning.
1377  //
1378 
1379 #if defined(_WIN64)
1380 
1381  if (ProcessToClone->Wow64Process != NULL) {
1382 
1383  //
1384  // Initialize the Wow64 process structure.
1385  //
1386 
1387  Wow64Process = (PWOW64_PROCESS) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (
1388  NonPagedPool,
1389  sizeof(WOW64_PROCESS),
1390  'WowM');
1391 
1392  if (Wow64Process == NULL) {
1393  KeDetachProcess ();
1394  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1395  }
1396 
1397  RtlZeroMemory (Wow64Process, sizeof(WOW64_PROCESS));
1398 
1399  ProcessToInitialize->Wow64Process = Wow64Process;
1400 
1401  Wow64Process->Wow64 = ProcessToClone->Wow64Process->Wow64;
1402 
1403  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
1404 
1405  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
1406 
1407  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
1408  ProcessToClone->WorkingSetPage,
1409  MM_READWRITE,
1410  MappingPte);
1411 
1412  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
1413 
1414  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
1415 
1416  WorkingSetList = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
1417  }
1418  else {
1419  WorkingSetList = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (ProcessToInitialize,
1420  ProcessToClone->WorkingSetPage,
1421  &OldIrql);
1422  }
1423 
1424  HighestUserAddress = WorkingSetList->HighestUserAddress;
1425 
1426  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
1427  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
1428  }
1429  else {
1430  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (ProcessToInitialize,
1431  WorkingSetList,
1432  OldIrql);
1433  }
1434 
1435  MmWorkingSetList->HighestUserAddress = HighestUserAddress;
1436  }
1437 
1438 #endif
1439 
1440  KeDetachProcess ();
1441 
1442  Status = MiCloneProcessAddressSpace (ProcessToClone,
1443  ProcessToInitialize);
1444 
1445  MiAllowWorkingSetExpansion (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm);
1446  } else {
1447 
1448  //
1449  // System Process.
1450  //
1451 
1452  KeDetachProcess ();
1453  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1454  }
1455 
1456  //
1457  // If this a cloned process or the system process, then large pages
1458  // were not used.
1459  //
1460 
1461  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1462  *CreateFlags &= ~(PROCESS_CREATE_FLAGS_LARGE_PAGES);
1463  }
1464 
1465  return Status;
1466 }
1467 
1468 #if !defined (_WIN64)
1469 VOID
1470 MiInsertHandBuiltProcessIntoList (
1471  IN PEPROCESS ProcessToInitialize
1472  )
1473 
1474 /*++
1475 
1476 Routine Description:
1477 
1478  Nonpaged helper routine.
1479 
1480 --*/
1481 
1482 {
1483  KIRQL OldIrql;
1484 
1485  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->MmProcessLinks.Flink == NULL);
1486  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->MmProcessLinks.Blink == NULL);
1487 
1488  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
1489 
1490  InsertTailList (&MmProcessList, &ProcessToInitialize->MmProcessLinks);
1491 
1492  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
1493 }
1494 #endif
1495 
1496 
1497 NTSTATUS
1498 MmInitializeHandBuiltProcess (
1499  IN PEPROCESS ProcessToInitialize,
1500  OUT PULONG_PTR DirectoryTableBase
1501  )
1502 
1503 /*++
1504 
1505 Routine Description:
1506 
1507  This routine initializes the working set mutex and
1508  address creation mutex for this "hand built" process.
1509  Normally the call to MmInitializeAddressSpace initializes the
1510  working set mutex. However, in this case, we have already initialized
1511  the address space and we are now creating a second process using
1512  the address space of the idle thread.
1513 
1514 Arguments:
1515 
1516  ProcessToInitialize - Supplies a pointer to the process to initialize.
1517 
1518  DirectoryTableBase - Receives the pair of directory table base pointers.
1519 
1520 Return Value:
1521 
1522  None.
1523 
1524 Environment:
1525 
1526  Kernel mode. APCs disabled, idle process context.
1527 
1528 --*/
1529 
1530 {
1531 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1532 
1533  //
1534  // On MP machines the idle & system process do not share a top level
1535  // page directory because hyperspace mappings are protected by a
1536  // per-process spinlock. Having two processes share a single hyperspace
1537  // (by virtue of sharing a top level page directory) would make the
1538  // spinlock synchronization meaningless.
1539  //
1540  // Note that it is completely illegal for the idle process to ever enter
1541  // a wait state, but the code below should never encounter waits for
1542  // mutexes, etc.
1543  //
1544 
1545  return MmCreateProcessAddressSpace (0,
1546  ProcessToInitialize,
1547  DirectoryTableBase);
1548 #else
1549 
1550  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
1551 
1552  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess();
1553 
1554  DirectoryTableBase[0] = CurrentProcess->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0];
1555  DirectoryTableBase[1] = CurrentProcess->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[1];
1556 
1557  KeInitializeGuardedMutex (&ProcessToInitialize->AddressCreationLock);
1558  ExInitializePushLock (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm.WorkingSetMutex);
1559 
1560  KeInitializeSpinLock (&ProcessToInitialize->HyperSpaceLock);
1561 
1562  ASSERT (ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.NumberGenericTableElements == 0);
1563 
1564  ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.BalancedRoot.u1.Parent = &ProcessToInitialize->VadRoot.BalancedRoot;
1565 
1566  ProcessToInitialize->Vm.WorkingSetSize = CurrentProcess->Vm.WorkingSetSize;
1567  ProcessToInitialize->Vm.VmWorkingSetList = MmWorkingSetList;
1568 
1569  KeQuerySystemTime (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm.LastTrimTime);
1570 
1571 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
1572  ProcessToInitialize->PaeTop = &MiSystemPaeVa;
1573 #endif
1574 
1575 #if !defined (_WIN64)
1576  MiInsertHandBuiltProcessIntoList (ProcessToInitialize);
1577 #endif
1578 
1579  MiAllowWorkingSetExpansion (&ProcessToInitialize->Vm);
1580 
1581  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1582 #endif
1583 }
1584 
1585 NTSTATUS
1586 MmInitializeHandBuiltProcess2 (
1587  IN PEPROCESS ProcessToInitialize
1588  )
1589 
1590 /*++
1591 
1592 Routine Description:
1593 
1594  This routine initializes the shared user VAD. This only needs to be done
1595  for NT64 (and x86 when booted /3GB) because on all other systems, the
1596  shared user address is located above the highest user address.
1597 
1598  For NT64 and x86 /3GB, this VAD must be allocated so that other random
1599  VAD allocations do not overlap this area which would cause the mapping
1600  to receive the wrong data.
1601 
1602 Arguments:
1603 
1604  ProcessToInitialize - Supplies the process that needs initialization.
1605 
1606 Return Value:
1607 
1608  NTSTATUS.
1609 
1610 Environment:
1611 
1612  Kernel mode. APCs Disabled.
1613 
1614 --*/
1615 
1616 {
1617  NTSTATUS Status;
1618  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
1619 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1620  ULONG DummyFlags;
1621 #if defined(_X86_)
1622  MMPTE TempPte2;
1623  PMMPTE MappingPte;
1624 #endif // _X86_
1625 #endif // NT_UP
1626 
1627 #if !defined(NT_UP)
1628 
1629  //
1630  // On MP machines the idle & system process do not share a top level
1631  // page directory because hyperspace mappings are protected by a
1632  // per-process spinlock. Having two processes share a single hyperspace
1633  // (by virtue of sharing a top level page directory) would make the
1634  // spinlock synchronization meaningless.
1635  //
1636 
1637  DummyFlags = 0;
1638  Status = MmInitializeProcessAddressSpace (ProcessToInitialize,
1639  NULL,
1640  NULL,
1641  &DummyFlags,
1642  NULL);
1643 
1644 #if defined(_X86_)
1645 
1646  if ((MmVirtualBias != 0) &&
1647  (PsInitialSystemProcess == NULL) &&
1648  (NT_SUCCESS (Status))) {
1649 
1650  KIRQL OldIrql;
1651  PMMPTE PointerPte;
1652  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1653  PMMPTE PointerFillPte;
1654  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
1655  PMMPTE CurrentAddressSpacePde;
1656 
1657  //
1658  // When booted /3GB, the initial system mappings at 8xxxxxxx must be
1659  // copied because things like the loader block contain pointers to
1660  // this area and are referenced by the system during early startup
1661  // despite the fact that the rest of the system is biased correctly.
1662  //
1663 
1664  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
1665 
1666 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
1667 
1668  //
1669  // Select the top level page directory that maps 2GB->3GB.
1670  //
1671 
1672  PointerPte = (PMMPTE) ProcessToInitialize->PaeTop;
1673 
1674  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte + 2);
1675 
1676 #else
1677 
1678  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_DIRECTORY_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS (ProcessToInitialize);
1679 
1680 #endif
1681 
1682  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
1683 
1684  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
1685 
1686  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
1687  PageFrameIndex,
1688  MM_READWRITE,
1689  MappingPte);
1690 
1691  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
1692 
1693  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
1694 
1695  PointerPte = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
1696  OldIrql = MM_NOIRQL;
1697  }
1698  else {
1699  PointerPte = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess,
1700  PageFrameIndex,
1701  &OldIrql);
1702  }
1703 
1704  PointerFillPte = &PointerPte[MiGetPdeOffset(CODE_START)];
1705 
1706  CurrentAddressSpacePde = MiGetPdeAddress ((PVOID) CODE_START);
1707 
1708  RtlCopyMemory (PointerFillPte,
1709  CurrentAddressSpacePde,
1710  (((1 + CODE_END) - CODE_START) / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE) * sizeof(MMPTE));
1711 
1712  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
1713  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
1714  }
1715  else {
1716  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PointerPte, OldIrql);
1717  }
1718  }
1719 
1720 #endif
1721 
1722 #else
1723 
1724  PMMVAD VadShare;
1725  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
1726 
1727  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1728  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
1729 
1730  //
1731  // Allocate a non-user-deletable VAD to map the shared memory page.
1732  //
1733 
1734  if (MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS > (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA) {
1735 
1736  KeAttachProcess (&ProcessToInitialize->Pcb);
1737 
1738  VadShare = MiAllocateVad (MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA,
1739  MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA+ (X64K)-1,
1740  FALSE);
1741 
1742  //
1743  // Insert the VAD.
1744  //
1745  // N.B. No failure can occur since there is no commit charge.
1746  //
1747 
1748  if (VadShare != NULL) {
1749 
1750  Status = MiInsertVadCharges (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1751 
1752  ASSERT (NT_SUCCESS (Status));
1753 
1754  LOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1755 
1756  MiInsertVad (VadShare, ProcessToInitialize);
1757 
1758  UNLOCK_WS (CurrentThread, ProcessToInitialize);
1759  }
1760  else {
1761  Status = STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1762  }
1763 
1764  KeDetachProcess ();
1765  }
1766 
1767 #endif
1768 
1769  if ((MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) && (NT_SUCCESS (Status))) {
1770 
1771  LockedPagesHeader = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1772  sizeof(LOCK_HEADER),
1773  'xTmM');
1774 
1775  if (LockedPagesHeader != NULL) {
1776 
1777  LockedPagesHeader->Count = 0;
1778  LockedPagesHeader->Valid = TRUE;
1779  InitializeListHead (&LockedPagesHeader->ListHead);
1780  KeInitializeSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock);
1781 
1782  //
1783  // Note an explicit memory barrier is not needed here because
1784  // we must detach from this process before the field can be
1785  // accessed. And any other processor would need to context
1786  // swap to this process before the field could be accessed, so
1787  // the implicit memory barriers in context swap are sufficient.
1788  //
1789 
1790  ProcessToInitialize->LockedPagesList = (PVOID) LockedPagesHeader;
1791  }
1792  else {
1793  Status = STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1794  }
1795  }
1796 
1797  return Status;
1798 }
1799 
1800 
1801 VOID
1802 MmDeleteProcessAddressSpace (
1803  IN PEPROCESS Process
1804  )
1805 
1806 /*++
1807 
1808 Routine Description:
1809 
1810  This routine deletes a process's Page Directory and working set page.
1811 
1812 Arguments:
1813 
1814  Process - Supplies a pointer to the deleted process.
1815 
1816 Return Value:
1817 
1818  None.
1819 
1820 Environment:
1821 
1822  Kernel mode. APCs Disabled.
1823 
1824 --*/
1825 
1826 {
1827  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
1828  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1829  PMMPFN Pfn2;
1830  KIRQL OldIrql;
1831  PMMPTE PointerPte;
1832  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1833  PFN_NUMBER VadBitMapPage;
1834  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex2;
1835 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
1836  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex3;
1837  PMMPTE ExtendedPageDirectoryParent;
1838  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
1839 #endif
1840 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
1841  PMMPTE PageDirectoryParent;
1842  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
1843 #endif
1844 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
1845  ULONG i;
1846  PPAE_ENTRY PaeVa;
1847 
1848  PaeVa = (PPAE_ENTRY) Process->PaeTop;
1849 #endif
1850 
1851  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
1852 
1853 #if !defined(_WIN64)
1854 
1855  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
1856 
1857  RemoveEntryList (&Process->MmProcessLinks);
1858 
1859  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
1860 
1861 #endif
1862 
1863  //
1864  // Return commitment.
1865  //
1866 
1867  MiReturnCommitment (MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
1868  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_PROCESS_DELETE, MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
1869  ASSERT (Process->CommitCharge == 0);
1870 
1871  //
1872  // Remove the working set list page from the deleted process.
1873  //
1874 
1875  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Process->WorkingSetPage);
1876  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1877 
1878  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmProcessCommit, 0 - MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE);
1879 
1880  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1881 
1882  if (Process->AddressSpaceInitialized == 2) {
1883 
1884  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
1885 
1886  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1887  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, Process->WorkingSetPage);
1888 
1889  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
1890 
1891  //
1892  // Map the hyper space page table page from the deleted process
1893  // so the vad bit map page can be captured.
1894  //
1895 
1896  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_HYPER_PAGE_TABLE_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS (Process);
1897 
1898  PointerPte = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
1899  PageFrameIndex);
1900 
1901  VadBitMapPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte + MiGetPteOffset(VAD_BITMAP_SPACE));
1902 
1903  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPte);
1904 
1905  //
1906  // Remove the VAD bitmap page.
1907  //
1908 
1909  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (VadBitMapPage);
1910  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1911 
1912  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
1913 
1914  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1915  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, VadBitMapPage);
1916 
1917  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
1918 
1919  //
1920  // Remove the first hyper space page table page.
1921  //
1922 
1923  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1924  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1925 
1926  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
1927 
1928  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
1929  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
1930  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
1931 
1932 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
1933 
1934  //
1935  // Remove the page directory pages.
1936  //
1937 
1938  PointerPte = (PMMPTE) PaeVa;
1939  ASSERT (PaeVa != &MiSystemPaeVa);
1940 
1941  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
1942  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
1943  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1944  PageFrameIndex2 = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
1945  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex2);
1946  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
1947 
1948  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
1949  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, PageFrameIndex2);
1950 
1951  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
1952  PointerPte += 1;
1953  }
1954 #endif
1955 
1956  //
1957  // Remove the top level page directory page.
1958  //
1959 
1960  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_DIRECTORY_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS(Process);
1961 
1962 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
1963 
1964  //
1965  // Get a pointer to the top-level page directory parent page via
1966  // its KSEG0 address.
1967  //
1968 
1969 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
1970 
1971  ExtendedPageDirectoryParent = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (
1972  CurrentProcess,
1973  PageFrameIndex);
1974 
1975  //
1976  // Remove the hyper space page directory parent page
1977  // from the deleted process.
1978  //
1979 
1980  PointerPxe = &ExtendedPageDirectoryParent[MiGetPxeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)];
1981  PageFrameIndex3 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE(PointerPxe);
1982  ASSERT (MI_PFN_ELEMENT(PageFrameIndex3)->u4.PteFrame == PageFrameIndex);
1983 
1984  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, ExtendedPageDirectoryParent);
1985 
1986  PageDirectoryParent = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
1987  PageFrameIndex3);
1988 
1989 #else
1990  PageDirectoryParent = KSEG_ADDRESS (PageFrameIndex);
1991 #endif
1992 
1993  //
1994  // Remove the hyper space page directory page from the deleted process.
1995  //
1996 
1997  PointerPpe = &PageDirectoryParent[MiGetPpeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)];
1998  PageFrameIndex2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE(PointerPpe);
1999 
2000 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2001  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParent);
2002 #endif
2003 
2004  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex2);
2005  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2006 
2007  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
2008 
2009  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2010 
2011  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex2);
2012 
2013  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
2014 
2015 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2016  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex3);
2017  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2018  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
2019  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
2020  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex3);
2021  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
2022 #endif
2023 #endif
2024 
2025  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2026 
2027  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
2028 
2029  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
2030 
2031  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
2032 
2033  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) || (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress));
2034 
2035  }
2036  else {
2037 
2038  //
2039  // Process initialization never completed, just return the pages
2040  // to the free list.
2041  //
2042 
2043  MiInsertPageInFreeList (Process->WorkingSetPage);
2044 
2045  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_DIRECTORY_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS (Process);
2046 
2047 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2048 
2049  //
2050  // Get a pointer to the top-level page directory parent page via
2051  // its KSEG0 address.
2052  //
2053 
2054  PageDirectoryParent = KSEG_ADDRESS (PageFrameIndex);
2055 
2056 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2057  PageDirectoryParent = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
2058  PageFrameIndex);
2059 
2060  PageFrameIndex3 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PageDirectoryParent[MiGetPxeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)]);
2061 
2062  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParent);
2063 
2064  PageDirectoryParent = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
2065  PageFrameIndex3);
2066 #endif
2067 
2068  PointerPpe = &PageDirectoryParent[MiGetPpeOffset(HYPER_SPACE)];
2069  PageFrameIndex2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE(PointerPpe);
2070 
2071 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2072  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParent);
2073 #endif
2074 
2075  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex2);
2076 
2077 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2078  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex3);
2079 #endif
2080 #endif
2081 
2082  PageFrameIndex2 = MI_GET_HYPER_PAGE_TABLE_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS (Process);
2083 
2084  PointerPte = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess,
2085  PageFrameIndex2);
2086 
2087  VadBitMapPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte + MiGetPteOffset(VAD_BITMAP_SPACE));
2088 
2089  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PointerPte);
2090 
2091  MiInsertPageInFreeList (VadBitMapPage);
2092 
2093  //
2094  // Free the hyper space page table page.
2095  //
2096 
2097  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex2);
2098 
2099 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
2100  PointerPte = (PMMPTE) PaeVa;
2101  ASSERT (PaeVa != &MiSystemPaeVa);
2102 
2103  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
2104  PageFrameIndex2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
2105  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex2);
2106  PointerPte += 1;
2107  }
2108 #endif
2109 
2110  //
2111  // Free the topmost page directory page.
2112  //
2113 
2114  MiInsertPageInFreeList (PageFrameIndex);
2115  }
2116 
2117  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2118 
2119  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (MM_PROCESS_CREATE_CHARGE,
2120  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_DELETE_PROCESS);
2121 
2122 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
2123 
2124  //
2125  // Free the page directory page pointers.
2126  //
2127 
2128  ASSERT (PaeVa != &MiSystemPaeVa);
2129  MiPaeFree (PaeVa);
2130 
2131 #endif
2132 
2133  if (Process->Session != NULL) {
2134 
2135  //
2136  // The Terminal Server session space data page and mapping PTE can only
2137  // be freed when the last process in the session is deleted. This is
2138  // because IA64 maps session space into region 1 and exited processes
2139  // maintain their session space mapping as attaches may occur even
2140  // after process exit that reference win32k, etc. Since the region 1
2141  // mapping is being inserted into region registers during swap context,
2142  // these mappings cannot be torn down until the very last deletion
2143  // occurs.
2144  //
2145 
2146  MiReleaseProcessReferenceToSessionDataPage (Process->Session);
2147  }
2148 
2149  //
2150  // Check to see if the paging files should be contracted.
2151  //
2152 
2153  MiContractPagingFiles ();
2154 
2155  return;
2156 }

2158 
2159 VOID
2160 MiDeletePteRange (
2161  IN PMMSUPPORT WsInfo,
2162  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
2163  IN PMMPTE LastPte,
2164  IN LOGICAL AddressSpaceDeletion
2165  )
2166 
2167 /*++
2168 
2169 Routine Description:
2170 
2171  This routine deletes a range of PTEs and when possible, the PDEs, PPEs and
2172  PXEs as well. Commit is returned here for the hierarchies here.
2173 
2174 Arguments:
2175 
2176  WsInfo - Supplies the working set structure whose PTEs are being deleted.
2177 
2178  PointerPte - Supplies the PTE to begin deleting at.
2179 
2180  LastPte - Supplies the PTE to stop deleting at (don't delete this one).
2181  -1 signifies keep going until a nonvalid PTE is found.
2182 
2183  AddressSpaceDeletion - Supplies TRUE if the address space is in the final
2184  stages of deletion, FALSE otherwise.
2185 
2186 Return Value:
2187 
2188  None.
2189 
2190 Environment:
2191 
2192  Kernel mode, APCs disabled.
2193 
2194 --*/
2195 
2196 {
2197  PVOID TempVa;
2198  KIRQL OldIrql;
2199  MMPTE_FLUSH_LIST PteFlushList;
2200  PFN_NUMBER CommittedPages;
2201  PEPROCESS Process;
2202  BOOLEAN AllProcessors;
2203  PMMPTE PointerPde;
2204  LOGICAL Boundary;
2205  LOGICAL FinalPte;
2206  PMMPFN Pfn1;
2207 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2208  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
2209 #endif
2210 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2211  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
2212 #endif
2213 
2214  if (PointerPte >= LastPte) {
2215  return;
2216  }
2217 
2218  if (WsInfo->VmWorkingSetList == MmWorkingSetList) {
2219  AllProcessors = FALSE;
2220  Process = CONTAINING_RECORD (WsInfo, EPROCESS, Vm);
2221  }
2222  else {
2223  AllProcessors = TRUE;
2224  Process = NULL;
2225  }
2226 
2227  CommittedPages = 0;
2228  PteFlushList.Count = 0;
2229  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (PteFlushList.FlushVa[0] = NULL);
2230 
2231  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
2232 
2233  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2234 
2235 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2236  PointerPpe = MiGetPdeAddress (PointerPte);
2237 
2238 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2239  PointerPxe = MiGetPpeAddress (PointerPte);
2240  if ((PointerPxe->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2241  (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2242  (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2243  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1))
2244 #else
2245  if ((PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2246  (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2247  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1))
2248 #endif
2249 #else
2250  if ((PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) &&
2251  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1))
2252 #endif
2253  {
2254 
2255  do {
2256 
2257  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2258 
2259  TempVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2260 
2261  if (Process != NULL) {
2262  MiDeletePte (PointerPte,
2263  TempVa,
2264  AddressSpaceDeletion,
2265  Process,
2266  NULL,
2267  &PteFlushList,
2268  OldIrql);
2269  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages += 1;
2270  }
2271  else {
2272  MiDeleteValidSystemPte (PointerPte,
2273  TempVa,
2274  WsInfo,
2275  &PteFlushList);
2276  }
2277 
2278  CommittedPages += 1;
2279  PointerPte += 1;
2280 
2281  //
2282  // If all the entries have been removed from the previous page
2283  // table page, delete the page table page itself. Likewise with
2284  // the page directory page.
2285  //
2286 
2287  if (MiIsPteOnPdeBoundary (PointerPte)) {
2288  Boundary = TRUE;
2289  }
2290  else {
2291  Boundary = FALSE;
2292  }
2293 
2294  if ((PointerPte >= LastPte) ||
2295 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2296 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2297  ((MiGetPpeAddress (PointerPte))->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2298 #endif
2299  ((MiGetPdeAddress (PointerPte))->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2300 #endif
2301  ((MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte))->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2302  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0)) {
2303 
2304  FinalPte = TRUE;
2305  }
2306  else {
2307  FinalPte = FALSE;
2308  }
2309 
2310  if ((Boundary == TRUE) || (FinalPte == TRUE)) {
2311 
2312  if (PteFlushList.Count == 0) {
2313  NOTHING;
2314  }
2315  else if (PteFlushList.Count == 1) {
2316  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (PteFlushList.FlushVa[0], AllProcessors);
2317  }
2318  else if (PteFlushList.Count < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
2319  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (PteFlushList.Count,
2320  &PteFlushList.FlushVa[0],
2321  AllProcessors);
2322  }
2323  else {
2324  if (AllProcessors) {
2325  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x1C);
2326  }
2327  else {
2328  MI_FLUSH_PROCESS_TB (FALSE);
2329  }
2330  }
2331 
2332  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte - 1);
2333 
2334  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2335 
2336  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde));
2337 
2338  if ((Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1) &&
2339  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1) &&
2340  (Pfn1->u1.WsIndex != 0)) {
2341 
2342  if (Process != NULL) {
2343  MiDeletePte (PointerPde,
2344  PointerPte - 1,
2345  AddressSpaceDeletion,
2346  Process,
2347  NULL,
2348  NULL,
2349  OldIrql);
2350  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages += 1;
2351  }
2352  else {
2353  MiDeleteValidSystemPte (PointerPde,
2354  PointerPte - 1,
2355  WsInfo,
2356  &PteFlushList);
2357  }
2358 
2359  CommittedPages += 1;
2360 
2361 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2362  if ((FinalPte == TRUE) || (MiIsPteOnPpeBoundary(PointerPte))) {
2363 
2364  PointerPpe = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPde);
2365 
2366  ASSERT (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2367 
2368  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPpe));
2369 
2370  if (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1 && Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1)
2371  {
2372  if (Process != NULL) {
2373  MiDeletePte (PointerPpe,
2374  PointerPde,
2375  AddressSpaceDeletion,
2376  Process,
2377  NULL,
2378  NULL,
2379  OldIrql);
2380  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages += 1;
2381  }
2382  else {
2383  MiDeleteValidSystemPte (PointerPpe,
2384  PointerPde,
2385  WsInfo,
2386  &PteFlushList);
2387  }
2388 
2389  CommittedPages += 1;
2390 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2391  if ((FinalPte == TRUE) || (MiIsPteOnPxeBoundary(PointerPte))) {
2392 
2393  PointerPxe = MiGetPdeAddress (PointerPde);
2394 
2395  ASSERT (PointerPxe->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2396 
2397  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPxe));
2398 
2399  if (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1 && Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1)
2400  {
2401  if (Process != NULL) {
2402  MiDeletePte (PointerPxe,
2403  PointerPpe,
2404  AddressSpaceDeletion,
2405  Process,
2406  NULL,
2407  NULL,
2408  OldIrql);
2409  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages += 1;
2410  }
2411  else {
2412  MiDeleteValidSystemPte (PointerPxe,
2413  PointerPpe,
2414  WsInfo,
2415  &PteFlushList);
2416  }
2417  CommittedPages += 1;
2418  }
2419  }
2420 #endif
2421  }
2422  }
2423 #endif
2424  }
2425  if (FinalPte == TRUE) {
2426  break;
2427  }
2428  }
2429  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2430  } while (TRUE);
2431  }
2432 
2433  if (PteFlushList.Count == 0) {
2434  NOTHING;
2435  }
2436  else if (PteFlushList.Count == 1) {
2437  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (PteFlushList.FlushVa[0], AllProcessors);
2438  }
2439  else if (PteFlushList.Count < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
2440  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (PteFlushList.Count,
2441  &PteFlushList.FlushVa[0],
2442  AllProcessors);
2443  }
2444  else {
2445  if (AllProcessors) {
2446  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x1D);
2447  }
2448  else {
2449  MI_FLUSH_PROCESS_TB (FALSE);
2450  }
2451  }
2452 
2453  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2454 
2455  if (CommittedPages != 0) {
2456  MiReturnCommitment (CommittedPages);
2457  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_PTE_RANGE, CommittedPages);
2458 
2459  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (CommittedPages, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_CLEAN_PROCESS_WS);
2460  }
2461 
2462  return;
2463 }
2464 
2465 
2466 VOID
2467 MiUnlinkWorkingSet (
2468  IN PMMSUPPORT WsInfo
2469  )
2470 
2471 /*++
2472 
2473 Routine Description:
2474 
2475  This routine removes the argument working set from the working set
2476  manager's linked list.
2477 
2478 Arguments:
2479 
2480  WsInfo - Supplies the working set to remove.
2481 
2482 Return Value:
2483 
2484  None.
2485 
2486 Environment:
2487 
2488  Kernel mode, APCs disabled.
2489 
2490 --*/
2491 
2492 {
2493  KIRQL OldIrql;
2494  KEVENT Event;
2495  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
2496 
2497  //
2498  // If working set expansion for this process is allowed, disable
2499  // it and remove the process from expanded process list if it
2500  // is on it.
2501  //
2502 
2503  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
2504 
2505  if (WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_TRIMMING) {
2506 
2507  //
2508  // Initialize an event and put the event address
2509  // in the blink field. When the trimming is complete,
2510  // this event will be set.
2511  //
2512 
2513  KeInitializeEvent (&Event, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
2514 
2515  WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Blink = (PLIST_ENTRY)&Event;
2516 
2517  //
2518  // Release the mutex and wait for the event.
2519  //
2520 
2521  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
2522  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
2523 
2524  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
2525 
2526  KeWaitForSingleObject (&Event,
2527  WrVirtualMemory,
2528  KernelMode,
2529  FALSE,
2530  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
2531 
2532  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
2533 
2534  ASSERT (WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_NOT_LISTED);
2535  }
2536  else if (WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_NOT_LISTED) {
2537 
2538  //
2539  // This process' working set is in an initialization state and has
2540  // never been inserted into any lists.
2541  //
2542 
2543  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
2544  }
2545  else {
2546 
2547  RemoveEntryList (&WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks);
2548 
2549  //
2550  // Disable expansion.
2551  //
2552 
2553  WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink = MM_WS_NOT_LISTED;
2554 
2555  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
2556  }
2557 
2558  return;
2559 }
2560 
2561 
2562 VOID
2563 MmCleanProcessAddressSpace (
2564  IN PEPROCESS Process
2565  )
2566 
2567 /*++
2568 
2569 Routine Description:
2570 
2571  This routine cleans an address space by deleting all the user and
2572  pageable portions of the address space. At the completion of this
2573  routine, no page faults may occur within the process.
2574 
2575 Arguments:
2576 
2577  None.
2578 
2579 Return Value:
2580 
2581  None.
2582 
2583 Environment:
2584 
2585  Kernel mode, APCs disabled.
2586 
2587 --*/
2588 
2589 {
2590  PMMVAD Vad;
2591  PMMPTE LastPte;
2592  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2593  PETHREAD Thread;
2594  LONG AboveWsMin;
2595  ULONG NumberOfCommittedPageTables;
2596  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
2597  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
2598  PLOCK_TRACKER Tracker;
2599  PIO_ERROR_LOG_PACKET ErrLog;
2600 #if defined (_WIN64)
2601  PWOW64_PROCESS TempWow64;
2602 #endif
2603 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2604  PVOID CommittedPageTables;
2605 #endif
2606 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2607  PVOID CommittedPageDirectories;
2608 #endif
2609 
2610  if ((Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) ||
2611  (Process->AddressSpaceInitialized == 0)) {
2612 
2613  //
2614  // This process's address space has already been deleted. However,
2615  // this process can still have a session space. Get rid of it now.
2616  //
2617 
2618  MiSessionRemoveProcess ();
2619 
2620  return;
2621  }
2622 
2623  if (Process->AddressSpaceInitialized == 1) {
2624 
2625  //
2626  // The process has been created but not fully initialized.
2627  // Return partial resources now.
2628  //
2629 
2630  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (
2631  Process->Vm.MinimumWorkingSetSize - MM_PROCESS_CREATE_CHARGE,
2632  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_CLEAN_PROCESS1);
2633 
2634  //
2635  // Clear the AddressSpaceInitialized flag so we don't over-return
2636  // resident available as this routine can be called more than once
2637  // for the same process.
2638  //
2639 
2640  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_ADDRESS_SPACE1);
2641  ASSERT (Process->AddressSpaceInitialized == 0);
2642 
2643  //
2644  // This process's address space has already been deleted. However,
2645  // this process can still have a session space. Get rid of it now.
2646  //
2647 
2648  MiSessionRemoveProcess ();
2649 
2650  return;
2651  }
2652 
2653  //
2654  // Remove this process from the trim list.
2655  //
2656 
2657  MiUnlinkWorkingSet (&Process->Vm);
2658 
2659  //
2660  // Remove this process from the session list.
2661  //
2662 
2663  MiSessionRemoveProcess ();
2664 
2665  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (&MmWsle[MM_MAXIMUM_WORKING_SET]) + 1;
2666 
2667  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
2668 
2669  //
2670  // Delete all the user owned pageable virtual addresses in the process.
2671  //
2672 
2673  //
2674  // Both mutexes must be owned to synchronize with the bit setting and
2675  // clearing of VM_DELETED. This is because various callers acquire
2676  // only one of them (either one) before checking.
2677  //
2678 
2679  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
2680 
2681  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process)
2682 
2683  PS_SET_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED);
2684 
2685  //
2686  // Delete all the valid user mode addresses from the working set list.
2687  // At this point page faults are allowed on user space addresses but are
2688  // generally rare (would have to be an attached thread doing the
2689  // references). Faults are allowed on page tables for user space, which
2690  // requires that we keep the working set structure consistent until we
2691  // finally take it all down.
2692  //
2693 
2694  MiDeleteAddressesInWorkingSet (Process);
2695 
2696  //
2697  // Remove hash table pages, if any. This is the first time we do this
2698  // during the deletion path, but we need to do it again before we finish
2699  // because we may fault in some page tables during the VAD clearing. We
2700  // could have maintained the hash table validity during the WorkingSet
2701  // deletion above in order to avoid freeing the hash table twice, but since
2702  // we're just deleting it all anyway, it's faster to do it this way. Note
2703  // that if we don't do this or maintain the validity, we can trap later
2704  // in MiGrowWsleHash.
2705  //
2706 
2707  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmWorkingSetList->HighestPermittedHashAddress);
2708 
2709  MiDeletePteRange (&Process->Vm, PointerPte, LastPte, FALSE);
2710 
2711  //
2712  // Clear the hash fields as a fault may occur below on the page table
2713  // pages during VAD clearing and resolution of the fault may result in
2714  // adding a hash table. Thus these fields must be consistent with the
2715  // clearing just done above.
2716  //
2717 
2718  MmWorkingSetList->HashTableSize = 0;
2719  MmWorkingSetList->HashTable = NULL;
2720 
2721  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process)
2722 
2723  //
2724  // Delete the virtual address descriptors and dereference any
2725  // section objects.
2726  //
2727 
2728  while (Process->VadRoot.NumberGenericTableElements != 0) {
2729 
2730  Vad = (PMMVAD) Process->VadRoot.BalancedRoot.RightChild;
2731 
2732  MiRemoveVadCharges (Vad, Process);
2733 
2734  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process)
2735 
2736  MiRemoveVad (Vad, Process);
2737 
2738  //
2739  // If the system is NT64 (or NT32 and has been biased to an
2740  // alternate base address to allow 3gb of user address space),
2741  // then check if the current VAD describes the shared memory page.
2742  //
2743 
2744  if (MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS > (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA) {
2745 
2746  //
2747  // If the VAD describes the shared memory page, then free the
2748  // VAD and continue with the next entry.
2749  //
2750 
2751  if (Vad->StartingVpn == MI_VA_TO_VPN (MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA)) {
2752  ASSERT (MmHighestUserAddress > (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA);
2753  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process)
2754  ExFreePool (Vad);
2755  continue;
2756  }
2757  }
2758 
2759  if (((Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory == 0) &&
2760  (Vad->ControlArea != NULL)) ||
2761  (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory)) {
2762 
2763  //
2764  // This VAD represents a mapped view or a driver-mapped physical
2765  // view - delete the view and perform any section related cleanup
2766  // operations.
2767  //
2768 
2769  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadRotatePhysical) {
2770  MiPhysicalViewRemover (Process, Vad);
2771  }
2772 
2773  //
2774  // NOTE: MiRemoveMappedView releases the working set pushlock
2775  // before returning.
2776  //
2777 
2778  MiRemoveMappedView (Process, Vad);
2779  }
2780  else {
2781 
2782  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadLargePages) {
2783 
2784  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2785 
2786  MiAweViewRemover (Process, Vad);
2787 
2788  MiReleasePhysicalCharges (Vad->EndingVpn - Vad->StartingVpn + 1,
2789  Process);
2790 
2791  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2792 
2793  MiFreeLargePages (MI_VPN_TO_VA (Vad->StartingVpn),
2794  MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn),
2795  FALSE);
2796 
2797  }
2798  else if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadAwe) {
2799 
2800  //
2801  // Free all the physical pages that this VAD might be mapping.
2802  // Since only the AWE lock synchronizes the remap API, carefully
2803  // remove this VAD from the list first.
2804  //
2805 
2806  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2807 
2808  MiAweViewRemover (Process, Vad);
2809  MiRemoveUserPhysicalPagesVad ((PMMVAD_SHORT)Vad);
2810 
2811  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2812 
2813  MiDeletePageTablesForPhysicalRange (
2814  MI_VPN_TO_VA (Vad->StartingVpn),
2815  MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn));
2816  }
2817  else {
2818 
2819  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadWriteWatch) {
2820  MiPhysicalViewRemover (Process, Vad);
2821  }
2822 
2823  MiDeleteVirtualAddresses (MI_VPN_TO_VA (Vad->StartingVpn),
2824  MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn),
2825  Vad);
2826  }
2827 
2828  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process)
2829  }
2830 
2831  ExFreePool (Vad);
2832  }
2833 
2834  if (Process->AweInfo != NULL) {
2835  MiCleanPhysicalProcessPages (Process);
2836  }
2837 
2838  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2839 
2840  if (Process->CloneRoot != NULL) {
2841  ASSERT (((PMM_AVL_TABLE)Process->CloneRoot)->NumberGenericTableElements == 0);
2842  ExFreePool (Process->CloneRoot);
2843  Process->CloneRoot = NULL;
2844  }
2845 
2846  if (Process->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL) {
2847  ASSERT (Process->PhysicalVadRoot->NumberGenericTableElements == 0);
2848  ExFreePool (Process->PhysicalVadRoot);
2849  Process->PhysicalVadRoot = NULL;
2850  }
2851 
2852  //
2853  // Delete the shared data page, if any. Note this deliberately
2854  // compares the highest user address instead of the highest VAD address.
2855  // This is because we must always delete the link to the physical page
2856  // even on platforms where the VAD was not allocated. The only exception
2857  // to this is when we're booted on x86 with /USERVA=1nnn to increase the
2858  // kernel address space beyond 2GB.
2859  //
2860 
2861  if (MmHighestUserAddress > (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA) {
2862 
2863  //
2864  // This zeroes the PTE - so you would think after this, it can still
2865  // be faulted on and re-evaluated directly via MiCheckVirtualAddress
2866  // even though it has no VAD - however this cannot happen because
2867  // during this deletion, the containing page table page will be
2868  // deleted and this cannot be replaced without a VAD, thus short
2869  // circuiting the re-evaluation case above.
2870  //
2871 
2872  MiDeleteVirtualAddresses ((PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA,
2873  (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA,
2874  NULL);
2875  }
2876 
2877  //
2878  // Adjust the count of pages above working set maximum. This
2879  // must be done here because the working set list is not
2880  // updated during this deletion.
2881  //
2882 
2883  AboveWsMin = (LONG)(Process->Vm.WorkingSetSize - Process->Vm.MinimumWorkingSetSize);
2884 
2885  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2886 
2887  if (AboveWsMin > 0) {
2888  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmPagesAboveWsMinimum, 0 - (PFN_NUMBER)AboveWsMin);
2889  }
2890 
2891  //
2892  // Delete the system portion of the address space.
2893  // Only now is it safe to specify TRUE to MiDelete because now that the
2894  // VADs have been deleted we can no longer fault on user space pages.
2895  //
2896  // Return commitment for page table pages. Note that for NT64, we
2897  // allocate the arrays *AFTER* the initial MM_MAX_COMMIT VADs are created
2898  // because we detect 32 bit processes and allocate smaller arrays for
2899  // those since they have less accessible user virtual address space.
2900  // Thus for NT64, we must check that the allocation actually succeeded.
2901  //
2902 
2903  NumberOfCommittedPageTables = MmWorkingSetList->NumberOfCommittedPageTables;
2904 
2905 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2906  NumberOfCommittedPageTables += MmWorkingSetList->NumberOfCommittedPageDirectories;
2907 #endif
2908 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2909  NumberOfCommittedPageTables += MmWorkingSetList->NumberOfCommittedPageDirectoryParents;
2910 #endif
2911 
2912  MiReturnCommitment (NumberOfCommittedPageTables);
2913 
2914  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_PROCESS_CLEAN_PAGETABLES,
2915  NumberOfCommittedPageTables);
2916 
2917  Process->CommitCharge -= NumberOfCommittedPageTables;
2918  PsReturnProcessPageFileQuota (Process, NumberOfCommittedPageTables);
2919 
2920 
2921  MI_INCREMENT_TOTAL_PROCESS_COMMIT (0 - NumberOfCommittedPageTables);
2922 
2923 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
2924  CommittedPageTables = MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables;
2925  if (CommittedPageTables != NULL) {
2926  MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageTables = NULL;
2927  ExFreePool (CommittedPageTables);
2928  }
2929 #endif
2930 
2931 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
2932  CommittedPageDirectories = MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories;
2933  if (CommittedPageDirectories != NULL) {
2934  MmWorkingSetList->CommittedPageDirectories = NULL;
2935  ExFreePool (CommittedPageDirectories);
2936  }
2937 #endif
2938 
2939  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
2940 
2941  //
2942  // Make sure all the clone descriptors went away.
2943  //
2944 
2945  ASSERT (Process->CloneRoot == NULL);
2946 
2947  //
2948  // Make sure there are no dangling locked pages.
2949  //
2950 
2951  LockedPagesHeader = (PLOCK_HEADER) Process->LockedPagesList;
2952 
2953  if (Process->NumberOfLockedPages != 0) {
2954 
2955  if (LockedPagesHeader != NULL) {
2956 
2957  if ((LockedPagesHeader->Count != 0) &&
2958  (LockedPagesHeader->Valid == TRUE)) {
2959 
2960  ASSERT (IsListEmpty (&LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) == 0);
2961  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Flink;
2962 
2963  Tracker = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
2964  LOCK_TRACKER,
2965  ListEntry);
2966 
2967  KeBugCheckEx (DRIVER_LEFT_LOCKED_PAGES_IN_PROCESS,
2968  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->CallingAddress,
2969  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->CallersCaller,
2970  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->Mdl,
2971  Process->NumberOfLockedPages);
2972  }
2973  }
2974  else if (MiSafeBooted == FALSE) {
2975 
2976  if ((KdDebuggerEnabled) && (KdDebuggerNotPresent == FALSE)) {
2977 
2978  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
