2979  "A driver has leaked %d bytes of physical memory.\n",
2980  Process->NumberOfLockedPages << PAGE_SHIFT);
2981 
2982  //
2983  // Pop into the debugger (even on free builds) to determine
2984  // the cause of the leak and march on.
2985  //
2986 
2987  DbgBreakPoint ();
2988  }
2989 
2990  if (MmTrackLockedPages == FALSE) {
2991 
2992  MmTrackLockedPages = TRUE;
2993  MmLeakedLockedPages += Process->NumberOfLockedPages;
2994 
2995  ErrLog = IoAllocateGenericErrorLogEntry (ERROR_LOG_MAXIMUM_SIZE);
2996 
2997  if (ErrLog != NULL) {
2998 
2999  //
3000  // Fill it in and write it out.
3001  //
3002 
3003  ErrLog->FinalStatus = STATUS_DRIVERS_LEAKING_LOCKED_PAGES;
3004  ErrLog->ErrorCode = STATUS_DRIVERS_LEAKING_LOCKED_PAGES;
3005  ErrLog->UniqueErrorValue = (ULONG) MmLeakedLockedPages;
3006 
3007  IoWriteErrorLogEntry (ErrLog);
3008  }
3009  }
3010  }
3011  }
3012 
3013  if (LockedPagesHeader != NULL) {
3014 
3015  //
3016  // No need to acquire the spinlock to traverse here as the pages are
3017  // (unfortunately) never going to be unlocked. Since this routine is
3018  // pageable, this removes the need to add a nonpaged stub routine to
3019  // do the traverses and frees.
3020  //
3021 
3022  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Flink;
3023 
3024  while (NextEntry != &LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) {
3025 
3026  Tracker = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
3027  LOCK_TRACKER,
3028  ListEntry);
3029 
3030  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
3031 
3032  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Flink;
3033 
3034  ExFreePool (Tracker);
3035  }
3036 
3037  ExFreePool (LockedPagesHeader);
3038  Process->LockedPagesList = NULL;
3039  }
3040 
3041 #if DBG
3042  if ((Process->NumberOfPrivatePages != 0) && (MmDebug & MM_DBG_PRIVATE_PAGES)) {
3043  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
3044  "MM: Process contains private pages %ld\n",
3045  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages);
3046  DbgBreakPoint ();
3047  }
3048 #endif
3049 
3050 #if defined(_WIN64)
3051 
3052  //
3053  // Delete the WowProcess structure.
3054  //
3055 
3056  if (Process->Wow64Process != NULL) {
3057  TempWow64 = Process->Wow64Process;
3058  Process->Wow64Process = NULL;
3059  ExFreePool (TempWow64);
3060  }
3061 #endif
3062 
3063  //
3064  // Remove hash table pages, if any. Yes, we've already done this once
3065  // during the deletion path, but we need to do it again because we may
3066  // have faulted in some page tables during the VAD clearing.
3067  //
3068 
3069  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (&MmWsle[MM_MAXIMUM_WORKING_SET]) + 1;
3070 
3071  ASSERT (PointerPte < LastPte);
3072 
3073  MiDeletePteRange (&Process->Vm, PointerPte, LastPte, FALSE);
3074 
3075  ASSERT (Process->Vm.MinimumWorkingSetSize >= MM_PROCESS_CREATE_CHARGE);
3076  ASSERT (Process->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_NOT_LISTED);
3077 
3078  MmWorkingSetList->HashTableSize = 0;
3079  MmWorkingSetList->HashTable = NULL;
3080 
3081  //
3082  // Remove all the working set list pages except for the first one.
3083  //
3084  // The first page is not removed because an attached thread could
3085  // still reference the shared user data page and since no VAD is
3086  // required for this translation, the fault code will materialize
3087  // a page table page(s) and access the working set list to add entries
3088  // for it (and its page table pages) to the working set list.
3089  //
3090 
3091  MiRemoveWorkingSetPages (&Process->Vm);
3092 
3093  //
3094  // Update the count of available resident pages.
3095  //
3096 
3097  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (
3098  Process->Vm.MinimumWorkingSetSize - MM_PROCESS_CREATE_CHARGE,
3099  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_CLEAN_PROCESS2);
3100 
3101  UNLOCK_WS_AND_ADDRESS_SPACE (Thread, Process);
3102 
3103  if (Process->JobStatus & PS_JOB_STATUS_REPORT_COMMIT_CHANGES) {
3104  PsChangeJobMemoryUsage (PS_JOB_STATUS_REPORT_COMMIT_CHANGES,
3105  -(SSIZE_T)NumberOfCommittedPageTables);
3106  }
3107 
3108  return;
3109 }
3110 
3111 #define KERNEL_BSTORE_SIZE 0
3112 #define KERNEL_LARGE_BSTORE_SIZE 0
3113 #define KERNEL_LARGE_BSTORE_COMMIT 0
3114 #define KERNEL_STACK_GUARD_PAGES 1
3115 
3116 
3117 PVOID
3118 MmCreateKernelStack (
3119  IN BOOLEAN LargeStack,
3120  IN UCHAR PreferredNode
3121  )
3122 
3123 /*++
3124 
3125 Routine Description:
3126 
3127  This routine allocates a kernel stack and a no-access page within
3128  the non-pageable portion of the system address space.
3129 
3130 Arguments:
3131 
3132  LargeStack - Supplies the value TRUE if a large stack should be
3133  created. FALSE if a small stack is to be created.
3134 
3135  PreferredNode - Supplies the preferred node to use for the physical
3136  page allocations. MP/NUMA systems only.
3137 
3138 Return Value:
3139 
3140  Returns a pointer to the base of the kernel stack. Note, that the
3141  base address points to the guard page, so space must be allocated
3142  on the stack before accessing the stack.
3143 
3144  If a kernel stack cannot be created, the value NULL is returned.
3145 
3146 Environment:
3147 
3148  Kernel mode. APCs Disabled.
3149 
3150 --*/
3151 
3152 {
3153  PMMPFN Pfn1;
3154  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3155  PMMPTE BasePte;
3156  MMPTE TempPte;
3157  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3158  ULONG NumberOfPtes;
3159  ULONG ChargedPtes;
3160  ULONG RequestedPtes;
3161  ULONG NumberOfBackingStorePtes;
3162  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3163  ULONG i;
3164  PVOID StackVa;
3165  KIRQL OldIrql;
3166  PSLIST_HEADER DeadStackList;
3167  MMPTE DemandZeroPte;
3168 
3169  if (!LargeStack) {
3170 
3171  //
3172  // Check to see if any unused stacks are available.
3173  //
3174 
3175 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3176  DeadStackList = &KeNodeBlock[PreferredNode]->DeadStackList;
3177 #else
3178  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (PreferredNode);
3179  DeadStackList = &MmDeadStackSListHead;
3180 #endif
3181 
3182  if (ExQueryDepthSList (DeadStackList) != 0) {
3183 
3184  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) InterlockedPopEntrySList (DeadStackList);
3185 
3186  if (Pfn1 != NULL) {
3187  PointerPte = Pfn1->PteAddress;
3188  PointerPte += 1;
3189  StackVa = (PVOID)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
3190  return StackVa;
3191  }
3192  }
3193  NumberOfPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_STACK_SIZE);
3194  NumberOfBackingStorePtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_BSTORE_SIZE);
3195  NumberOfPages = NumberOfPtes + NumberOfBackingStorePtes;
3196  }
3197  else {
3198  NumberOfPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE);
3199  NumberOfBackingStorePtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_LARGE_BSTORE_SIZE);
3200  NumberOfPages = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT
3201  + KERNEL_LARGE_BSTORE_COMMIT);
3202  }
3203 
3204  ChargedPtes = NumberOfPtes + NumberOfBackingStorePtes;
3205 
3206  //
3207  // Charge commitment for the page file space for the kernel stack.
3208  //
3209 
3210  if (MiChargeCommitment (ChargedPtes, NULL) == FALSE) {
3211 
3212  //
3213  // Commitment exceeded, return NULL, indicating no kernel
3214  // stacks are available.
3215  //
3216 
3217  return NULL;
3218  }
3219 
3220  //
3221  // Obtain enough pages to contain the stack plus a guard page from
3222  // the system PTE pool. The system PTE pool contains nonpaged PTEs
3223  // which are currently empty.
3224  //
3225 
3226  RequestedPtes = ChargedPtes + KERNEL_STACK_GUARD_PAGES;
3227 
3228  BasePte = MiReserveSystemPtes (RequestedPtes, SystemPteSpace);
3229 
3230  if (BasePte == NULL) {
3231  MiReturnCommitment (ChargedPtes);
3232  return NULL;
3233  }
3234 
3235  PointerPte = BasePte;
3236 
3237  StackVa = (PVOID)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte + NumberOfPtes + 1);
3238 
3239  if (LargeStack) {
3240  PointerPte += BYTES_TO_PAGES (MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE - KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT);
3241  }
3242 
3243  DemandZeroPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
3244 
3245  DemandZeroPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
3246 
3247  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
3248  0,
3249  MM_READWRITE,
3250  (PointerPte + 1));
3251 
3252  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
3253 
3254  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3255 
3256  //
3257  // Check to make sure the physical pages are available.
3258  //
3259 
3260  if (MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE() <= (SPFN_NUMBER)NumberOfPages) {
3261  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3262  MiReleaseSystemPtes (BasePte, RequestedPtes, SystemPteSpace);
3263  MiReturnCommitment (ChargedPtes);
3264  return NULL;
3265  }
3266 
3267  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_KERNEL_STACK_CREATE, ChargedPtes);
3268 
3269  MI_DECREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (NumberOfPages,
3270  MM_RESAVAIL_ALLOCATE_CREATE_STACK);
3271 
3272  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
3273  PointerPte += 1;
3274  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3275  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
3276  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
3277  }
3278  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (
3279  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_NODE (PreferredNode));
3280 
3281  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, DemandZeroPte);
3282 
3283  MiInitializePfn (PageFrameIndex, PointerPte, 1);
3284 
3285  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
3286 
3287  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
3288  }
3289 
3290  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3291 
3292  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmProcessCommit, ChargedPtes);
3293  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmKernelStackResident, NumberOfPages);
3294  InterlockedExchangeAdd (&MmKernelStackPages, (LONG) RequestedPtes);
3295 
3296  if (LargeStack) {
3297  InterlockedIncrement (&MmLargeStacks);
3298  }
3299  else {
3300  InterlockedIncrement (&MmSmallStacks);
3301  }
3302 
3303  return StackVa;
3304 }
3305 
3306 VOID
3307 MmDeleteKernelStack (
3308  IN PVOID PointerKernelStack,
3309  IN BOOLEAN LargeStack
3310  )
3311 
3312 /*++
3313 
3314 Routine Description:
3315 
3316  This routine deletes a kernel stack and the no-access page within
3317  the non-pageable portion of the system address space.
3318 
3319 Arguments:
3320 
3321  PointerKernelStack - Supplies a pointer to the base of the kernel stack.
3322 
3323  LargeStack - Supplies the value TRUE if a large stack is being deleted.
3324  FALSE if a small stack is to be deleted.
3325 
3326 Return Value:
3327 
3328  None.
3329 
3330 Environment:
3331 
3332  Kernel mode. APCs Disabled.
3333 
3334 --*/
3335 
3336 {
3337  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3338  PMMPFN Pfn1;
3339  PMMPFN Pfn2;
3340  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3341  ULONG NumberOfPtes;
3342  ULONG NumberOfStackPtes;
3343  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3344  PFN_NUMBER PageTableFrameIndex;
3345  ULONG i;
3346  KIRQL OldIrql;
3347  MMPTE PteContents;
3348  PSLIST_HEADER DeadStackList;
3349 
3350  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (PointerKernelStack);
3351 
3352  //
3353  // PointerPte points to the guard page, point to the previous
3354  // page before removing physical pages.
3355  //
3356 
3357  PointerPte -= 1;
3358 
3359  //
3360  // Check to see if the stack page should be placed on the dead
3361  // kernel stack page list. The dead kernel stack list is a
3362  // singly linked list of kernel stacks from terminated threads.
3363  // The stacks are saved on a linked list up to a maximum number
3364  // to avoid the overhead of flushing the entire TB on all processors
3365  // everytime a thread terminates. The TB on all processors must
3366  // be flushed as kernel stacks reside in the non paged system part
3367  // of the address space.
3368  //
3369 
3370  if (!LargeStack) {
3371 
3372 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3373 
3374  //
3375  // Scan the physical page frames and only place this stack on the
3376  // dead stack list if all the pages are on the same node. Realize
3377  // if this push goes cross node it may make the interlocked instruction
3378  // slightly more expensive, but worth it all things considered.
3379  //
3380 
3381  ULONG NodeNumber;
3382 
3383  PteContents = *PointerPte;
3384  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
3385 
3386  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
3387  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3388  NodeNumber = Pfn1->u3.e1.PageColor;
3389 
3390  DeadStackList = &KeNodeBlock[NodeNumber]->DeadStackList;
3391 
3392 #else
3393 
3394  DeadStackList = &MmDeadStackSListHead;
3395 
3396 #endif
3397 
3398  NumberOfPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_STACK_SIZE + KERNEL_BSTORE_SIZE);
3399 
3400  if (ExQueryDepthSList (DeadStackList) < MmMaximumDeadKernelStacks) {
3401 
3402 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3403 
3404  //
3405  // The node could use some more dead stacks - but first make sure
3406  // all the physical pages are from the same node in a multinode
3407  // system.
3408  //
3409 
3410  if (KeNumberNodes > 1) {
3411 
3412  ULONG CheckPtes;
3413 
3414  CheckPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (KERNEL_STACK_SIZE);
3415 
3416  PointerPte -= 1;
3417  for (i = 1; i < CheckPtes; i += 1) {
3418 
3419  PteContents = *PointerPte;
3420 
3421  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3422  break;
3423  }
3424 
3425  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
3426  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3427 
3428  if (NodeNumber != Pfn1->u3.e1.PageColor) {
3429  PointerPte += i;
3430  goto FreeStack;
3431  }
3432  PointerPte -= 1;
3433  }
3434  PointerPte += CheckPtes;
3435  }
3436 #endif
3437 
3438  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
3439 
3440  InterlockedPushEntrySList (DeadStackList,
3441  (PSLIST_ENTRY)&Pfn1->u1.NextStackPfn);
3442 
3443  return;
3444  }
3445  }
3446  else {
3447  NumberOfPtes = BYTES_TO_PAGES (MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE + KERNEL_LARGE_BSTORE_SIZE);
3448  }
3449 
3450 
3451 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3452 FreeStack:
3453 #endif
3454 
3455  //
3456  // We have exceeded the limit of dead kernel stacks or this is a large
3457  // stack, delete this kernel stack.
3458  //
3459 
3460  NumberOfPages = 0;
3461 
3462  NumberOfStackPtes = NumberOfPtes + KERNEL_STACK_GUARD_PAGES;
3463 
3464  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3465 
3466  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPtes; i += 1) {
3467 
3468  PteContents = *PointerPte;
3469 
3470  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
3471  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
3472  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3473  PageTableFrameIndex = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
3474  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
3475  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
3476 
3477  //
3478  // Mark the page as deleted so it will be freed when the
3479  // reference count goes to zero.
3480  //
3481 
3482  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
3483  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
3484  NumberOfPages += 1;
3485  }
3486  PointerPte -= 1;
3487  }
3488 
3489  //
3490  // Now at the stack guard page, ensure it is still a guard page.
3491  //
3492 
3493  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3494 
3495  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3496 
3497  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmProcessCommit, 0 - (ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPtes);
3498  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmKernelStackResident, 0 - NumberOfPages);
3499  InterlockedExchangeAdd (&MmKernelStackPages, (LONG)(0 - NumberOfStackPtes));
3500 
3501  if (LargeStack) {
3502  InterlockedDecrement (&MmLargeStacks);
3503  }
3504  else {
3505  InterlockedDecrement (&MmSmallStacks);
3506  }
3507 
3508  //
3509  // Update the count of resident available pages.
3510  //
3511 
3512  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (NumberOfPages,
3513  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_DELETE_STACK);
3514 
3515  //
3516  // Return PTEs and commitment.
3517  //
3518 
3519  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte, NumberOfStackPtes, SystemPteSpace);
3520 
3521  MiReturnCommitment (NumberOfPtes);
3522 
3523  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_KERNEL_STACK_DELETE, NumberOfPtes);
3524 
3525  return;
3526 }
3527 
3528 ULONG MiStackGrowthFailures[1];
3529 
3530 NTSTATUS
3531 MmGrowKernelStack (
3532  __in PVOID CurrentStack
3533  )
3534 
3535 /*++
3536 
3537 Routine Description:
3538 
3539  This function attempts to grows the current thread's kernel stack
3540  such that there is always KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT bytes below
3541  the current stack pointer.
3542 
3543 Arguments:
3544 
3545  CurrentStack - Supplies a pointer to the current stack pointer.
3546 
3547 Return Value:
3548 
3549  STATUS_SUCCESS is returned if the stack was grown.
3550 
3551  STATUS_STACK_OVERFLOW is returned if there was not enough space reserved
3552  for the commitment.
3553 
3554  STATUS_NO_MEMORY is returned if there was not enough physical memory
3555  in the system.
3556 
3557 --*/
3558 
3559 {
3560  return MmGrowKernelStackEx (CurrentStack, KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT);
3561 }
3562 
3563 NTSTATUS
3564 MmGrowKernelStackEx (
3565  __in PVOID CurrentStack,
3566  __in SIZE_T CommitSize
3567  )
3568 
3569 /*++
3570 
3571 Routine Description:
3572 
3573  This function attempts to grows the current thread's kernel stack
3574  such that there is the specified number of bytes commited below
3575  the specified stack pointer.
3576 
3577 Arguments:
3578 
3579  CurrentStack - Supplies a pointer to the current stack pointer.
3580 
3581  CommmitSize - Supplies the required commit size in bytes.
3582 
3583 Return Value:
3584 
3585  STATUS_SUCCESS is returned if the stack was grown.
3586 
3587  STATUS_STACK_OVERFLOW is returned if there was not enough space reserved
3588  for the commitment.
3589 
3590  STATUS_NO_MEMORY is returned if there was not enough physical memory
3591  in the system.
3592 
3593 --*/
3594 
3595 {
3596  PMMPTE NewLimit;
3597  PMMPTE StackLimit;
3598  PMMPTE EndStack;
3599  PKTHREAD Thread;
3600  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3601  KIRQL OldIrql;
3602  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3603  MMPTE TempPte;
3604 
3605  Thread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
3606  ASSERT (((PCHAR)Thread->StackBase - (PCHAR)Thread->StackLimit) <=
3607  ((LONG)MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE + PAGE_SIZE));
3608 
3609  StackLimit = MiGetPteAddress (Thread->StackLimit);
3610 
3611  ASSERT (StackLimit->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
3612 
3613  NewLimit = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)((PUCHAR)CurrentStack - CommitSize));
3614 
3615  if (NewLimit == StackLimit) {
3616  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3617  }
3618 
3619  //
3620  // If the new stack limit exceeds the reserved region for the kernel
3621  // stack, then return an error.
3622  //
3623 
3624  EndStack = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)((PUCHAR)Thread->StackBase -
3625  MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE));
3626 
3627  if (NewLimit < EndStack) {
3628 
3629  //
3630  // Don't go into guard page.
3631  //
3632 
3633  MiStackGrowthFailures[0] += 1;
3634 
3635 #if DBG
3636  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
3637  "MmGrowKernelStack failed: Thread %p %p %p\n",
3638  Thread, NewLimit, EndStack);
3639 #endif
3640 
3641  return STATUS_STACK_OVERFLOW;
3642 
3643  }
3644 
3645  //
3646  // Lock the PFN database and attempt to expand the kernel stack.
3647  //
3648 
3649  StackLimit -= 1;
3650 
3651  NumberOfPages = (PFN_NUMBER) (StackLimit - NewLimit + 1);
3652 
3653  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3654 
3655  if (MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE() <= (SPFN_NUMBER)NumberOfPages) {
3656  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3657  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
3658  }
3659 
3660  //
3661  // Note MmResidentAvailablePages must be charged before calling
3662  // MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait as it may release the PFN lock.
3663  //
3664 
3665  MI_DECREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (NumberOfPages,
3666  MM_RESAVAIL_ALLOCATE_GROW_STACK);
3667 
3668  while (StackLimit >= NewLimit) {
3669 
3670  ASSERT (StackLimit->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3671 
3672  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
3673  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
3674  }
3675  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (StackLimit));
3676  StackLimit->u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
3677 
3678  StackLimit->u.Soft.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
3679 
3680  MiInitializePfn (PageFrameIndex, StackLimit, 1);
3681 
3682  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
3683  PageFrameIndex,
3684  MM_READWRITE,
3685  StackLimit);
3686 
3687  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
3688  *StackLimit = TempPte;
3689  StackLimit -= 1;
3690  }
3691 
3692  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3693 
3694  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmKernelStackResident, NumberOfPages);
3695 
3696 #if DBG
3697  ASSERT (NewLimit->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
3698  if (NewLimit != EndStack) {
3699  ASSERT ((NewLimit - 1)->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
3700  }
3701 #endif
3702 
3703  Thread->StackLimit = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (NewLimit);
3704 
3705  PERFINFO_GROW_STACK(Thread);
3706 
3707  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3708 }
3709 
3710 
3711 VOID
3712 MiOutPageSingleKernelStack (
3713  IN PKTHREAD Thread,
3714  IN PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT StackInfo,
3715  IN PMMPTE_FLUSH_LIST PteFlushList
3716  )
3717 
3718 /*++
3719 
3720 Routine Description:
3721 
3722  This routine makes the specified kernel stack non-resident and
3723  puts the pages on the transition list. Note that pages below
3724  the CurrentStackPointer are not useful and these pages are freed here.
3725 
3726 Arguments:
3727 
3728  Thread - Supplies a pointer to the thread whose stack should be removed.
3729 
3730  StackInfo - Supplies a pointer to the relevant stack information :
3731 
3732  StackBase - Supplies the highest virtual address of the
3733  stack. This is where the stack begins.
3734 
3735  KernelStack - Supplies the current stack pointer location.
3736 
3737  StackLimit - Supplies the lowest committed virtual address
3738  in the stack.
3739 
3740  ActualLimit - Supplies the lowest possible virtual address
3741  in the stack.
3742 
3743  PteFlushList - Supplies a flush list to use so the TB flush can be
3744  deferred to the caller.
3745 
3746 Return Value:
3747 
3748  None.
3749 
3750 Environment:
3751 
3752  Kernel mode.
3753 
3754 --*/
3755 
3756 {
3757  PVOID DiscardExcess;
3758  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3759  PMMPTE LastPte;
3760  PMMPTE EndOfStackPte;
3761  PMMPFN Pfn1;
3762  PMMPFN Pfn2;
3763  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3764  PFN_NUMBER PageTableFrameIndex;
3765  PFN_NUMBER ResAvailToReturn;
3766  KIRQL OldIrql;
3767  MMPTE TempPte;
3768  PVOID BaseOfKernelStack;
3769 
3770  ULONG Count;
3771  PMMPTE LimitPte;
3772  PMMPTE LowestLivePte;
3773 
3774  ASSERT (KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_SIZE >= MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE);
3775 
3776  ASSERT (BYTE_OFFSET (StackInfo->StackBase) == 0);
3777  ASSERT (BYTE_OFFSET (StackInfo->ActualLimit) == 0);
3778 
3779  ASSERT (((PCHAR)StackInfo->StackBase - (PCHAR)StackInfo->StackLimit) <=
3780  ((LONG)MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE + PAGE_SIZE));
3781 
3782  //
3783  // The first page of the stack is the page before the base
3784  // of the stack.
3785  //
3786 
3787  BaseOfKernelStack = ((PCHAR)StackInfo->StackBase - PAGE_SIZE);
3788  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseOfKernelStack);
3789  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack - 1);
3790 
3791  LowestLivePte = NULL;
3792 
3793  if (MI_STACK_IS_TRIMMABLE (Thread)) {
3794 
3795  DiscardExcess = (PVOID) (ROUND_TO_PAGES (Thread->InitialStack) - KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT);
3796 
3797  //
3798  // This is a large stack. The stack pagein won't necessarily
3799  // bring back all the pages. Make sure that we account now for the
3800  // ones that will disappear.
3801  //
3802 
3803  LowestLivePte = MiGetPteAddress (DiscardExcess);
3804 
3805  LimitPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID) StackInfo->StackLimit);
3806 
3807  if (LowestLivePte < LimitPte) {
3808  LowestLivePte = LimitPte;
3809  }
3810  }
3811 
3812  EndOfStackPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID) StackInfo->ActualLimit) - 1;
3813 
3814  ASSERT (LowestLivePte <= LastPte);
3815 
3816  //
3817  // Put a signature at the current stack location - sizeof(ULONG_PTR).
3818  //
3819 
3820  *((PULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack - 1) = (ULONG_PTR) Thread;
3821 
3822  Count = 0;
3823  ResAvailToReturn = 0;
3824 
3825  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3826 
3827  do {
3828  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
3829  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
3830 
3831 
3832  TempPte = *PointerPte;
3833  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, 0);
3834 
3835  TempPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
3836 
3837  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3838  Pfn2->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
3839 
3840  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
3841 
3842  if (PteFlushList->Count != MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
3843  PteFlushList->FlushVa[PteFlushList->Count] = BaseOfKernelStack;
3844  PteFlushList->Count += 1;
3845  }
3846 
3847  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, PageFrameIndex);
3848  PointerPte -= 1;
3849  Count += 1;
3850  BaseOfKernelStack = ((PCHAR)BaseOfKernelStack - PAGE_SIZE);
3851  } while (PointerPte >= LastPte);
3852 
3853  //
3854  // Just toss the pages that won't ever come back in.
3855  //
3856 
3857  while (PointerPte != EndOfStackPte) {
3858  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3859  break;
3860  }
3861 
3862  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
3863  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
3864 
3865  PageTableFrameIndex = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
3866  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
3867  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
3868 
3869  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
3870  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
3871 
3872  TempPte = KernelDemandZeroPte;
3873 
3874  TempPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
3875 
3876  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
3877 
3878  if (PteFlushList->Count != MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
3879  PteFlushList->FlushVa[PteFlushList->Count] = BaseOfKernelStack;
3880  PteFlushList->Count += 1;
3881  }
3882 
3883  Count += 1;
3884 
3885  //
3886  // Return resident available for pages beyond the guaranteed portion
3887  // as an explicit call to grow the kernel stack will be needed to get
3888  // these pages back.
3889  //
3890 
3891  if (PointerPte < LowestLivePte) {
3892  ASSERT (Thread->LargeStack);
3893  ResAvailToReturn += 1;
3894  }
3895 
3896  PointerPte -= 1;
3897  BaseOfKernelStack = ((PCHAR)BaseOfKernelStack - PAGE_SIZE);
3898  }
3899 
3900  if (ResAvailToReturn != 0) {
3901  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (ResAvailToReturn,
3902  MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_OUTPAGE_STACK);
3903  ResAvailToReturn = 0;
3904  }
3905 
3906  ASSERT (PteFlushList->Count != 0);
3907  ASSERT (Count != 0);
3908 
3909  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
3910 
3911  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmKernelStackResident, 0 - Count);
3912 
3913  return;
3914 }
3915 
3916 VOID
3917 MmOutPageKernelStack (
3918  IN PKTHREAD Thread
3919  )
3920 
3921 /*++
3922 
3923 Routine Description:
3924 
3925  This routine makes the specified kernel stack non-resident and
3926  puts the pages on the transition list. Note that pages below
3927  the CurrentStackPointer are not useful and these pages are freed here.
3928 
3929 Arguments:
3930 
3931  Thread - Supplies a pointer to the thread whose stack should be removed.
3932 
3933 Return Value:
3934 
3935  None.
3936 
3937 Environment:
3938 
3939  Kernel mode.
3940 
3941 --*/
3942 
3943 {
3944  MMPTE_FLUSH_LIST PteFlushList;
3945 
3946  ASSERT (KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_SIZE >= MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE);
3947 
3948  ASSERT (((PCHAR)Thread->StackBase - (PCHAR)Thread->StackLimit) <=
3949  ((LONG)MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE + PAGE_SIZE));
3950 
3951  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_DISABLE_PAGE_KERNEL_STACKS) {
3952  return;
3953  }
3954 
3955  PteFlushList.Count = 0;
3956  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (PteFlushList.FlushVa[0] = NULL);
3957 
3958 #if defined (_MI_CHAINED_STACKS)
3959 
3960  {
3961 
3962  PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT StackInfo;
3963  PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT NextStackInfo;
3964 
3965  //
3966  // Note ActualLimit is only set in Current, and InitialStack in Previous.
3967  //
3968  // StackLimit is the lowest committed address.
3969  //
3970  // KernelStack is the lowest referenced virtual address.
3971  //
3972  // StackBase is the highest virtual address.
3973  // ActualLimit is the lowest possible virtual address.
3974  //
3975 
3976  StackInfo = KeGetFirstKernelStackSegment (Thread);
3977 
3978  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackLimit == (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackLimit);
3979 
3980  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackBase == (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackBase); // hi VA
3981  ASSERT (StackInfo->KernelStack == (ULONG_PTR) Thread->KernelStack);
3982 
3983 
3984  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackLimit < StackInfo->StackBase);
3985  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackLimit >= StackInfo->ActualLimit);
3986 
3987  ASSERT (StackInfo->ActualLimit < StackInfo->StackBase);
3988  ASSERT (StackInfo->ActualLimit >= StackInfo->StackBase - MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE);
3989 
3990  ASSERT (StackInfo->KernelStack < StackInfo->StackBase);
3991  ASSERT (StackInfo->KernelStack >= StackInfo->StackLimit);
3992 
3993  do {
3994 
3995  NextStackInfo = KeGetNextKernelStackSegment (StackInfo);
3996 
3997  MiOutPageSingleKernelStack (Thread, StackInfo, &PteFlushList);
3998 
3999  StackInfo = NextStackInfo;
4000 
4001  } while (StackInfo != NULL);
4002 
4003  }
4004 
4005 #else
4006 
4007  {
4008 
4009  KERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT LocalStackInfo;
4010 
4011  LocalStackInfo.StackBase = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackBase;
4012  LocalStackInfo.StackLimit = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackLimit;
4013  LocalStackInfo.KernelStack = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->KernelStack;
4014 
4015  if (Thread->LargeStack) {
4016  LocalStackInfo.ActualLimit = LocalStackInfo.StackBase - MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE;
4017  }
4018  else {
4019  LocalStackInfo.ActualLimit = LocalStackInfo.StackBase - KERNEL_STACK_SIZE;
4020  }
4021 
4022  MiOutPageSingleKernelStack (Thread, &LocalStackInfo, &PteFlushList);
4023 
4024  }
4025 
4026 #endif
4027 
4028  ASSERT (PteFlushList.Count != 0);
4029 
4030  if (PteFlushList.Count == 1) {
4031  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (PteFlushList.FlushVa[0], TRUE);
4032  }
4033  else if (PteFlushList.Count < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
4034  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (PteFlushList.Count,
4035  &PteFlushList.FlushVa[0],
4036  TRUE);
4037  }
4038  else {
4039  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x24);
4040  }
4041 
4042  return;
4043 }
4044 
4045 VOID
4046 MiInPageSingleKernelStack (
4047  IN PKTHREAD Thread,
4048  IN PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT StackInfo
4049  )
4050 
4051 /*++
4052 
4053 Routine Description:
4054 
4055  This routine makes the specified kernel stack resident.
4056 
4057 Arguments:
4058 
4059  Thread - Supplies a pointer to the thread whose stack should be
4060  made resident.
4061 
4062  StackInfo - Supplies a pointer to the relevant stack information.
4063 
4064 Return Value:
4065 
4066  None.
4067 
4068 Environment:
4069 
4070  Kernel mode.
4071 
4072 --*/
4073 
4074 {
4075  PVOID DiscardExcess;
4076  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
4077  PVOID BaseOfKernelStack;
4078  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4079  PMMPTE EndOfStackPte;
4080  PMMPTE SignaturePte;
4081  ULONG DiskRead;
4082  PFN_NUMBER ContainingPage;
4083  KIRQL OldIrql;
4084 
4085  //
4086  // The first page of the stack is the page before the base of the stack.
4087  //
4088 
4089  if (MI_STACK_IS_TRIMMABLE (Thread)) {
4090 
4091  DiscardExcess = (PVOID) (ROUND_TO_PAGES (StackInfo->InitialStack) - KERNEL_LARGE_STACK_COMMIT);
4092 
4093  EndOfStackPte = MiGetPteAddress (DiscardExcess);
4094 
4095  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)StackInfo->StackLimit);
4096 
4097  //
4098  // Trim back the stack. Make sure that the stack does not
4099  // grow, i.e. StackLimit remains the limit.
4100  //
4101 
4102  if (EndOfStackPte < PointerPte) {
4103  EndOfStackPte = PointerPte;
4104  }
4105 
4106  DiscardExcess = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (EndOfStackPte);
4107 
4108  Thread->StackLimit = DiscardExcess;
4109  StackInfo->StackLimit = (ULONG_PTR) DiscardExcess;
4110  }
4111  else {
4112  EndOfStackPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID) StackInfo->StackLimit);
4113  }
4114 
4115  BaseOfKernelStack = (PVOID) (StackInfo->StackBase - PAGE_SIZE);
4116 
4117  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseOfKernelStack);
4118 
4119  DiskRead = 0;
4120  SignaturePte = MiGetPteAddress ((PULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack - 1);
4121  ASSERT (SignaturePte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
4122  if ((SignaturePte->u.Long != MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE) &&
4123  (SignaturePte->u.Soft.Transition == 0)) {
4124  DiskRead = 1;
4125  }
4126 
4127  NumberOfPages = 0;
4128 
4129  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4130 
4131  while (PointerPte >= EndOfStackPte) {
4132 
4133  if (!((PointerPte->u.Long == KernelDemandZeroPte.u.Long) ||
4134  (PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection == MM_NOACCESS))) {
4135 
4136  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
4137  0x3451,
4138  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
4139  (ULONG_PTR)Thread,
4140  0);
4141  }
4142  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
4143  if (PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection == MM_NOACCESS) {
4144  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection = PAGE_READWRITE;
4145  }
4146 
4147  ContainingPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte));
4148  MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (PointerPte,
4149  PointerPte,
4150  1,
4151  ContainingPage,
4152  OldIrql);
4153 
4154  PointerPte -= 1;
4155  NumberOfPages += 1;
4156  }
4157 
4158  //
4159  // Check the signature at the current stack location - sizeof (ULONG_PTR).
4160  //
4161 
4162  if (*((PULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack - 1) != (ULONG_PTR)Thread) {
4163  KeBugCheckEx (KERNEL_STACK_INPAGE_ERROR,
4164  DiskRead,
4165  *((PULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack - 1),
4166  0,
4167  (ULONG_PTR)StackInfo->KernelStack);
4168  }
4169 
4170  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4171 
4172  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmKernelStackResident, NumberOfPages);
4173 
4174  return;
4175 }
4176 
4177 
4178 VOID
4179 MmInPageKernelStack (
4180  IN PKTHREAD Thread
4181  )
4182 
4183 /*++
4184 
4185 Routine Description:
4186 
4187  This routine makes the specified kernel stack resident.
4188 
4189 Arguments:
4190 
4191  Supplies a pointer to the base of the kernel stack.
4192 
4193 Return Value:
4194 
4195  Thread - Supplies a pointer to the thread whose stack should be
4196  made resident.
4197 
4198 Environment:
4199 
4200  Kernel mode.
4201 
4202 --*/
4203 
4204 {
4205  PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT StackInfo;
4206  KERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT LocalStackInfo;
4207 
4208  ASSERT (((PCHAR)Thread->StackBase - (PCHAR)Thread->StackLimit) <=
4209  ((LONG)MI_LARGE_STACK_SIZE + PAGE_SIZE));
4210 
4211  if (NtGlobalFlag & FLG_DISABLE_PAGE_KERNEL_STACKS) {
4212  return;
4213  }
4214 
4215  //
4216  // Construct a local StackInfo structure and make the pertinent
4217  // stack resident so that any others can be walked to.
4218  //
4219  // Note ActualLimit is only set in Current, and InitialStack in Previous.
4220  //
4221  // StackLimit is the lowest committed address.
4222  //
4223  // KernelStack is the lowest referenced virtual address.
4224  //
4225  // StackBase is the highest virtual address.
4226  //
4227  // ActualLimit is the lowest possible virtual address but this field
4228  // in the local StackInfo is not filled in here.
4229  //
4230  // DO NOT INITIALIZE or REFERENCE the StackInfo->ActualLimit field !!!
4231  //
4232  // The StackInfo->ActualLimit is not replicated in the KTHREAD anywhere.
4233  // And the StackInfo itself is not resident. So this field cannot be
4234  // referenced until *AFTER* the stack has been made resident.
4235  //
4236 
4237  LocalStackInfo.StackBase = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackBase;
4238  LocalStackInfo.StackLimit = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->StackLimit;
4239  LocalStackInfo.KernelStack = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->KernelStack;
4240  LocalStackInfo.InitialStack = (ULONG_PTR) Thread->InitialStack;
4241 
4242  StackInfo = &LocalStackInfo;
4243 
4244  MiInPageSingleKernelStack (Thread, StackInfo);
4245 
4246 #if defined (_MI_CHAINED_STACKS)
4247 
4248  //
4249  // Note constructing the local StackInfo (instead of calling
4250  // KeGetFirstKernelStackSegment) was necessary because the thread's
4251  // initial stack VA is not resident on entry to this function.
4252  //
4253 
4254  StackInfo = KeGetFirstKernelStackSegment (Thread);
4255 
4256  ASSERT (StackInfo == &((PKERNEL_STACK_CONTROL) (LocalStackInfo.InitialStack))->Current);
4257  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackBase == LocalStackInfo.StackBase);
4258  ASSERT (StackInfo->StackLimit == LocalStackInfo.StackLimit);
4259  ASSERT (StackInfo->KernelStack == LocalStackInfo.KernelStack);
4260 
4261  do {
4262 
4263  PKERNEL_STACK_SEGMENT PreviousStackInfo;
4264 
4265  //
4266  // KeGetNextKernelStackSegment (StackInfo) cannot be used because
4267  // it reaches into the next segment which is currently paged out.
4268  //
4269 
4270  PreviousStackInfo = StackInfo + 1;
4271 
4272  if (PreviousStackInfo->StackBase == 0) {
4273  break;
4274  }
4275 
4276  LocalStackInfo = *PreviousStackInfo;
4277 
4278  MiInPageSingleKernelStack (Thread, &LocalStackInfo);
4279 
4280  StackInfo = &((PKERNEL_STACK_CONTROL) LocalStackInfo.InitialStack)->Current;
4281 
4282  } while (TRUE);
4283 
4284 #endif
4285 
4286  return;
4287 }
4288 
4289 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4290 
4291 PFN_NUMBER
4292 MiTrimPageParents (
4293  IN PEPROCESS OutProcess,
4294  IN PFN_NUMBER PdePage,
4295  IN PMMPTE OutTempPte
4296  )
4297 {
4298  PFN_NUMBER TopPage;
4299  KIRQL OldIrql;
4300  MMPTE TempPte;
4301  MMPTE TempPte2;
4302  PMMPTE MappingPte;
4303  PMMPTE PageDirectoryMap;
4304  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
4305  PMMPFN Pfn1;
4306  PFN_NUMBER PpePage;
4307 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4308  PMMPFN Pfn2;
4309  PFN_NUMBER PxePage;
4310 #endif
4311 
4312  //
4313  // OutProcess really is referenced on checked or non-AMD builds, but it's
4314  // not worth ifdefing this just for the compiler.
4315  //
4316 
4317  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (OutProcess);
4318 
4319  OldIrql = MM_NOIRQL;
4320  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage);
4321  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
4322 
4323  //
4324  // Remove the page directory page.
4325  //
4326 
4327  PpePage = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
4328  ASSERT (PpePage != 0);
4329 
4330 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 4)
4331  ASSERT (PpePage == MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE((PMMPTE)(&(OutProcess->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0]))));
4332 #endif
4333 
4334  PageDirectoryMap = NULL;
4335 
4336  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
4337 
4338  if (MappingPte > (PMMPTE)1) {
4339 
4340  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
4341  PpePage,
4342  MM_READWRITE,
4343  MappingPte);
4344 
4345  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
4346 
4347  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
4348 
4349  PageDirectoryMap = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
4350  }
4351  else {
4352  if (MappingPte == NULL) {
4353  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PpePage, &OldIrql);
4354  }
4355  }
4356 
4357  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPpeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
4358 
4359  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4360  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber == PdePage);
4361 
4362  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4363 
4364  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPpeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
4365 
4366  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4367 
4368 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 4)
4369 
4370  //
4371  // Remove the top level page directory parent page.
4372  //
4373 
4374  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPpeOffset(PDE_TBASE)];
4375 
4376  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte,
4377  MM_READWRITE);
4378 
4379  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPpeOffset(PDE_TBASE)] = TempPte;
4380 
4381  TopPage = PpePage;
4382 
4383 #endif
4384 
4385  if (MappingPte == (PMMPTE)1) {
4386 
4387  //
4388  // Nothing needs to be done if a KSEG3 mapping was used ...
4389  //
4390 
4391  NOTHING;
4392  }
4393  else if (MappingPte != NULL) {
4394  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
4395  }
4396  else {
4397  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap, OldIrql);
4398  }
4399 
4400 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4401 
4402  //
4403  // Remove the page directory parent page. Then remove
4404  // the top level extended page directory parent page.
4405  //
4406 
4407  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PpePage);
4408  PxePage = Pfn2->u4.PteFrame;
4409  ASSERT (PxePage);
4410  ASSERT (PxePage == MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE((PMMPTE)(&(OutProcess->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0]))));
4411 
4412  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
4413 
4414  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
4415 
4416  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte2,
4417  PxePage,
4418  MM_READWRITE,
4419  MappingPte);
4420 
4421  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte2);
4422 
4423  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte2);
4424 
4425  PageDirectoryMap = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
4426  }
4427  else {
4428  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PxePage, &OldIrql);
4429  }
4430 
4431  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPxeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
4432 
4433  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4434  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber == PpePage);
4435 
4436  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4437 
4438  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPxeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
4439 
4440  ASSERT (MI_PFN_ELEMENT(PpePage)->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4441 
4442  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPxeOffset(PXE_BASE)];
4443 
4444  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4445 
4446  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPxeOffset(PXE_BASE)] = TempPte;
4447 
4448  if (MappingPte != NULL) {
4449  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
4450  }
4451  else {
4452  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap, OldIrql);
4453  }
4454 
4455  TopPage = PxePage;
4456 
4457 #endif
4458 
4459  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4460  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PdePage);
4461 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4462  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, PpePage);
4463 #endif
4464  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4465 
4466  *OutTempPte = TempPte;
4467 
4468  return TopPage;
4469 }
4470 
4471 #endif
4472 
4473 
4474 VOID
4475 MmOutSwapProcess (
4476  IN PKPROCESS Process
4477  )
4478 
4479 /*++
4480 
4481 Routine Description:
4482 
4483  This routine out swaps the specified process.
4484 
4485 Arguments:
4486 
4487  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process to swap out of memory.
4488 
4489 Return Value:
4490 
4491  None.
4492 
4493 --*/
4494 
4495 {
4496  KIRQL OldIrql;
4497  PEPROCESS OutProcess;
4498  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4499  PMMPFN Pfn1;
4500  PMMPFN Pfn2;
4501  PMMPFN Pfn3;
4502  PFN_NUMBER HyperSpacePageTable;
4503  PMMPTE HyperSpacePageTableMap;
4504  PFN_NUMBER PdePage;
4505  PFN_NUMBER ProcessPage;
4506  MMPTE TempPte;
4507  MMPTE TempPte2;
4508  MMPTE TempPte3;
4509  PMMPTE MappingPte;
4510  PMMPTE PageDirectoryMap;
4511  PFN_NUMBER VadBitMapPage;
4512  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
4513 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
4514  PMMPFN Pfn5[PD_PER_SYSTEM];
4515  ULONG i;
4516  PFN_NUMBER PdePage2;
4517  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectories[PD_PER_SYSTEM];
4518  PPAE_ENTRY PaeVa;
4519 #endif
4520 
4521  OutProcess = CONTAINING_RECORD (Process, EPROCESS, Pcb);
4522 
4523  PS_SET_BITS (&OutProcess->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAP_ENABLED);
4524 
4525 #if DBG
4526  if ((MmDebug & MM_DBG_SWAP_PROCESS) != 0) {
4527  return;
4528  }
4529 #endif
4530 
4531  if (OutProcess->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_IN_SESSION) {
4532  MiSessionOutSwapProcess (OutProcess);
4533  }
4534 
4535  //
4536  // The process cannot be fully swapped out unless its working set has
4537  // been reduced to the bare minimum. If the working set is larger than
4538  // this, then just return as the working set manager thread will trim it
4539  // down. Eventually when it is trimmed to the bare minimum, the working
4540  // set manager thread will detach from the process and if it is the last
4541  // thread (ie: all the others are in usermode waits), then another process
4542  // outswap request will occur for this process at which time we will be
4543  // able to proceed below.
4544  //
4545 
4546  if (OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetSize == MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE) {
4547 
4548  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
4549 
4550  ASSERT (OutProcess->Outswapped == 0);
4551 
4552  if (OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_TRIMMING) {
4553 
4554  //
4555  // An outswap is not allowed at this point because the process
4556  // has been attached to and is being trimmed.
4557  //
4558 
4559  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
4560  return;
4561  }
4562 
4563  //
4564  // Swap the process working set info and page parent/directory/table
4565  // pages from memory.
4566  //
4567 
4568  PS_SET_BITS (&OutProcess->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAPPED);
4569 
4570  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
4571 
4572  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
4573 
4574  //
4575  // Remove the working set list page from the process.
4576  //
4577  // Note the PFN lock does not need to be held to put the PTEs for
4578  // these pages into transition because no one can be referencing
4579  // these addresses in the context of the process being outswapped.
4580  //
4581 
4582  HyperSpacePageTable = MI_GET_HYPER_PAGE_TABLE_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS (OutProcess);
4583  HyperSpacePageTableMap = NULL;
4584 
4585  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
4586 
4587  if (MappingPte > (PMMPTE) 1) {
4588 
4589  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte3,
4590  HyperSpacePageTable,
4591  MM_READWRITE,
4592  MappingPte);
4593 
4594  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte3);
4595 
4596  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte3);
4597 
4598  HyperSpacePageTableMap = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
4599  }
4600  else if (MappingPte == NULL) {
4601  HyperSpacePageTableMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess,
4602  HyperSpacePageTable,
4603  &OldIrql);
4604  }
4605 
4606  //
4607  // Put the working set list table PTE into transition.
4608  //
4609 
4610  TempPte = HyperSpacePageTableMap[MiGetPteOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
4611 
4612  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4613 
4614  HyperSpacePageTableMap[MiGetPteOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
4615 
4616  //
4617  // Put the VAD bitmap PTE into transition.
4618  //
4619 
4620  PointerPte = &HyperSpacePageTableMap[MiGetPteOffset (VAD_BITMAP_SPACE)];
4621  TempPte2 = *PointerPte;
4622 
4623  VadBitMapPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE((PMMPTE)&TempPte2);
4624 
4625  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte2, MM_READWRITE);
4626 
4627  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte2);
4628 
4629  if (MappingPte == (PMMPTE)1) {
4630 
4631  //
4632  // Nothing needs to be done if a KSEG3 mapping was used ...
4633  //
4634 
4635  NOTHING;
4636  }
4637  else if (MappingPte != NULL) {
4638  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
4639  }
4640  else {
4641  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTableMap, OldIrql);
4642  }
4643 
4644  //
4645  // Capture all the PFN information and then get the PFN lock and
4646  // actually move all the pages onto the modified list.
4647  //
4648 
4649  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (VadBitMapPage);
4650  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (OutProcess->WorkingSetPage);
4651 
4652  Pfn3 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (HyperSpacePageTable);
4653  ASSERT (Pfn3->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4654  PdePage = Pfn3->u4.PteFrame;
4655  ASSERT (PdePage != 0);
4656 
4657  //
4658  // Remove the hyper space page table from the process.
4659  //
4660 
4661  PageDirectoryMap = NULL;
4662 
4663  MappingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
4664 
4665  if (MappingPte > (PMMPTE) 1) {
4666 
4667  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte3,
4668  PdePage,
4669  MM_READWRITE,
4670  MappingPte);
4671 
4672  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte3);
4673 
4674  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (MappingPte, TempPte3);
4675 
4676  PageDirectoryMap = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (MappingPte);
4677  }
4678  else {
4679  if (MappingPte == NULL) {
4680  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PdePage, &OldIrql);
4681  }
4682  }
4683 
4684  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
4685 
4686  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4687  ASSERT (TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber == HyperSpacePageTable);
4688 
4689  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4690 
4691  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
4692 
4693 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
4694 
4695  //
4696  // Remove the additional page directory pages.
4697  //
4698 
4699  PaeVa = (PPAE_ENTRY)OutProcess->PaeTop;
4700  ASSERT (PaeVa != &MiSystemPaeVa);
4701 
4702  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
4703 
4704  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[i];
4705  PdePage2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE((PMMPTE)&TempPte);
4706 
4707  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4708 
4709  PageDirectoryMap[i] = TempPte;
4710  ASSERT (MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage2)->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4711 
4712  PageDirectories[i] = PdePage2;
4713  PaeVa->PteEntry[i].u.Long = TempPte.u.Long;
4714 
4715  Pfn5[i] = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage2);
4716  }
4717 
4718 #if DBG
4719  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[i];
4720  PdePage2 = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&TempPte);
4721  ASSERT ((MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage2))->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4722 #endif
4723 
4724 #endif
4725 
4726 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
4727 
4728  //
4729  // Remove the top level page directory page.
4730  //
4731 
4732  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(PDE_BASE)];
4733 
4734  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte, MM_READWRITE);
4735 
4736  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(PDE_BASE)] = TempPte;
4737 
4738 #endif
4739 
4740  if (MappingPte == (PMMPTE)1) {
4741 
4742  //
4743  // Nothing needs to be done if a KSEG3 mapping was used ...
4744  //
4745 
4746  NOTHING;
4747  }
4748  else if (MappingPte != NULL) {
4749  MiReleaseSystemPtes (MappingPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
4750  }
4751  else {
4752  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap, OldIrql);
4753  }
4754 
4755  //
4756  // Now acquire the PFN lock and free all the pages whose PTEs we
4757  // put in transition above.
4758  //
4759 
4760  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4761 
4762  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4763  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, VadBitMapPage);
4764 
4765  ASSERT (Pfn2->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4766  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn2, OutProcess->WorkingSetPage);
4767 
4768  ASSERT (Pfn3->u3.e1.Modified == 1);
4769  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn3, HyperSpacePageTable);
4770 
4771 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
4772  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
4773  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn5[i], PageDirectories[i]);
4774  }
4775 #endif
4776 
4777 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4778  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4779  PdePage = MiTrimPageParents (OutProcess, PdePage, &TempPte);
4780  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4781 #endif
4782 
4783  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage);
4784 
4785  //
4786  // Decrement share count so the top level page directory page gets
4787  // removed. This can cause the PteCount to equal the sharecount as the
4788  // page directory page no longer contains itself, yet can have
4789  // itself as a transition page.
4790  //
4791 
4792  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount -= 2;
4793  Pfn1->PteAddress = (PMMPTE) &OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte;
4794 
4795  OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte = TempPte.u.Flush;
4796 
4797 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
4798  PaeVa->PteEntry[i].u.Long = TempPte.u.Long;
4799 #endif
4800 
4801  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(OutProcess)) {
4802  ProcessPage = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (OutProcess);
4803  }
4804  else {
4805  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (OutProcess);
4806  ProcessPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
4807  }
4808 
4809  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = ProcessPage;
4810  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (ProcessPage);
4811 
4812  //
4813  // Increment the share count for the process page.
4814  //
4815 
4816  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
4817 
4818  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4819 
4820  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
4821 
4822  if (OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink > MM_WS_TRIMMING) {
4823 
4824  //
4825  // The entry must be on the list.
4826  //
4827 
4828  RemoveEntryList (&OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks);
4829  OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink = MM_WS_SWAPPED_OUT;
4830  }
4831 
4832  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
4833 
4834  OutProcess->WorkingSetPage = 0;
4835  OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetSize = 0;
4836  }
4837 
4838  return;
4839 }
4840 
4841 VOID
4842 MmInSwapProcess (
4843  IN PKPROCESS Process
4844  )
4845 
4846 /*++
4847 
4848 Routine Description:
4849 
4850  This routine in swaps the specified process.
4851 
4852 Arguments:
4853 
4854  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process that is to be swapped
4855  into memory.
4856 
4857 Return Value:
4858 
4859  None.
4860 
4861 --*/
4862 
4863 {
4864  KIRQL OldIrql;
4865  PEPROCESS OutProcess;
4866  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
4867  PFN_NUMBER PdePage;
4868  PMMPTE PageDirectoryMap;
4869  MMPTE VadBitMapPteContents;
4870  PFN_NUMBER VadBitMapPage;
4871  ULONG WorkingSetListPteOffset;
4872  ULONG VadBitMapPteOffset;
4873  PMMPTE WorkingSetListPte;
4874  PMMPTE VadBitMapPte;
4875  MMPTE TempPte;
4876  PFN_NUMBER HyperSpacePageTable;
4877  PMMPTE HyperSpacePageTableMap;
4878  PFN_NUMBER WorkingSetPage;
4879  PMMPFN Pfn1;
4880  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4881  PFN_NUMBER ProcessPage;
4882 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4883  PFN_NUMBER TopPage;
4884  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectoryPage;
4885  PMMPTE PageDirectoryParentMap;
4886 #endif
4887 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
4888  ULONG i;
4889  PPAE_ENTRY PaeVa;
4890  MMPTE PageDirectoryPtes[PD_PER_SYSTEM];
4891 #endif
4892 
4893  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
4894 
4895  OutProcess = CONTAINING_RECORD (Process, EPROCESS, Pcb);
4896 
4897  if (OutProcess->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAPPED) {
4898 
4899  //
4900  // The process is out of memory, rebuild the initialized page
4901  // structure.
4902  //
4903 
4904  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(OutProcess)) {
4905  ProcessPage = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (OutProcess);
4906  }
4907  else {
4908  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (OutProcess);
4909  ProcessPage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
4910  }
4911 
4912  WorkingSetListPteOffset = MiGetPteOffset (MmWorkingSetList);
4913  VadBitMapPteOffset = MiGetPteOffset (VAD_BITMAP_SPACE);
4914 
4915  WorkingSetListPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmWorkingSetList);
4916  VadBitMapPte = MiGetPteAddress (VAD_BITMAP_SPACE);
4917 
4918  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4919 
4920  PdePage = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
4921 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4922  MiGetPteAddress (PXE_BASE),
4923 #elif (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4924  MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)PDE_TBASE),
4925 #else
4926  MiGetPteAddress (PDE_BASE),
4927 #endif
4928  (PMMPTE)&OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte,
4929  0,
4930  ProcessPage,
4931  OldIrql);
4932 
4933  //
4934  // Adjust the counts for the process page.
4935  //
4936 
4937  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (ProcessPage);
4938  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount -= 1;
4939 
4940  ASSERT ((LONG)Pfn1->u2.ShareCount >= 1);
4941 
4942 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4943  TopPage = PdePage;
4944 #endif
4945 
4946  //
4947  // Adjust the counts properly for the page directory page.
4948  //
4949 
4950  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PdePage);
4951  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
4952  Pfn1->u1.Event = (PVOID)OutProcess;
4953  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = PdePage;
4954 
4955 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4956  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPteAddress (PXE_BASE);
4957 #elif (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4958  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPteAddress ((PVOID)PDE_TBASE);
4959 #else
4960  Pfn1->PteAddress = MiGetPteAddress (PDE_BASE);
4961 #endif
4962 
4963 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
4964 
4965  //
4966  // Only the extended page directory parent page has really been
4967  // read in above. Read in the page directory parent page now.
4968  //
4969 
4970  PageDirectoryParentMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
4971 
4972  TempPte = PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPxeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
4973 
4974  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParentMap);
4975 
4976  PageDirectoryPage = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
4977  MiGetPxeAddress (MmWorkingSetList),
4978  &TempPte,
4979  0,
4980  PdePage,
4981  OldIrql);
4982 
4983  ASSERT (PageDirectoryPage == TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
4984  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount >= 3);
4985 
4986  PageDirectoryParentMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
4987 
4988  PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPxeOffset(PXE_BASE)].u.Flush =
4989  OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte;
4990  PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPxeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
4991 
4992  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParentMap);
4993 
4994  PdePage = PageDirectoryPage;
4995 
4996 #endif
4997 
4998 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
4999 
5000  //
5001  // Only the page directory parent page has really been read in above
5002  // (and the extended page directory parent for 4-level architectures).
5003  // Read in the page directory page now.
5004  //
5005 
5006  PageDirectoryParentMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5007 
5008  TempPte = PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPpeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
5009 
5010  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParentMap);
5011 
5012  PageDirectoryPage = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
5013  MiGetPpeAddress (MmWorkingSetList),
5014  &TempPte,
5015  0,
5016  PdePage,
5017  OldIrql);
5018 
5019  ASSERT (PageDirectoryPage == TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
5020 
5021  PageDirectoryParentMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5022 
5023 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS==3)
5024  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount >= 3);
5025  PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPpeOffset(PDE_TBASE)].u.Flush =
5026  OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte;
5027 #endif
5028 
5029  PageDirectoryParentMap[MiGetPpeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
5030 
5031  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryParentMap);
5032 
5033  PdePage = PageDirectoryPage;
5034 
5035 #endif
5036 
5037 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
5038 
5039  //
5040  // Locate the additional page directory pages and make them resident.
5041  //
5042 
5043  PaeVa = (PPAE_ENTRY)OutProcess->PaeTop;
5044  ASSERT (PaeVa != &MiSystemPaeVa);
5045 
5046  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5047  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
5048  PageDirectoryPtes[i] = PageDirectoryMap[i];
5049  }
5050  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap);
5051 
5052  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
5053  MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
5054  MiGetPteAddress (PDE_BASE + (i << PAGE_SHIFT)),
5055  &PageDirectoryPtes[i],
5056  0,
5057  PdePage,
5058  OldIrql);
5059  PageDirectoryPtes[i].u.Long &= ~MmPaeMask;
5060  PaeVa->PteEntry[i].u.Long = (PageDirectoryPtes[i].u.Long & ~MM_PAE_PDPTE_MASK);
5061  }
5062 
5063  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5064  for (i = 0; i < PD_PER_SYSTEM - 1; i += 1) {
5065  PageDirectoryMap[i] = PageDirectoryPtes[i];
5066  }
5067  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap);
5068 
5069  TempPte.u.Flush = OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte;
5070  TempPte.u.Long &= ~MM_PAE_PDPTE_MASK;
5071  TempPte.u.Long &= ~MmPaeMask;
5072  PaeVa->PteEntry[i].u.Flush = TempPte.u.Flush;
5073 
5074 #endif
5075 
5076  //
5077  // Locate the page table page for hyperspace and make it resident.
5078  //
5079 
5080  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5081 
5082  TempPte = PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)];
5083 
5084  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap);
5085 
5086  HyperSpacePageTable = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
5087  MiGetPdeAddress (HYPER_SPACE),
5088  &TempPte,
5089  0,
5090  PdePage,
5091  OldIrql);
5092 
5093  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount >= 3);
5094 
5095  PageDirectoryMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, PdePage);
5096 
5097 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS==2)
5098  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(PDE_BASE)].u.Flush =
5099  OutProcess->PageDirectoryPte;
5100 #endif
5101 
5102  PageDirectoryMap[MiGetPdeOffset(MmWorkingSetList)] = TempPte;
5103 
5104  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, PageDirectoryMap);
5105 
5106  //
5107  // Map in the hyper space page table page and retrieve the
5108  // PTEs that map the working set list and VAD bitmap. Note that
5109  // although both PTEs lie in the same page table page, they must
5110  // be retrieved separately because: the Vad PTE may indicate its page
5111  // is in a paging file and the WSL PTE may indicate its PTE is in
5112  // transition. The VAD page inswap may take the WSL page from
5113  // the transition list - CHANGING the WSL PTE ! So the WSL PTE cannot
5114  // be captured until after the VAD inswap completes.
5115  //
5116 
5117  HyperSpacePageTableMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTable);
5118  VadBitMapPteContents = HyperSpacePageTableMap[VadBitMapPteOffset];
5119 
5120  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTableMap);
5121 
5122  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (HyperSpacePageTable);
5123  Pfn1->u1.WsIndex = 1;
5124 
5125  //
5126  // Read in the VAD bitmap page.
5127  //
5128 
5129  VadBitMapPage = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (VadBitMapPte,
5130  &VadBitMapPteContents,
5131  0,
5132  HyperSpacePageTable,
5133  OldIrql);
5134 
5135  //
5136  // Read in the working set list page.
5137  //
5138 
5139  HyperSpacePageTableMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTable);
5140  TempPte = HyperSpacePageTableMap[WorkingSetListPteOffset];
5141  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTableMap);
5142 
5143  WorkingSetPage = MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (WorkingSetListPte,
5144  &TempPte,
5145  0,
5146  HyperSpacePageTable,
5147  OldIrql);
5148 
5149  //
5150  // Update the PTEs, this can be done together for PTEs that lie within
5151  // the same page table page.
5152  //
5153 
5154  HyperSpacePageTableMap = MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTable);
5155  HyperSpacePageTableMap[WorkingSetListPteOffset] = TempPte;
5156 
5157  HyperSpacePageTableMap[VadBitMapPteOffset] = VadBitMapPteContents;
5158 
5159  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, HyperSpacePageTableMap);
5160 
5161  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (WorkingSetPage);
5162  Pfn1->u1.WsIndex = 3;
5163 
5164  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (VadBitMapPage);
5165  Pfn1->u1.WsIndex = 2;
5166 
5167  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5168 
5169  //
5170  // Set up process structures.
5171  //
5172 
5173 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
5174  PdePage = TopPage;
5175 #endif
5176 
5177  OutProcess->WorkingSetPage = WorkingSetPage;
5178 
5179  OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetSize = MM_PROCESS_COMMIT_CHARGE;
5180 
5181 #if !defined (_X86PAE_)
5182 
5183  INITIALIZE_DIRECTORY_TABLE_BASE (&Process->DirectoryTableBase[0],
5184  PdePage);
5185  INITIALIZE_DIRECTORY_TABLE_BASE (&Process->DirectoryTableBase[1],
5186  HyperSpacePageTable);
5187 #else
5188  //
5189  // The DirectoryTableBase[0] never changes for PAE processes.
5190  //
5191 
5192  Process->DirectoryTableBase[1] = HyperSpacePageTable;
5193 #endif
5194 
5195  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
5196 
5197  //
5198  // Allow working set trimming on this process.
5199  //
5200 
5201  if (OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_SWAPPED_OUT) {
5202  InsertTailList (&MmWorkingSetExpansionHead.ListHead,
5203  &OutProcess->Vm.WorkingSetExpansionLinks);
5204  }
5205 
5206  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&OutProcess->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAPPED);
5207 
5208 #if !defined(_WIN64)
5209 
5210  if (OutProcess->PdeUpdateNeeded) {
5211 
5212  //
5213  // Another thread updated the system PDE range while this process
5214  // was outswapped. Update the PDEs now.
5215  //
5216 
5217  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&OutProcess->Flags,
5218  PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
5219 
5220  MiUpdateSystemPdes (OutProcess);
5221  }
5222 
5223 #endif
5224 
5225  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
5226  }
5227 
5228  if (OutProcess->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_IN_SESSION) {
5229  MiSessionInSwapProcess (OutProcess, FALSE);
5230  }
5231 
5232  PS_CLEAR_BITS (&OutProcess->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAP_ENABLED);
5233 
5234  if (PERFINFO_IS_GROUP_ON(PERF_MEMORY)) {
5235  PERFINFO_SWAPPROCESS_INFORMATION PerfInfoSwapProcess;
5236  PerfInfoSwapProcess.ProcessId = HandleToUlong((OutProcess)->UniqueProcessId);
5237  PerfInfoSwapProcess.PageDirectoryBase = MmGetDirectoryFrameFromProcess(OutProcess);
5238  PerfInfoLogBytes (PERFINFO_LOG_TYPE_INSWAPPROCESS,
5239  &PerfInfoSwapProcess,
5240  sizeof(PerfInfoSwapProcess));
5241  }
5242  return;
5243 }
5244 
5245 NTSTATUS
5246 MiCreatePebOrTeb (
5247  IN PEPROCESS TargetProcess,
5248  IN ULONG Size,
5249  OUT PVOID *Base
5250  )
5251 
5252 /*++
5253 
5254 Routine Description:
5255 
5256  This routine creates a TEB or PEB page within the target process.
5257 
5258 Arguments:
5259 
5260  TargetProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process in which to create
5261  the structure.
5262 
5263  Size - Supplies the size of the structure to create a VAD for.
5264 
5265  Base - Supplies a pointer to place the PEB/TEB virtual address on success.
5266  This has no meaning if success is not returned.
5267 
5268 Return Value:
5269 
5270  NTSTATUS.
5271 
5272 Environment:
5273 
5274  Kernel mode, attached to the specified process.
5275 
5276 --*/
5277 
5278 {
5279  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
5280  PETHREAD Thread;
5281  NTSTATUS Status;
5282 
5283  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
5284 
5285  //
5286  // Allocate and initialize the Vad before acquiring the address space
5287  // and working set mutexes so as to minimize mutex hold duration.
5288  //
5289 
5290  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
5291  sizeof(MMVAD_LONG),
5292  'ldaV');
5293 
5294  if (Vad == NULL) {
5295  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
5296  }
5297 
5298  Vad->u.LongFlags = 0;
5299 
5300  Vad->u.VadFlags.CommitCharge = BYTES_TO_PAGES (Size);
5301  Vad->u.VadFlags.MemCommit = 1;
5302  Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory = 1;
5303  Vad->u.VadFlags.Protection = MM_READWRITE;
5304 
5305  //
5306  // Mark VAD as not deletable, no protection change.
5307  //
5308 
5309  Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange = 1;
5310  Vad->u2.LongFlags2 = 0;
5311  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.OneSecured = 1;
5312  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.LongVad = 1;
5313  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.ReadOnly = 0;
5314 
5315  //
5316  // Get the address creation mutex to block multiple threads from
5317  // creating or deleting address space at the same time and
5318  // get the working set mutex so virtual address descriptors can
5319  // be inserted and walked.
5320  //
5321 
5322  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5323 
5324 
5325  //
5326  // Find a VA for the PEB on a page-size boundary.
5327  //
5328 
5329  if (Size == sizeof(PEB)
5330 #if defined(_WIN64)
5331  || (Size == sizeof(PEB32))
5332 #endif
5333  ) {
5334  PVOID HighestVadAddress;
5335 
5336  LARGE_INTEGER CurrentTime;
5337 
5338  HighestVadAddress = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS + 1);
5339 
5340  KeQueryTickCount (&CurrentTime);
5341 
5342  CurrentTime.LowPart &= ((X64K >> PAGE_SHIFT) - 1);
5343  if (CurrentTime.LowPart <= 1) {
5344  CurrentTime.LowPart = 2;
5345  }
5346 
5347  //
5348  // Select a varying PEB address without fragmenting the address space.
5349  //
5350 
5351  HighestVadAddress = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)HighestVadAddress - (CurrentTime.LowPart << PAGE_SHIFT));
5352 
5353  if (MiCheckForConflictingVadExistence (TargetProcess, HighestVadAddress, (PVOID) ((PCHAR) HighestVadAddress + ROUND_TO_PAGES (Size) - 1)) == FALSE) {
5354 
5355  //
5356  // Got an address ...
5357  //
5358 
5359  *Base = HighestVadAddress;
5360  goto AllocatedAddress;
5361  }
5362  }
5363 
5364 
5365  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRangeDown (&TargetProcess->VadRoot,
5366  ROUND_TO_PAGES (Size),
5367  ((PCHAR)MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS + 1),
5368  PAGE_SIZE,
5369  Base);
5370 
5371  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5372 
5373  //
5374  // No range was available, deallocate the Vad and return the status.
5375  //
5376 
5377  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5378  ExFreePool (Vad);
5379  return Status;
5380  }
5381 
5382 AllocatedAddress:
5383 
5384  //
5385  // An unoccupied address range has been found, finish initializing the
5386  // virtual address descriptor to describe this range.
5387  //
5388 
5389  Vad->StartingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (*Base);
5390  Vad->EndingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN ((PCHAR)*Base + Size - 1);
5391 
5392  Vad->u3.Secured.StartVpn = (ULONG_PTR)*Base;
5393  Vad->u3.Secured.EndVpn = (ULONG_PTR)MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn);
5394 
5395  Status = MiInsertVadCharges ((PMMVAD) Vad, TargetProcess);
5396 
5397  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
5398 
5399  //
5400  // A failure has occurred. Deallocate the Vad and return the status.
5401  //
5402 
5403  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5404  ExFreePool (Vad);
5405 
5406  return Status;
5407  }
5408 
5409  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, TargetProcess);
5410 
5411  MiInsertVad ((PMMVAD) Vad, TargetProcess);
5412 
5413  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, TargetProcess);
5414 
5415  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5416 
5417  return Status;
5418 }
5419 
5420 NTSTATUS
5421 MmCreateTeb (
5422  IN PEPROCESS TargetProcess,
5423  IN PINITIAL_TEB InitialTeb,
5424  IN PCLIENT_ID ClientId,
5425  OUT PTEB *Base
5426  )
5427 
5428 /*++
5429 
5430 Routine Description:
5431 
5432  This routine creates a TEB page within the target process
5433  and copies the initial TEB values into it.
5434 
5435 Arguments:
5436 
5437  TargetProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process in which to create
5438  and initialize the TEB.
5439 
5440  InitialTeb - Supplies a pointer to the initial TEB to copy into the
5441  newly created TEB.
5442 
5443  ClientId - Supplies a client ID.
5444 
5445  Base - Supplies a location to return the base of the newly created
5446  TEB on success.
5447 
5448 Return Value:
5449 
5450  NTSTATUS.
5451 
5452 Environment:
5453 
5454  Kernel mode.
5455 
5456 --*/
5457 
5458 {
5459  PTEB TebBase;
5460  NTSTATUS Status;
5461  ULONG TebSize;
5462 #if defined(_WIN64)
5463  PWOW64_PROCESS Wow64Process;
5464  PTEB32 Teb32Base = NULL;
5465  PINITIAL_TEB InitialTeb32Ptr = NULL;
5466  INITIAL_TEB InitialTeb32;
5467 #endif
5468 
5469  //
5470  // Get the size of the TEB
5471  //
5472 
5473  TebSize = sizeof (TEB);
5474 
5475 #if defined(_WIN64)
5476  Wow64Process = TargetProcess->Wow64Process;
5477  if (Wow64Process != NULL) {
5478  TebSize = ROUND_TO_PAGES (sizeof (TEB)) + sizeof (TEB32);
5479 
5480  //
5481  // Capture the 32-bit InitialTeb if the target thread's process is a Wow64 process,
5482  // and the creating the thread is running inside a Wow64 process as well.
5483  //
5484 
5485  if (PsGetCurrentProcess()->Wow64Process != NULL) {
5486 
5487  try {
5488 
5489  InitialTeb32Ptr = Wow64GetInitialTeb32 ();
5490 
5491  if (InitialTeb32Ptr != NULL) {
5492 
5493  ProbeForReadSmallStructure (InitialTeb32Ptr,
5494  sizeof (InitialTeb32),
5495  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (INITIAL_TEB));
5496 
5497  RtlCopyMemory (&InitialTeb32,
5498  InitialTeb32Ptr,
5499  sizeof (InitialTeb32));
5500 
5501  InitialTeb32Ptr = &InitialTeb32;
5502  }
5503  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5504  return GetExceptionCode ();
5505  }
5506  }
5507  }
5508 #endif
5509 
5510  //
5511  // Attach to the specified process.
5512  //
5513 
5514  KeAttachProcess (&TargetProcess->Pcb);
5515 
5516  Status = MiCreatePebOrTeb (TargetProcess, TebSize, (PVOID) &TebBase);
5517 
5518  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5519  KeDetachProcess();
5520  return Status;
5521  }
5522 
5523  //
5524  // Initialize the TEB. Note accesses to the TEB can raise exceptions
5525  // if no address space is available for the TEB or the user has exceeded
5526  // quota (non-paged, pagefile, commit) or the TEB is paged out and an
5527  // inpage error occurs when fetching it.
5528  //
5529 
5530  //
5531  // Note that since the TEB is populated with demand zero pages, only
5532  // nonzero fields need to be initialized here.
5533  //
5534 
5535  try {
5536 
5537 #if !defined(_WIN64)
5538  TebBase->NtTib.ExceptionList = EXCEPTION_CHAIN_END;
5539 #endif
5540 
5541  //
5542  // Although various fields must be zero for the process to launch
5543  // properly, don't assert them as an ordinary user could provoke these
5544  // by maliciously writing over random addresses in another thread,
5545  // hoping to nail a just-being-created TEB.
5546  //
5547 
5548  DONTASSERT (TebBase->NtTib.SubSystemTib == NULL);
5549  TebBase->NtTib.Version = OS2_VERSION;
5550  DONTASSERT (TebBase->NtTib.ArbitraryUserPointer == NULL);
5551  TebBase->NtTib.Self = (PNT_TIB)TebBase;
5552  DONTASSERT (TebBase->EnvironmentPointer == NULL);
5553  TebBase->ProcessEnvironmentBlock = TargetProcess->Peb;
5554  TebBase->ClientId = *ClientId;
5555  TebBase->RealClientId = *ClientId;
5556  DONTASSERT (TebBase->ActivationContextStackPointer == NULL);
5557 
5558  if ((InitialTeb->OldInitialTeb.OldStackBase == NULL) &&
5559  (InitialTeb->OldInitialTeb.OldStackLimit == NULL)) {
5560 
5561  TebBase->NtTib.StackBase = InitialTeb->StackBase;
5562  TebBase->NtTib.StackLimit = InitialTeb->StackLimit;
5563  TebBase->DeallocationStack = InitialTeb->StackAllocationBase;
5564  }
5565  else {
5566  TebBase->NtTib.StackBase = InitialTeb->OldInitialTeb.OldStackBase;
5567  TebBase->NtTib.StackLimit = InitialTeb->OldInitialTeb.OldStackLimit;
5568  }
5569 
5570  TebBase->StaticUnicodeString.Buffer = TebBase->StaticUnicodeBuffer;
5571  TebBase->StaticUnicodeString.MaximumLength = (USHORT) sizeof (TebBase->StaticUnicodeBuffer);
5572  DONTASSERT (TebBase->StaticUnicodeString.Length == 0);
5573 
5574  //
5575  // Used for BBT of ntdll and kernel32.dll.
5576  //
5577 
5578  TebBase->ReservedForPerf = BBTBuffer;
5579 
5580 #if defined(_WIN64)
5581  if (Wow64Process != NULL) {
5582 
5583  Teb32Base = (PTEB32)((PCHAR)TebBase + ROUND_TO_PAGES (sizeof(TEB)));
5584 
5585  Teb32Base->NtTib.ExceptionList = PtrToUlong (EXCEPTION_CHAIN_END);
5586  Teb32Base->NtTib.Version = TebBase->NtTib.Version;
5587  Teb32Base->NtTib.Self = PtrToUlong (Teb32Base);
5588  Teb32Base->ProcessEnvironmentBlock = PtrToUlong (Wow64Process->Wow64);
5589  Teb32Base->ClientId.UniqueProcess = PtrToUlong (TebBase->ClientId.UniqueProcess);
5590  Teb32Base->ClientId.UniqueThread = PtrToUlong (TebBase->ClientId.UniqueThread);
5591  Teb32Base->RealClientId.UniqueProcess = PtrToUlong (TebBase->RealClientId.UniqueProcess);
5592  Teb32Base->RealClientId.UniqueThread = PtrToUlong (TebBase->RealClientId.UniqueThread);
5593  Teb32Base->StaticUnicodeString.Buffer = PtrToUlong (Teb32Base->StaticUnicodeBuffer);
5594  Teb32Base->StaticUnicodeString.MaximumLength = (USHORT)sizeof (Teb32Base->StaticUnicodeBuffer);
5595  ASSERT (Teb32Base->StaticUnicodeString.Length == 0);
5596  Teb32Base->GdiBatchCount = PtrToUlong (TebBase);
5597  Teb32Base->Vdm = PtrToUlong (TebBase->Vdm);
5598  ASSERT (Teb32Base->ActivationContextStackPointer == 0);
5599 
5600  if (InitialTeb32Ptr != NULL) {
5601  Teb32Base->NtTib.StackBase = PtrToUlong (InitialTeb32Ptr->StackBase);
5602  Teb32Base->NtTib.StackLimit = PtrToUlong (InitialTeb32Ptr->StackLimit);
5603  Teb32Base->DeallocationStack = PtrToUlong (InitialTeb32Ptr->StackAllocationBase);
5604  }
5605  }
5606 
5607  TebBase->NtTib.ExceptionList = (PVOID)Teb32Base;
5608 #endif
5609 
5610  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5611 
5612  //
5613  // An exception has occurred, inform our caller.
5614  //
5615 
5616  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
5617  }
5618 
5619  KeDetachProcess();
5620  *Base = TebBase;
5621 
5622  return Status;
5623 }
5624 
5625 //
5626 // This code is built twice on the Win64 build - once for PE32+
5627 // and once for PE32 images.
5628 //
5629 
5630 #define MI_INIT_PEB_FROM_IMAGE(Hdrs, ImgConfig) { \
5631  PebBase->ImageSubsystem = (Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Subsystem; \
5632  PebBase->ImageSubsystemMajorVersion = \
5633  (Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.MajorSubsystemVersion; \
5634  PebBase->ImageSubsystemMinorVersion = \
5635  (Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.MinorSubsystemVersion; \
5636  \
5637  /* */ \
5638  /* See if this image wants GetVersion to lie about who the system is */ \
5639  /* If so, capture the lie into the PEB for the process. */ \
5640  /* */ \
5641  \
5642  if ((Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Win32VersionValue != 0) { \
5643  PebBase->OSMajorVersion = \
5644  (Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Win32VersionValue & 0xFF; \
5645  PebBase->OSMinorVersion = \
5646  ((Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Win32VersionValue >> 8) & 0xFF; \
5647  PebBase->OSBuildNumber = \
5648  (USHORT)(((Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Win32VersionValue >> 16) & 0x3FFF); \
5649  if ((ImgConfig) != NULL && (ImgConfig)->CSDVersion != 0) { \
5650  PebBase->OSCSDVersion = (ImgConfig)->CSDVersion; \
5651  } \
5652  \
5653  /* Win32 API GetVersion returns the following bogus bit definitions */ \
5654  /* in the high two bits: */ \
5655  /* */ \
5656  /* 00 - Windows NT */ \
5657  /* 01 - reserved */ \
5658  /* 10 - Win32s running on Windows 3.x */ \
5659  /* 11 - Windows 95 */ \
5660  /* */ \
5661  /* */ \
5662  /* Win32 API GetVersionEx returns a dwPlatformId with the following */ \
5663  /* values defined in winbase.h */ \
5664  /* */ \
5665  /* 00 - VER_PLATFORM_WIN32s */ \
5666  /* 01 - VER_PLATFORM_WIN32_WINDOWS */ \
5667  /* 10 - VER_PLATFORM_WIN32_NT */ \
5668  /* 11 - reserved */ \
5669  /* */ \
5670  /* */ \
5671  /* So convert the former from the Win32VersionValue field into the */ \
5672  /* OSPlatformId field. This is done by XORing with 0x2. The */ \
5673  /* translation is symmetric so there is the same code to do the */ \
5674  /* reverse in windows\base\client\module.c (GetVersion) */ \
5675  /* */ \
5676  PebBase->OSPlatformId = \
5677  ((Hdrs)->OptionalHeader.Win32VersionValue >> 30) ^ 0x2; \
5678  } \
5679  }
5680 
5681 
5682 #if defined(_WIN64)
5683 NTSTATUS
5684 MiInitializeWowPeb (
5685  IN PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders,
5686  IN PPEB PebBase,
5687  IN PEPROCESS TargetProcess
5688  )
5689 
5690 /*++
5691 
5692 Routine Description:
5693 
5694  This routine creates a PEB32 page within the target process
5695  and copies the initial PEB32 values into it.
5696 
5697 Arguments:
5698 
5699  NtHeaders - Supplies a pointer to the NT headers for the image.
5700 
5701  PebBase - Supplies a pointer to the initial PEB to derive the PEB32 values
5702  from.
5703 
5704  TargetProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process in which to create
5705  and initialize the PEB32.
5706 
5707 Return Value:
5708 
5709  NTSTATUS.
5710 
5711 Environment:
5712 
5713  Kernel mode.
5714 
5715 --*/
5716 
5717 {
5718  PMMVAD Vad;
5719  NTSTATUS Status;
5720  ULONG ReturnedSize;
5721  PPEB32 PebBase32;
5722  ULONG ProcessAffinityMask;
5723  PVOID ImageBase;
5724  BOOLEAN MappedAsImage;
5725  PSUBSECTION Subsection;
5726  PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea;
5727  PIMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY32 ImageConfigData32;
5728 
5729  ProcessAffinityMask = 0;
5730  ImageConfigData32 = NULL;
5731  MappedAsImage = FALSE;
5732 
5733  //
5734  // All references to the Peb and NtHeaders must be wrapped in try-except
5735  // in case the user has exceeded quota (non-paged, pagefile, commit)
5736  // or any inpage errors happen for the user addresses, etc.
5737  //
5738 
5739  try {
5740 
5741  ImageBase = PebBase->ImageBaseAddress;
5742 
5743  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5744  return STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
5745  }
5746 
5747  //
5748  // Inspect the address space to determine if the executable image is
5749  // mapped with a single copy on write subsection (ie: as data) or if
5750  // the alignment was such that it was mapped as a full image section.
5751  //
5752 
5753  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5754 
5755  ASSERT ((TargetProcess->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) == 0);
5756 
5757  Vad = MiCheckForConflictingVad (TargetProcess, ImageBase, ImageBase);
5758 
5759  if (Vad == NULL) {
5760 
5761  //
5762  // No virtual address is reserved at the specified base address,
5763  // return an error.
5764  //
5765 
5766  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5767  return STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
5768  }
5769 
5770  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory == 0) {
5771 
5772  ControlArea = Vad->ControlArea;
5773 
5774  if ((ControlArea->u.Flags.Image == 1) &&
5775  (ControlArea->Segment->SegmentFlags.ExtraSharedWowSubsections == 0)) {
5776 
5777  if ((ControlArea->u.Flags.GlobalOnlyPerSession == 0) &&
5778  (ControlArea->u.Flags.Rom == 0)) {
5779 
5780  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION) (ControlArea + 1);
5781  }
5782  else {
5783  Subsection = (PSUBSECTION) ((PLARGE_CONTROL_AREA)ControlArea + 1);
5784  }
5785 
5786  //
5787  // Real images always have a subsection for the PE header and then
5788  // at least one other subsection for the other sections in the
5789  // image.
5790  //
5791 
5792  if (Subsection->NextSubsection != NULL) {
5793  MappedAsImage = TRUE;
5794  }
5795  }
5796  }
5797 
5798  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
5799 
5800  try {
5801 
5802  ImageConfigData32 = RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
5803  PebBase->ImageBaseAddress,
5804  MappedAsImage,
5805  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG,
5806  &ReturnedSize);
5807 
5808  if (ImageConfigData32 != NULL) {
