5809  ProbeForReadSmallStructure ((PVOID)ImageConfigData32,
5810  sizeof (*ImageConfigData32),
5811  sizeof (ULONG));
5812  }
5813 
5814  MI_INIT_PEB_FROM_IMAGE ((PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS32)NtHeaders,
5815  ImageConfigData32);
5816 
5817  if ((ImageConfigData32 != NULL) &&
5818  (ImageConfigData32->ProcessAffinityMask != 0)) {
5819 
5820  ProcessAffinityMask = ImageConfigData32->ProcessAffinityMask;
5821  }
5822 
5823  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5824  return STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
5825  }
5826 
5827  //
5828  // Create a PEB32 for the process.
5829  //
5830 
5831  Status = MiCreatePebOrTeb (TargetProcess,
5832  (ULONG)sizeof (PEB32),
5833  (PVOID)&PebBase32);
5834 
5835  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
5836  return Status;
5837  }
5838 
5839  //
5840  // Mark the process as WOW64 by storing the 32-bit PEB pointer
5841  // in the Wow64 field.
5842  //
5843 
5844  TargetProcess->Wow64Process->Wow64 = PebBase32;
5845 
5846  //
5847  // Clone the PEB into the PEB32.
5848  //
5849 
5850  try {
5851  PebBase32->InheritedAddressSpace = PebBase->InheritedAddressSpace;
5852  PebBase32->ImageUsesLargePages = PebBase->ImageUsesLargePages;
5853  PebBase32->Mutant = PtrToUlong(PebBase->Mutant);
5854  PebBase32->ImageBaseAddress = PtrToUlong(PebBase->ImageBaseAddress);
5855  PebBase32->AnsiCodePageData = PtrToUlong(PebBase->AnsiCodePageData);
5856  PebBase32->OemCodePageData = PtrToUlong(PebBase->OemCodePageData);
5857  PebBase32->UnicodeCaseTableData = PtrToUlong(PebBase->UnicodeCaseTableData);
5858  PebBase32->NumberOfProcessors = PebBase->NumberOfProcessors;
5859  PebBase32->BeingDebugged = PebBase->BeingDebugged;
5860  PebBase32->NtGlobalFlag = PebBase->NtGlobalFlag;
5861  PebBase32->CriticalSectionTimeout = PebBase->CriticalSectionTimeout;
5862 
5863  if (PebBase->HeapSegmentReserve > 1024*1024*1024) { // 1GB
5864  PebBase32->HeapSegmentReserve = 1024*1024; // 1MB
5865  }
5866  else {
5867  PebBase32->HeapSegmentReserve = (ULONG)PebBase->HeapSegmentReserve;
5868  }
5869 
5870  if (PebBase->HeapSegmentCommit > PebBase32->HeapSegmentReserve) {
5871  PebBase32->HeapSegmentCommit = 2*PAGE_SIZE;
5872  }
5873  else {
5874  PebBase32->HeapSegmentCommit = (ULONG)PebBase->HeapSegmentCommit;
5875  }
5876 
5877  PebBase32->HeapDeCommitTotalFreeThreshold = (ULONG)PebBase->HeapDeCommitTotalFreeThreshold;
5878  PebBase32->HeapDeCommitFreeBlockThreshold = (ULONG)PebBase->HeapDeCommitFreeBlockThreshold;
5879  PebBase32->NumberOfHeaps = PebBase->NumberOfHeaps;
5880  PebBase32->MaximumNumberOfHeaps = (PAGE_SIZE - sizeof(PEB32)) / sizeof(ULONG);
5881  PebBase32->ProcessHeaps = PtrToUlong(PebBase32+1);
5882  PebBase32->OSMajorVersion = PebBase->OSMajorVersion;
5883  PebBase32->OSMinorVersion = PebBase->OSMinorVersion;
5884  PebBase32->OSBuildNumber = PebBase->OSBuildNumber;
5885  PebBase32->OSPlatformId = PebBase->OSPlatformId;
5886  PebBase32->OSCSDVersion = PebBase->OSCSDVersion;
5887  PebBase32->ImageSubsystem = PebBase->ImageSubsystem;
5888  PebBase32->ImageSubsystemMajorVersion = PebBase->ImageSubsystemMajorVersion;
5889  PebBase32->ImageSubsystemMinorVersion = PebBase->ImageSubsystemMinorVersion;
5890  PebBase32->SessionId = MmGetSessionId (TargetProcess);
5891  DONTASSERT (PebBase32->pShimData == 0);
5892  DONTASSERT (PebBase32->AppCompatFlags.QuadPart == 0);
5893 
5894  //
5895  // Leave the AffinityMask in the 32bit PEB as zero and let the
5896  // 64bit NTDLL set the initial mask. This is to allow the
5897  // round robin scheduling of non MP safe imaging in the
5898  // caller to work correctly.
5899  //
5900  // Later code will set the affinity mask in the PEB32 if the
5901  // image actually specifies one.
5902  //
5903  // Note that the AffinityMask in the PEB is simply a mechanism
5904  // to pass affinity information from the image to the loader.
5905  //
5906  // Pass the affinity mask up to the 32 bit NTDLL via
5907  // the PEB32. The 32 bit NTDLL will determine that the
5908  // affinity is not zero and try to set the affinity
5909  // mask from user-mode. This call will be intercepted
5910  // by the wow64 thunks which will convert it
5911  // into a 64bit affinity mask and call the kernel.
5912  //
5913 
5914  PebBase32->ImageProcessAffinityMask = ProcessAffinityMask;
5915 
5916  DONTASSERT (PebBase32->ActivationContextData == 0);
5917  DONTASSERT (PebBase32->SystemDefaultActivationContextData == 0);
5918 
5919  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
5920  Status = GetExceptionCode ();
5921  }
5922  return Status;
5923 }
5924 #endif
5925 
5926 
5927 NTSTATUS
5928 MmCreatePeb (
5929  IN PEPROCESS TargetProcess,
5930  IN PINITIAL_PEB InitialPeb,
5931  OUT PPEB *Base
5932  )
5933 
5934 /*++
5935 
5936 Routine Description:
5937 
5938  This routine creates a PEB page within the target process
5939  and copies the initial PEB values into it.
5940 
5941 Arguments:
5942 
5943  TargetProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process in which to create
5944  and initialize the PEB.
5945 
5946  InitialPeb - Supplies a pointer to the initial PEB to copy into the
5947  newly created PEB.
5948 
5949  Base - Supplies a location to return the base of the newly created
5950  PEB on success.
5951 
5952 Return Value:
5953 
5954  NTSTATUS.
5955 
5956 Environment:
5957 
5958  Kernel mode.
5959 
5960 --*/
5961 
5962 {
5963  PPEB PebBase;
5964  USHORT Magic;
5965  USHORT Characteristics;
5966  NTSTATUS Status;
5967  PVOID ViewBase;
5968  LARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset;
5969  PIMAGE_NT_HEADERS NtHeaders;
5970  SIZE_T ViewSize;
5971  ULONG ReturnedSize;
5972  PIMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY ImageConfigData;
5973  ULONG_PTR ProcessAffinityMask;
5974 
5975  ViewBase = NULL;
5976  SectionOffset.LowPart = 0;
5977  SectionOffset.HighPart = 0;
5978  ViewSize = 0;
5979 
5980  //
5981  // Attach to the specified process.
5982  //
5983 
5984  KeAttachProcess (&TargetProcess->Pcb);
5985 
5986  //
5987  // Map the NLS tables into the application's address space.
5988  //
5989 
5990  Status = MmMapViewOfSection (InitNlsSectionPointer,
5991  TargetProcess,
5992  &ViewBase,
5993  0L,
5994  0L,
5995  &SectionOffset,
5996  &ViewSize,
5997  ViewShare,
5998  MEM_TOP_DOWN | SEC_NO_CHANGE,
5999  PAGE_READONLY);
6000 
6001  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
6002  KeDetachProcess ();
6003  return Status;
6004  }
6005 
6006  Status = MiCreatePebOrTeb (TargetProcess, sizeof(PEB), (PVOID)&PebBase);
6007 
6008  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
6009  KeDetachProcess ();
6010  return Status;
6011  }
6012 
6013  //
6014  // Initialize the Peb. Every reference to the Peb
6015  // must be wrapped in try-except in case the inpage fails. The inpage
6016  // can fail for any reason including network failures, disk errors,
6017  // low resources, etc.
6018  //
6019 
6020  try {
6021  PebBase->InheritedAddressSpace = InitialPeb->InheritedAddressSpace;
6022  PebBase->ImageUsesLargePages = InitialPeb->ImageUsesLargePages;
6023  PebBase->Mutant = InitialPeb->Mutant;
6024  PebBase->ImageBaseAddress = TargetProcess->SectionBaseAddress;
6025 
6026  PebBase->AnsiCodePageData = (PVOID)((PUCHAR)ViewBase+InitAnsiCodePageDataOffset);
6027  PebBase->OemCodePageData = (PVOID)((PUCHAR)ViewBase+InitOemCodePageDataOffset);
6028  PebBase->UnicodeCaseTableData = (PVOID)((PUCHAR)ViewBase+InitUnicodeCaseTableDataOffset);
6029 
6030  PebBase->NumberOfProcessors = KeNumberProcessors;
6031  PebBase->BeingDebugged = (BOOLEAN)(TargetProcess->DebugPort != NULL ? TRUE : FALSE);
6032  PebBase->NtGlobalFlag = NtGlobalFlag;
6033  PebBase->CriticalSectionTimeout = MmCriticalSectionTimeout;
6034  PebBase->HeapSegmentReserve = MmHeapSegmentReserve;
6035  PebBase->HeapSegmentCommit = MmHeapSegmentCommit;
6036  PebBase->HeapDeCommitTotalFreeThreshold = MmHeapDeCommitTotalFreeThreshold;
6037  PebBase->HeapDeCommitFreeBlockThreshold = MmHeapDeCommitFreeBlockThreshold;
6038  DONTASSERT (PebBase->NumberOfHeaps == 0);
6039  PebBase->MaximumNumberOfHeaps = (PAGE_SIZE - sizeof (PEB)) / sizeof( PVOID);
6040  PebBase->ProcessHeaps = (PVOID *)(PebBase+1);
6041 
6042  PebBase->OSMajorVersion = NtMajorVersion;
6043  PebBase->OSMinorVersion = NtMinorVersion;
6044  PebBase->OSBuildNumber = (USHORT)(NtBuildNumber & 0x3FFF);
6045  PebBase->OSPlatformId = 2; // VER_PLATFORM_WIN32_NT from winbase.h
6046  PebBase->OSCSDVersion = (USHORT)CmNtCSDVersion;
6047  DONTASSERT (PebBase->pShimData == 0);
6048  DONTASSERT (PebBase->AppCompatFlags.QuadPart == 0);
6049  DONTASSERT (PebBase->ActivationContextData == NULL);
6050  DONTASSERT (PebBase->SystemDefaultActivationContextData == NULL);
6051 
6052  if (TargetProcess->Session != NULL) {
6053  PebBase->SessionId = MmGetSessionId (TargetProcess);
6054  }
6055 
6056  PebBase->MinimumStackCommit = (SIZE_T)MmMinimumStackCommitInBytes;
6057 
6058  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6059  KeDetachProcess();
6060  return GetExceptionCode ();
6061  }
6062 
6063  //
6064  // Every reference to NtHeaders (including the call to RtlImageNtHeader)
6065  // must be wrapped in try-except in case the inpage fails. The inpage
6066  // can fail for any reason including network failures, disk errors,
6067  // low resources, etc.
6068  //
6069 
6070  try {
6071  NtHeaders = RtlImageNtHeader (PebBase->ImageBaseAddress);
6072  Magic = NtHeaders->OptionalHeader.Magic;
6073  Characteristics = NtHeaders->FileHeader.Characteristics;
6074  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6075  KeDetachProcess();
6076  return STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
6077  }
6078 
6079  if (NtHeaders != NULL) {
6080 
6081  ProcessAffinityMask = 0;
6082 
6083 #if defined(_WIN64)
6084 
6085  if (TargetProcess->Wow64Process) {
6086 
6087  Status = MiInitializeWowPeb (NtHeaders, PebBase, TargetProcess);
6088 
6089  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
6090  KeDetachProcess ();
6091  return Status;
6092  }
6093  }
6094  else // a PE32+ image
6095 #endif
6096  {
6097  try {
6098  ImageConfigData = RtlImageDirectoryEntryToData (
6099  PebBase->ImageBaseAddress,
6100  TRUE,
6101  IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG,
6102  &ReturnedSize);
6103 
6104  if (ImageConfigData != NULL) {
6105  ProbeForReadSmallStructure ((PVOID)ImageConfigData,
6106  sizeof (*ImageConfigData),
6107  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (IMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY));
6108  }
6109 
6110  MI_INIT_PEB_FROM_IMAGE(NtHeaders, ImageConfigData);
6111 
6112  if (ImageConfigData != NULL && ImageConfigData->ProcessAffinityMask != 0) {
6113  ProcessAffinityMask = ImageConfigData->ProcessAffinityMask;
6114  }
6115 
6116  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6117  KeDetachProcess();
6118  return STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
6119  }
6120 
6121  }
6122 
6123  //
6124  // Note NT4 examined the NtHeaders->FileHeader.Characteristics
6125  // for the IMAGE_FILE_AGGRESIVE_WS_TRIM bit, but this is not needed
6126  // or used for NT5 and above.
6127  //
6128 
6129  //
6130  // See if image wants to override the default processor affinity mask.
6131  //
6132 
6133  try {
6134 
6135  if (Characteristics & IMAGE_FILE_UP_SYSTEM_ONLY) {
6136 
6137  //
6138  // Image is NOT MP safe. Assign it a processor on a rotating
6139  // basis to spread these processes around on MP systems.
6140  //
6141 
6142  do {
6143  PebBase->ImageProcessAffinityMask = ((KAFFINITY)0x1 << MmRotatingUniprocessorNumber);
6144  if (++MmRotatingUniprocessorNumber >= KeNumberProcessors) {
6145  MmRotatingUniprocessorNumber = 0;
6146  }
6147  } while ((PebBase->ImageProcessAffinityMask & KeActiveProcessors) == 0);
6148  }
6149  else {
6150 
6151  if (ProcessAffinityMask != 0) {
6152 
6153  //
6154  // Pass the affinity mask from the image header
6155  // to LdrpInitializeProcess via the PEB.
6156  //
6157 
6158  PebBase->ImageProcessAffinityMask = ProcessAffinityMask;
6159  }
6160  }
6161  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
6162  KeDetachProcess();
6163  return STATUS_INVALID_IMAGE_PROTECT;
6164  }
6165  }
6166 
6167  KeDetachProcess();
6168 
6169  *Base = PebBase;
6170 
6171  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
6172 }
6173 
6174 VOID
6175 MmDeleteTeb (
6176  IN PEPROCESS TargetProcess,
6177  IN PVOID TebBase
6178  )
6179 
6180 /*++
6181 
6182 Routine Description:
6183 
6184  This routine deletes a TEB page within the target process.
6185 
6186 Arguments:
6187 
6188  TargetProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process in which to delete
6189  the TEB.
6190 
6191  TebBase - Supplies the base address of the TEB to delete.
6192 
6193 Return Value:
6194 
6195  None.
6196 
6197 Environment:
6198 
6199  Kernel mode.
6200 
6201 --*/
6202 
6203 {
6204  PVOID EndingAddress;
6205  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
6206  PETHREAD Thread;
6207  NTSTATUS Status;
6208  PMMSECURE_ENTRY Secure;
6209  PMMVAD PreviousVad;
6210  PMMVAD NextVad;
6211 
6212  EndingAddress = ((PCHAR)TebBase +
6213  ROUND_TO_PAGES (sizeof(TEB)) - 1);
6214 
6215 #if defined(_WIN64)
6216  if (TargetProcess->Wow64Process) {
6217  EndingAddress = ((PCHAR)EndingAddress + ROUND_TO_PAGES (sizeof(TEB32)));
6218  }
6219 #endif
6220 
6221  //
6222  // Attach to the specified process.
6223  //
6224 
6225  KeAttachProcess (&TargetProcess->Pcb);
6226 
6227  //
6228  // Get the address creation mutex to block multiple threads from
6229  // creating or deleting address space at the same time and
6230  // get the working set mutex so virtual address descriptors can
6231  // be inserted and walked.
6232  //
6233 
6234  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
6235 
6236  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG) MiLocateAddress (TebBase);
6237 
6238  ASSERT (Vad != NULL);
6239 
6240  ASSERT ((Vad->StartingVpn == MI_VA_TO_VPN (TebBase)) &&
6241  (Vad->EndingVpn == MI_VA_TO_VPN (EndingAddress)));
6242 
6243  //
6244  // If someone has secured the TEB (in addition to the standard securing
6245  // that was done by memory management on creation, then don't delete it
6246  // now - just leave it around until the entire process is deleted.
6247  //
6248 
6249  ASSERT (Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange == 1);
6250  if (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.OneSecured) {
6251  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
6252  }
6253  else {
6254  ASSERT (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.MultipleSecured);
6255  ASSERT (IsListEmpty (&Vad->u3.List) == 0);
6256 
6257  //
6258  // If there's only one entry, then that's the one we defined when we
6259  // initially created the TEB. So TEB deletion can take place right
6260  // now. If there's more than one entry, let the TEB sit around until
6261  // the process goes away.
6262  //
6263 
6264  Secure = CONTAINING_RECORD (Vad->u3.List.Flink,
6265  MMSECURE_ENTRY,
6266  List);
6267 
6268  if (Secure->List.Flink == &Vad->u3.List) {
6269  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
6270  }
6271  else {
6272  Status = STATUS_NOT_FOUND;
6273  }
6274  }
6275 
6276  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
6277 
6278  PreviousVad = MiGetPreviousVad (Vad);
6279  NextVad = MiGetNextVad (Vad);
6280 
6281  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
6282 
6283  MiRemoveVadCharges ((PMMVAD)Vad, TargetProcess);
6284 
6285  //
6286  // Return commitment for page table pages and clear VAD bitmaps
6287  // if possible.
6288  //
6289 
6290  MiReturnPageTablePageCommitment (TebBase,
6291  EndingAddress,
6292  TargetProcess,
6293  PreviousVad,
6294  NextVad);
6295 
6296  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, TargetProcess);
6297 
6298  MiRemoveVad ((PMMVAD)Vad, TargetProcess);
6299 
6300  MiDeleteVirtualAddresses (TebBase, EndingAddress, NULL);
6301 
6302  UNLOCK_WS_AND_ADDRESS_SPACE (Thread, TargetProcess);
6303 
6304  ExFreePool (Vad);
6305  }
6306  else {
6307  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (TargetProcess);
6308  }
6309 
6310  KeDetachProcess();
6311 }
6312 
6313 VOID
6314 MiAllowWorkingSetExpansion (
6315  IN PMMSUPPORT WsInfo
6316  )
6317 
6318 /*++
6319 
6320 Routine Description:
6321 
6322  This routine inserts the working set into the list scanned by the trimmer.
6323 
6324 Arguments:
6325 
6326  WsInfo - Supplies the working set to insert.
6327 
6328 Return Value:
6329 
6330  None.
6331 
6332 Environment:
6333 
6334  Kernel mode.
6335 
6336 --*/
6337 
6338 {
6339  KIRQL OldIrql;
6340 
6341  ASSERT (WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Flink == MM_WS_NOT_LISTED);
6342  ASSERT (WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks.Blink == MM_WS_NOT_LISTED);
6343 
6344  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
6345 
6346  InsertTailList (&MmWorkingSetExpansionHead.ListHead,
6347  &WsInfo->WorkingSetExpansionLinks);
6348 
6349  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
6350 
6351  return;
6352 }
6353 
6354 #if DBG
6355 ULONG MiDeleteLocked;
6356 #endif
6357 
6358 
6359 VOID
6360 MiDeleteAddressesInWorkingSet (
6361  IN PEPROCESS Process
6362  )
6363 
6364 /*++
6365 
6366 Routine Description:
6367 
6368  This routine deletes all user mode addresses from the working set list.
6369 
6370 Arguments:
6371 
6372  Process - Supplies a pointer to the current process.
6373 
6374 Return Value:
6375 
6376  None.
6377 
6378 Environment:
6379 
6380  Kernel mode, Working Set Lock held.
6381 
6382 --*/
6383 
6384 {
6385  PMMWSLE Wsle;
6386  WSLE_NUMBER index;
6387  WSLE_NUMBER Entry;
6388  PVOID Va;
6389  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6390  MMPTE_DELETE_LIST PteDeleteList;
6391 #if DBG
6392  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6393  PVOID SwapVa;
6394  PMMWSLE LastWsle;
6395 #endif
6396 
6397  //
6398  // Go through the working set and for any user-accessible page which is
6399  // in it, rip it out of the working set and free the page.
6400  //
6401 
6402  index = 2;
6403  Wsle = &MmWsle[index];
6404  PteDeleteList.Count = 0;
6405 
6406  MmWorkingSetList->HashTable = NULL;
6407 
6408  //
6409  // Go through the working set list and remove all pages for user
6410  // space addresses.
6411  //
6412 
6413  for ( ; index <= MmWorkingSetList->LastEntry; index += 1, Wsle += 1) {
6414 
6415  if (Wsle->u1.e1.Valid == 0) {
6416  continue;
6417  }
6418 
6419  Va = Wsle->u1.VirtualAddress;
6420 
6421 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
6422  ASSERT (MiGetPxeAddress(Va)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6423 #endif
6424 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
6425  ASSERT (MiGetPpeAddress(Va)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6426 #endif
6427  ASSERT (MiGetPdeAddress(Va)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6428  ASSERT (MiGetPteAddress(Va)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6429 
6430  if (Va >= (PVOID)MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
6431  continue;
6432  }
6433 
6434  //
6435  // Ensure the WSLE and the PTE are both valid so that any
6436  // conflict between them can be resolved before both are deleted.
6437  //
6438 
6439  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (Va);
6440 
6441  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6442  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
6443  0x3452,
6444  (ULONG_PTR) Va,
6445  (ULONG_PTR) Wsle,
6446  (ULONG_PTR) PointerPte->u.Long);
6447  }
6448 
6449  //
6450  // This is a user mode address, for each one we remove we must
6451  // maintain the NonDirectCount. This is because we may fault
6452  // later for page tables and need to grow the hash table when
6453  // updating the working set. NonDirectCount needs to be correct
6454  // at that point.
6455  //
6456 
6457  if (Wsle->u1.e1.Direct == 0) {
6458  Process->Vm.VmWorkingSetList->NonDirectCount -= 1;
6459  }
6460 
6461  //
6462  // This entry is in the working set list.
6463  //
6464 
6465  MiReleaseWsle (index, &Process->Vm);
6466 
6467  if (index < MmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic) {
6468 
6469  //
6470  // This entry is locked.
6471  //
6472 
6473  MmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic -= 1;
6474 
6475  if (index != MmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic) {
6476 
6477  Entry = MmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic;
6478 #if DBG
6479  MiDeleteLocked += 1;
6480  SwapVa = MmWsle[MmWorkingSetList->FirstDynamic].u1.VirtualAddress;
6481  SwapVa = PAGE_ALIGN (SwapVa);
6482 
6483  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MiGetPteAddress (SwapVa)->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
6484 
6485  ASSERT (Entry == MiLocateWsle (SwapVa, MmWorkingSetList, Pfn1->u1.WsIndex, FALSE));
6486 #endif
6487  MiSwapWslEntries (Entry, index, &Process->Vm, FALSE);
6488 
6489  //
6490  // We may have reused the WSLE we just deleted to hold a valid
6491  // entry as a result of the swap, so make sure we check it
6492  // again.
6493  //
6494 
6495  index -= 1;
6496  Wsle -= 1;
6497  }
6498  }
6499 
6500  PteDeleteList.PointerPte[PteDeleteList.Count] = PointerPte;
6501  PteDeleteList.PteContents[PteDeleteList.Count] = *PointerPte;
6502  PteDeleteList.Count += 1;
6503 
6504  if (PteDeleteList.Count == MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6505  MiDeletePteList (&PteDeleteList, Process);
6506  PteDeleteList.Count = 0;
6507  }
6508  }
6509 
6510  if (PteDeleteList.Count != 0) {
6511  MiDeletePteList (&PteDeleteList, Process);
6512  }
6513 
6514 #if DBG
6515  Wsle = &MmWsle[2];
6516  LastWsle = &MmWsle[MmWorkingSetList->LastInitializedWsle];
6517  while (Wsle <= LastWsle) {
6518  if (Wsle->u1.e1.Valid == 1) {
6519 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
6520  ASSERT(MiGetPxeAddress(Wsle->u1.VirtualAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6521 #endif
6522 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
6523  ASSERT(MiGetPpeAddress(Wsle->u1.VirtualAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6524 #endif
6525  ASSERT(MiGetPdeAddress(Wsle->u1.VirtualAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6526  ASSERT(MiGetPteAddress(Wsle->u1.VirtualAddress)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6527  }
6528  Wsle += 1;
6529  }
6530 #endif
6531 }
6532 
6533 
6534 VOID
6535 MiDeletePteList (
6536  IN PMMPTE_DELETE_LIST PteDeleteList,
6537  IN PEPROCESS CurrentProcess
6538  )
6539 
6540 /*++
6541 
6542 Routine Description:
6543 
6544  This routine deletes the specified virtual address.
6545 
6546 Arguments:
6547 
6548  PteDeleteList - Supplies the list of PTEs to delete.
6549 
6550  CurrentProcess - Supplies the current process.
6551 
6552 Return Value:
6553 
6554  None.
6555 
6556 Environment:
6557 
6558  Kernel mode. Working set mutex held.
6559 
6560  Note since this is only called during process teardown, the write watch
6561  bits are not updated. If this ever called from other places, code
6562  will need to be added here to update those bits.
6563 
6564 --*/
6565 
6566 {
6567  ULONG i;
6568  ULONG j;
6569  PMMPTE PointerPde;
6570  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6571  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6572  PMMPFN Pfn2;
6573  KIRQL OldIrql;
6574  PMMCLONE_BLOCK CloneBlock;
6575  PMMCLONE_DESCRIPTOR CloneDescriptor;
6576  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6577  PFN_NUMBER PageTableFrameIndex;
6578  MMPTE DemandZeroWritePte;
6579  MMPTE_FLUSH_LIST PteFlushList;
6580 
6581  j = 0;
6582  PteFlushList.Count = 0;
6583  DemandZeroWritePte.u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
6584 
6585  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6586 
6587  for (i = 0; i < PteDeleteList->Count; i += 1) {
6588 
6589  PointerPte = PteDeleteList->PointerPte[i];
6590 
6591  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6592 
6593  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
6594  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6595 
6596  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 1) {
6597 
6598  CloneBlock = (PMMCLONE_BLOCK) Pfn1->PteAddress;
6599 
6600  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
6601 
6602  PageTableFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde);
6603  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
6604 
6605  //
6606  // Capture the state of the modified bit for this PTE.
6607  //
6608 
6609  MI_CAPTURE_DIRTY_BIT_TO_PFN (PointerPte, Pfn1);
6610 
6611  //
6612  // Decrement the share and valid counts of the page table
6613  // page which maps this PTE.
6614  //
6615 
6616  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
6617 
6618  //
6619  // Decrement the share count for the physical page.
6620  //
6621 
6622  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
6623 
6624  //
6625  // Set the pointer to PTE to be a demand zero PTE. This allows
6626  // the page usage count to be kept properly and handles the case
6627  // when a page table page has only valid PTEs and needs to be
6628  // deleted later when the VADs are removed.
6629  //
6630 
6631  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, DemandZeroWritePte);
6632 
6633  //
6634  // Check to see if this is a fork prototype PTE and if so
6635  // update the clone descriptor address.
6636  //
6637 
6638  ASSERT (MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte) <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS);
6639 
6640  //
6641  // Locate the clone descriptor within the clone tree.
6642  //
6643 
6644  CloneDescriptor = MiLocateCloneAddress (CurrentProcess, (PVOID)CloneBlock);
6645  if (CloneDescriptor != NULL) {
6646 
6647  //
6648  // Decrement the reference count for the clone block,
6649  // note that this could release and reacquire
6650  // the mutexes hence cannot be done until after the
6651  // working set index has been removed.
6652  //
6653  // Flush the TB as this path could release the PFN lock.
6654  // Even though the process is terminating, a thread could
6655  // attach to it and try to reference the user address space.
6656  // By flushing the TB we ensure no access to free pages is
6657  // allowed.
6658  //
6659  // The PteDeleteList could be overloaded to save stack, but
6660  // using a separate list lets us flush just the entries since
6661  // the last call and still retain a pristine PteDeleteList
6662  // for debugging purposes.
6663  //
6664 
6665  while (j <= i) {
6666  ASSERT (PteFlushList.Count < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT);
6667  PteFlushList.FlushVa[PteFlushList.Count] = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PteDeleteList->PointerPte[j]);
6668  j += 1;
6669  PteFlushList.Count += 1;
6670  }
6671 
6672  MiDecrementCloneBlockReference (CloneDescriptor,
6673  CloneBlock,
6674  CurrentProcess,
6675  &PteFlushList,
6676  OldIrql);
6677 
6678  //
6679  // Note PteFlushList.Count will be set to 0 if
6680  // MiDecrementCloneBlockReference did a flush.
6681  //
6682  }
6683  }
6684  else {
6685 
6686  //
6687  // This PTE is NOT a prototype PTE, delete the physical page.
6688  //
6689  // Decrement the share and valid counts of the page table
6690  // page which maps this PTE.
6691  //
6692 
6693  PageTableFrameIndex = Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
6694  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
6695 
6696  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
6697 
6698  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
6699 
6700  //
6701  // Decrement the share count for the physical page. As the page
6702  // is private it will be put on the free list.
6703  //
6704 
6705  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
6706 
6707  //
6708  // Decrement the count for the number of private pages.
6709  //
6710 
6711  CurrentProcess->NumberOfPrivatePages -= 1;
6712 
6713  //
6714  // Set the pointer to PTE to be a demand zero PTE. This allows
6715  // the page usage count to be kept properly and handles the case
6716  // when a page table page has only valid PTEs and needs to be
6717  // deleted later when the VADs are removed.
6718  //
6719 
6720  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, DemandZeroWritePte);
6721  }
6722  }
6723 
6724  //
6725  // Flush the TB - even though the process is terminating, a thread could
6726  // attach to it and try to reference the user address space. By flushing
6727  // the TB we ensure no access to free pages is allowed.
6728  //
6729 
6730  MI_FLUSH_PROCESS_TB (FALSE);
6731 
6732  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6733 
6734  return;
6735 }
6736 
6737 PFN_NUMBER
6738 MiMakeOutswappedPageResident (
6739  IN PMMPTE ActualPteAddress,
6740  IN OUT PMMPTE PointerTempPte,
6741  IN ULONG Global,
6742  IN PFN_NUMBER ContainingPage,
6743  IN KIRQL OldIrql
6744  )
6745 
6746 /*++
6747 
6748 Routine Description:
6749 
6750  This routine makes the specified PTE valid.
6751 
6752 Arguments:
6753 
6754  ActualPteAddress - Supplies the actual address that the PTE will
6755  reside at. This is used for page coloring.
6756 
6757  PointerTempPte - Supplies the PTE to operate on, returns a valid PTE.
6758 
6759  Global - Supplies 1 if the resulting PTE is global.
6760 
6761  ContainingPage - Supplies the physical page number of the page which
6762  contains the resulting PTE. If this value is 0, no
6763  operations on the containing page are performed.
6764 
6765  OldIrql - Supplies the IRQL the caller acquired the PFN lock at.
6766 
6767 Return Value:
6768 
6769  Returns the physical page number that was allocated for the PTE.
6770 
6771 Environment:
6772 
6773  Kernel mode, PFN LOCK HELD - may be released and reacquired.
6774 
6775 --*/
6776 
6777 {
6778  MMPTE TempPte;
6779  MMPTE PteContents;
6780  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6781  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6782  PFN_NUMBER MdlHack[(sizeof(MDL)/sizeof(PFN_NUMBER)) + 1];
6783  PMDL Mdl;
6784  LARGE_INTEGER StartingOffset;
6785  KEVENT Event;
6786  IO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatus;
6787  PFN_NUMBER PageFileNumber;
6788  NTSTATUS Status;
6789  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
6790  ULONG RefaultCount;
6791 #if DBG
6792  PVOID HyperVa;
6793  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
6794 #endif
6795 
6796  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
6797 
6798 restart:
6799 
6800  ASSERT (PointerTempPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
6801 
6802  if (PointerTempPte->u.Long == MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE) {
6803 
6804  //
6805  // Any page will do.
6806  //
6807 
6808  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
6809  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
6810  }
6811 
6812  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (
6813  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (ActualPteAddress));
6814 
6815  if (Global) {
6816  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
6817  PageFrameIndex,
6818  MM_READWRITE,
6819  ActualPteAddress);
6820  }
6821  else {
6822  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte,
6823  PageFrameIndex,
6824  MM_READWRITE,
6825  ActualPteAddress);
6826  }
6827 
6828  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
6829 
6830  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPte, Global);
6831 
6832  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerTempPte, TempPte);
6833  MiInitializePfnForOtherProcess (PageFrameIndex,
6834  ActualPteAddress,
6835  ContainingPage);
6836 
6837  }
6838  else if (PointerTempPte->u.Soft.Transition == 1) {
6839 
6840  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (PointerTempPte);
6841  PointerTempPte->u.Trans.Protection = MM_READWRITE;
6842  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6843 
6844  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached);
6845 
6846  if ((MmAvailablePages == 0) ||
6847  ((Pfn1->u4.InPageError == 1) && (Pfn1->u3.e1.ReadInProgress == 1))) {
6848 
6849  //
6850  // This can only happen if the system is utilizing a hardware
6851  // compression cache. This ensures that only a safe amount
6852  // of the compressed virtual cache is directly mapped so that
6853  // if the hardware gets into trouble, we can bail it out.
6854  //
6855 
6856  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6857 
6858  KeDelayExecutionThread (KernelMode,
6859  FALSE,
6860  (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmHalfSecond);
6861  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6862  goto restart;
6863  }
6864 
6865  //
6866  // PTE refers to a transition PTE.
6867  //
6868 
6869  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation != ActiveAndValid) {
6870  MiUnlinkPageFromList (Pfn1);
6871 
6872  //
6873  // Even though this routine is only used to bring in special
6874  // system pages that are separately charged, a modified write
6875  // may be in progress and if so, will have applied a systemwide
6876  // charge against the locked pages count. This all works out nicely
6877  // (with no code needed here) as the write completion will see
6878  // the nonzero ShareCount and remove the charge.
6879  //
6880 
6881  InterlockedIncrementPfn ((PSHORT)&Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount);
6882  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
6883  }
6884 
6885  //
6886  // Update the PFN database, the share count is now 1 and
6887  // the reference count is incremented as the share count
6888  // just went from zero to 1.
6889  //
6890 
6891  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
6892 
6893  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x12);
6894 
6895  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0) {
6896 
6897  //
6898  // Release the page file space for this page.
6899  //
6900 
6901  MiReleasePageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6902  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
6903  }
6904 
6905  if (Global) {
6906  MI_MAKE_TRANSITION_KERNELPTE_VALID (TempPte, PointerTempPte);
6907  }
6908  else {
6909  MI_MAKE_TRANSITION_PTE_VALID (TempPte, PointerTempPte);
6910  }
6911 
6912  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
6913  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPte, Global);
6914  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerTempPte, TempPte);
6915  }
6916  else {
6917 
6918  //
6919  // Page resides in a paging file.
6920  // Any page will do.
6921  //
6922 
6923  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
6924  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
6925  }
6926 
6927  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (
6928  MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (ActualPteAddress));
6929 
6930  //
6931  // Initialize the PFN database element, but don't
6932  // set read in progress as collided page faults cannot
6933  // occur here.
6934  //
6935 
6936  MiInitializePfnForOtherProcess (PageFrameIndex,
6937  ActualPteAddress,
6938  ContainingPage);
6939 
6940  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6941 
6942  PointerTempPte->u.Soft.Protection = MM_READWRITE;
6943 
6944  KeInitializeEvent (&Event, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
6945 
6946  //
6947  // Calculate the VPN for the in-page operation.
6948  //
6949 
6950  TempPte = *PointerTempPte;
6951  PageFileNumber = GET_PAGING_FILE_NUMBER (TempPte);
6952 
6953  StartingOffset.QuadPart = (LONGLONG)(GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (TempPte)) <<
6954  PAGE_SHIFT;
6955 
6956  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6957 
6958  //
6959  // Build MDL for request.
6960  //
6961 
6962  Mdl = (PMDL)&MdlHack[0];
6963  MmInitializeMdl (Mdl,
6964  MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (ActualPteAddress),
6965  PAGE_SIZE);
6966  Mdl->MdlFlags |= MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
6967 
6968  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(Mdl + 1);
6969  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
6970 
6971 #if DBG
6972  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
6973 
6974  HyperVa = MiMapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, PageFrameIndex, &OldIrql);
6975  RtlFillMemoryUlong (HyperVa,
6976  PAGE_SIZE,
6977  0x34785690);
6978  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpace (CurrentProcess, HyperVa, OldIrql);
6979 #endif
6980 
6981  //
6982  // Issue the read request.
6983  //
6984 
6985  RefaultCount = 0;
6986 
6987 Refault:
6988  Status = IoPageRead (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->File,
6989  Mdl,
6990  &StartingOffset,
6991  &Event,
6992  &IoStatus);
6993 
6994  if (Status == STATUS_PENDING) {
6995  KeWaitForSingleObject (&Event,
6996  WrPageIn,
6997  KernelMode,
6998  FALSE,
6999  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
7000  Status = IoStatus.Status;
7001  }
7002 
7003  if (Mdl->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
7004  MmUnmapLockedPages (Mdl->MappedSystemVa, Mdl);
7005  }
7006 
7007  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
7008  if (IoStatus.Information != PAGE_SIZE) {
7009  KeBugCheckEx (KERNEL_STACK_INPAGE_ERROR,
7010  2,
7011  IoStatus.Status,
7012  PageFileNumber,
7013  StartingOffset.LowPart);
7014  }
7015  }
7016 
7017  if ((!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) || (!NT_SUCCESS(IoStatus.Status))) {
7018 
7019  if ((MmIsRetryIoStatus (Status)) ||
7020  (MmIsRetryIoStatus (IoStatus.Status))) {
7021 
7022  RefaultCount -= 1;
7023 
7024  if (RefaultCount & MiFaultRetryMask) {
7025 
7026  //
7027  // Insufficient resources, delay and reissue
7028  // the in page operation.
7029  //
7030 
7031  KeDelayExecutionThread (KernelMode,
7032  FALSE,
7033  (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmHalfSecond);
7034 
7035  KeClearEvent (&Event);
7036  goto Refault;
7037  }
7038  }
7039  KeBugCheckEx (KERNEL_STACK_INPAGE_ERROR,
7040  Status,
7041  IoStatus.Status,
7042  PageFileNumber,
7043  StartingOffset.LowPart);
7044  }
7045 
7046  PteContents = TempPte;
7047 
7048  if (Global) {
7049  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (TempPte,
7050  PageFrameIndex,
7051  MM_READWRITE,
7052  ActualPteAddress);
7053  }
7054  else {
7055  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte,
7056  PageFrameIndex,
7057  MM_READWRITE,
7058  ActualPteAddress);
7059  }
7060 
7061  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
7062 
7063  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPte, Global);
7064 
7065  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7066 
7067  //
7068  // Release the page file space.
7069  //
7070 
7071  MiReleasePageFileSpace (PteContents);
7072  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
7073  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached);
7074 
7075  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x13);
7076 
7077  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerTempPte, TempPte);
7078  }
7079  return PageFrameIndex;
7080 }

7083 UCHAR
7084 MiSetMemoryPriorityProcess (
7085  IN PEPROCESS Process,
7086  IN UCHAR MemoryPriority
7087  )
7088 
7089 /*++
7090 
7091 Routine Description:
7092 
7093  Nonpaged wrapper to set the memory priority of a process.
7094 
7095 Arguments:
7096 
7097  Process - Supplies the process to update.
7098 
7099  MemoryPriority - Supplies the new memory priority of the process.
7100 
7101 Return Value:
7102 
7103  Old priority.
7104 
7105 --*/
7106 
7107 {
7108  KIRQL OldIrql;
7109  UCHAR OldPriority;
7110 
7111  LOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
7112 
7113  OldPriority = (UCHAR) Process->Vm.Flags.MemoryPriority;
7114  Process->Vm.Flags.MemoryPriority = MemoryPriority;
7115 
7116  UNLOCK_EXPANSION (OldIrql);
7117 
7118  return OldPriority;
7119 }
7120 
7121 VOID
7122 MmSetMemoryPriorityProcess (
7123  IN PEPROCESS Process,
7124  IN UCHAR MemoryPriority
7125  )
7126 
7127 /*++
7128 
7129 Routine Description:
7130 
7131  Sets the memory priority of a process.
7132 
7133 Arguments:
7134 
7135  Process - Supplies the process to update
7136 
7137  MemoryPriority - Supplies the new memory priority of the process
7138 
7139 Return Value:
7140 
7141  None.
7142 
7143 --*/
7144 
7145 {
7146  if (MmSystemSize == MmSmallSystem && MmNumberOfPhysicalPages < ((15*1024*1024)/PAGE_SIZE)) {
7147 
7148  //
7149  // If this is a small system, make every process BACKGROUND.
7150  //
7151 
7152  MemoryPriority = MEMORY_PRIORITY_BACKGROUND;
7153  }
7154 
7155  MiSetMemoryPriorityProcess (Process, MemoryPriority);
7156 
7157  return;
7158 }
7159 
7160 
7161 PMMVAD
7162 MiAllocateVad (
7163  IN ULONG_PTR StartingVirtualAddress,
7164  IN ULONG_PTR EndingVirtualAddress,
7165  IN LOGICAL Deletable
7166  )
7167 
7168 /*++
7169 
7170 Routine Description:
7171 
7172  Reserve the specified range of address space.
7173 
7174 Arguments:
7175 
7176  StartingVirtualAddress - Supplies the starting virtual address.
7177 
7178  EndingVirtualAddress - Supplies the ending virtual address.
7179 
7180  Deletable - Supplies TRUE if the VAD is to be marked as deletable, FALSE
7181  if deletions of this VAD should be disallowed.
7182 
7183 Return Value:
7184 
7185  A VAD pointer on success, NULL on failure.
7186 
7187 --*/
7188 
7189 {
7190  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
7191 
7192  ASSERT (StartingVirtualAddress <= EndingVirtualAddress);
7193 
7194  if (Deletable == TRUE) {
7195  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool, sizeof(MMVAD_SHORT), 'SdaV');
7196  }
7197  else {
7198  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool, sizeof(MMVAD_LONG), 'ldaV');
7199  }
7200 
7201  if (Vad == NULL) {
7202  return NULL;
7203  }
7204 
7205  //
7206  // Set the starting and ending virtual page numbers of the VAD.
7207  //
7208 
7209  Vad->StartingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (StartingVirtualAddress);
7210  Vad->EndingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (EndingVirtualAddress);
7211 
7212  //
7213  // Mark VAD as no commitment, private, and readonly.
7214  //
7215 
7216  Vad->u.LongFlags = 0;
7217  Vad->u.VadFlags.CommitCharge = MM_MAX_COMMIT;
7218  Vad->u.VadFlags.Protection = MM_READONLY;
7219  Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory = 1;
7220 
7221  if (Deletable == TRUE) {
7222  ASSERT (Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange == 0);
7223  }
7224  else {
7225  Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange = 1;
7226  Vad->u2.LongFlags2 = 0;
7227  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.OneSecured = 1;
7228  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.LongVad = 1;
7229  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.ReadOnly = 1;
7230  Vad->u3.Secured.StartVpn = StartingVirtualAddress;
7231  Vad->u3.Secured.EndVpn = EndingVirtualAddress;
7232  }
7233 
7234  return (PMMVAD) Vad;
7235 }
7236 
7237 
7238 PFN_NUMBER
7239 MmGetDirectoryFrameFromProcess(
7240  IN PEPROCESS Process
7241  )
7242 
7243 /*++
7244 
7245 Routine Description:
7246 
7247  This routine retrieves the PFN of the process's top pagetable page. It can
7248  be used to map physical pages back to a process.
7249 
7250 Arguments:
7251 
7252  Process - Supplies the process to query.
7253 
7254 Return Value:
7255 
7256  Page frame number of the top level page table page.
7257 
7258 Environment:
7259 
7260  Kernel mode. No locks held.
7261 
7262 --*/
7263 
7264 {
7265  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () == PASSIVE_LEVEL);
7266  return MI_GET_DIRECTORY_FRAME_FROM_PROCESS(Process);
7267 }
